Sándor Juhász Nagy ( 13 October 1883 -- 10 May 1946 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as State Secretary of Religion and Education between 1918 and 1919 with ministerial competence .
Richard Duke ( 1658 - -1711 ) was an English clergyman and poet , associated with the Tory writers of the Restoration era .
Inese Jaunzeme ( 21 May 1932 -- 13 February 2011 ) was a Latvian athlete who competed mainly in the javelin throw .
Tsiang Tingfu ( Chinese : 蔣廷黻 ; pinyin : Jiǎng Tíngfú ; 17 February 1895 -- 9 October 1965 ) was a historian and diplomat of the Republic of China .
Huang Ruheng ( Chinese : 黃汝亨 , 1558 - -1626 ) was a noted Chinese calligrapher of the late Ming Dynasty .
Moses Wight ( 1827 - -1895 ) was an artist in Boston , Massachusetts and Paris in the 19th - century .
William Gordon , 6th Viscount of Kenmure and Lord Lochinvar ( c. 1672 -- 24 February 1716 ) was a Scottish Jacobite .
Ella Du Cane ( 1874 - 1943 ) was a British artist best known for her watercolors of landscapes and exotic locales .
Christopher McEvoy died at Dorking , England on 12 October 1953 following a prolonged illness .
Kristo Floqi ( 24 May 1872 -- 1951 ) was an Albanian patriot , playwright , politician , and lawyer .
Saint Hermann Joseph , O.Praem . , ( ca . 1150 -- 4 April 1241 ) was a German Premonstratensian canon regular and mystic .
Thomas B. Mitchell ( died 1876 ) was an American lawyer and politician from New York .
Hezekiah Woodward ( 1590 - -1675 ) was an English nonconformist minister and educator , also involved in the pamphlet wars of the 1640s .
Youra Eshaya Pera ( Syriac : ܝܘܪܐ ܐܫܥܝܐ , Arabic : يورا أيشايا‎ ) ( 1992 - -1933 ) is a former Iraqi and ethnic Assyrian and football player who was the first Iraqi player ever to play in Europe .
Hezekiah Burton ( 1632 - -1681 ) was an English theologian .
Alfanus II or Alfano II ( died 1121 ) was the Archbishop of Salerno from 1086/7 until his death , succeeding Alfanus I. Like his predecessor and his successor , Romuald I , he was a Lombard .
Dong Haichuan ( 13 October 1797 or 1813 -- 25 October 1882 ) is regarded as a skillful martial artist and is widely credited to be the founder of Baguazhang .
The Very Rev. Henry Richard Dawson ( 23 December 1792 -- 24 October 1840 ) was the Church of Ireland Dean of St. Patrick 's Cathedral , Dublin from 1828 to 1840 , and Rector of Castlecomer , County Kilkenny .
Mahmoud Tawalbe ( Arabic : محمود طوالبة‎ ; died 2002 ) was the head of the Palestinian Islamic Jihad in Jenin , one of the main strongholds of the Islamist organization .
Jean du Feynier ( died 1538 ) was the Master of the Order of Preachers from 1532 to 1538 .
Jackie Healy - Rae ( 9 March 1931 -- 5 December 2014 ) was an Irish politician who served as an independent Teachta Dála ( TD ) for the Kerry South constituency from 1997 to 2011 .
Ugo Frigerio ( 16 September 1901 -- 7 July 1968 ) was an Italian race walker .
Enguerrand de Monstrelet ( c. 1400 -- 20 July 1453 ) , was a French chronicler .
Anton Praetorius ( 1560 -- 6 December 1613 ) was a German Calvinist pastor who spoke out against the persecution of witches ( witchhunts , witchcraft trials ) and against torture .
John Siberch ( c.1476 - -1554 ) was the first Cambridge printer and an associate of Erasmus .
Martin Barry , MD , FRCPE , FRSE , FRS ( 28 March 1802 , Fratton , Portsmouth , Hampshire -- 27 April 1855 , Beccles , Suffolk ) , was a British physician who studied histology and embryology .
Paul Daneman ( 29 October 1925 -- 28 April 2001 ) was an English film , television , theatre and voice actor .
Mathurin Guillemé ( 3 July 1859 - 7 April 1942 ) was a Catholic White Fathers missionary who was Vicar Apostolic of Nyassa in today 's Malawi from 1911 until his resignation in 1934 .
Michael O'Reilly ( died 1758 ) was an Irish prelate of the Roman Catholic Church .
Sir George Cornewall Lewis , 2nd Baronet PC ( 21 April 1806 -- 13 April 1863 ) was a British statesman and man of letters .
Étienne Jeanneau ( also Janot or Geanneau ) ( c. 1668 -- 8 May 1743 ) was a Canadian merchant , court officer and notary , and militia officer .
Sister Gregory Kirkus ( 9 November 1910 -- 30 August 2007 ) was an English Roman Catholic nun , educator , historian and archivist .
Magdalena Moons ( 24 January 1541 , The Hague -- 15 June 1613 , Utrecht ) was famous for her role during the Dutch war of liberation , when she saved the city of Leiden during the siege by Spain in 1574 .
Ernst Zinner ( 2 February 1886 , in Goldberg , Silesia -- 30 August 1970 ) was a German astronomer and noted historian of astronomy .
Pryse Campbell ( 1727 -- 14 December 1768 ) , was a Scottish politician .
John Segrave , 2nd Baron Segrave ( 1256 - -1325 ) was an English commander in the First War of Scottish Independence .
Pope Innocent IX ( Latin : Innocentius IX ; 20 July 1519 -- 30 December 1591 ) , born Giovanni Antonio Facchinetti , was Pope from 29 October to 30 December 1591 .
Thomas Minton ( 1765 -- 1836 ) was an English potter .
Aubrey de Sélincourt ( 7 June 1894 -- 20 December 1962 ) was an English writer , classical scholar and translator .
Edgar Barth ( 26 January 1917 -- 20 May 1965 ) was a German ( East German until 1957 , then West German ) Formula One and sports car racing driver .
Samuel Booth ( 1775 - -1842 ) , the father of William Booth , was born in Belper , Amber Valley , Derbyshire , England .
Frank O'Donovan ( 10 October 1900 -- 28 June 1974 ) was an Irish actor , singer and songwriter .
Sir Claude Aurelius Elliott OBE , MA , ( 27 July 1888 - 21 November 1973 ) was Head Master of Eton College at Windsor in Berkshire , and was later Provost at the same school .
Atulkrishna Ghosh ( Bengali : অতুলকৃষ্ণ ঘোষ ) ( 1890 - -1966 ) was an Indian revolutionary , member of the Anushilan Samiti , and a leader of the Jugantar movement involved in Hindu German Conspiracy during World War I.
Sydney Box ( 29 April 1907 -- 25 May 1983 ) was a British film producer and screenwriter , and brother of British film producer Betty Box .
Floyer Sydenham ( 1710 -- 1 April 1787 ) was an English scholar of Ancient Greek .
Jevstatije II ( Serbian : Јевстатије II ) was the Archbishop of Serbs from 1292 to 1309 .
William Burke , 7th Earl of Clanricarde ( died 1687 ) , Irish peer , was the son of Sir William Burke , younger son of Ulick Burke , 3rd Earl of Clanricarde , and Joan O'Shaughnessy .
Malak Hifni Nasif ( 25 December 1886 -- 17 October 1918 ) was an Egyptian feminist who contributed greatly to the intellectual and political discourse on the advancement of Egyptian women in the early 20th century .
Kurt Lundqvist ( 20 November 1914 -- 26 March 1976 ) was a Swedish track and field athlete who competed in the high jump .
Elijah Allsopp ( 1877 - 1958 ) was a footballer who played in The Football League for Notts County .
Edward Jurith ( born 1951 , died November , 2013 ) served as Acting Director of the Office of National Drug Control Policy from January 10 , 2001 to December 7 , 2001 .
Edward Metcalfe ( 1792 -- 7 May 1847 ) was a British Benedictine scholar .
Jeanne Brabants ( 25 January 1920 -- 2 January 2014 ) was a Belgian dancer , choreographer and teacher .
Alice Brooke Bodington or Alice Brook ( 1840 -- 1897 ) was a researcher and writer in the field of biology and evolution .
Martin Billingsley ( 1591 - -1622 ) was an English writing - master , a successor in giving advice on handwriting to Peter Bales .
Joseph William Allen ( 1803 -- August 29 1852 ) was an English landscape painter and art teacher , who was also active in the founding of the Society of British Artists .
William Hodge Mill ( 1792 - -1853 ) was an English churchman and orientalist , the first principal of Bishop 's College , Calcutta and later Regius Professor of Hebrew at Cambridge .
Roger Jones , 1st Viscount Ranelagh PC ( Ire ) ( before 1589 -- 1643 ) was a member of the Peerage of Ireland and lord president of Connaught .
Frank Adamo ( 1893 -- 1988 ) was an American doctor honored for his medical service during World War II . He rose to the rank of Lieutenant Colonel and was awarded a Legion of Merit medal for his service .
Thomas Oikonomou ( Greek : Θωμάς Οικονόμου , 1864 - -1927 ) was a Greek actor and one of the first modern Greek directors .
Andrew Sall ( 1612 - -1682 ) was an Irish Jesuit , later a convert to the Church of England .
Carlos Pedrell ( 16 October 1878 -- 9 March 1941 ) was a Uruguayan composer , guitarist and educator .
Frederick Perry Fish ( 13 January 1855 -- 6 November 1930 ) was an American lawyer and executive who served as president of American Telephone & Telegraph Corporation from 1901 to 1907 .
Nicholas Albery ( 28 July 1948 -- 3 June 2001 ) social inventor and author , was the founder or leader of various projects related to the improvement of society , often known as the alternative society .
Edwin Augustus Rigg ( 1822 - -1882 ) , 49er , was a military officer in the American Civil War and the Apache Wars .
Albert Besson ( 1896 - -1965 ) was a French hygienist , physician and member of the French Académie Nationale de Médecine .
Hu Xiansu or Hu Hsien - Hsu ( simplified Chinese : 胡先骕 ; traditional Chinese : 胡先驌 ; pinyin : Hú Xiānsù , 24 May 1894 -- 16 July 1968 ) , was a Chinese botanist and an influential traditional scholar of his time .
Henry Eld died at sea on board U. S. ship of war Ohio on March 12 , 1850 , bound home from Rio de Janeiro after a three and a half years ' cruise .
Attilio Bettega ( 19 February 1953 -- 2 May 1985 ) was an Italian rally driver .
Bernhard Rensch ( 21 January 1900 -- 4 April 1990 ) was a German evolutionary biologist , and ornithologist who did field work in Indonesia and India .
Brenda Irene Isabelle Frances Theresa Dean Paul ( 8 May 1907 -- 26 July 1959 ) , generally known by her stage name Brenda Dean Paul , was a British silent film actress and socialite , and a member of the Bright young things in the 1920s .
Martin Sperr ( 14 September 1944 -- 6 April 2002 ) was a German dramatist and actor .
Sir Isaac Holden , 1st Baronet ( 7 May 1807 -- 13 August 1897 ) was an inventor and manufacturer , who is known both for his work in developing the Square Motion wool - combing machine with wool - combing and as a Radical Liberal Member of Parliament .
Bartolomeo Cittadella ( 1636 - -1704 ) , a painter of the Venetian school , who , according to Guarienti , flourished at Vicenza in the latter part of the seventeenth century .
Thomas Scott Turnbull ( 28 October 1825 -- 22 March 1880 ) was the son of a Newcastle saddler .
Goffredo Cappa ( 1644 - -1717 ) , also known as Gioffredo Cappa or Jofredus Cappa , was an Italian luthier , known for his violins and cellos .
Lou Zhaojun ( Chinese : 婁昭君 ; 501 - -562 ) , formally Empress Ming ( 明皇后 , literally `` the understanding empress '' ) , was an empress dowager of the Chinese dynasty Northern Qi .
Andrew Aldcorn ( c.1792 -- 13 August 1877 ) was an Australian medical practitioner and politician .
Jonathan Smedley ( 1671 - -1729 ) was an Anglo - Irish churchman who became Dean of Clogher in 1724 .
Mikael Pedersen ( 25 October 1855 Fløng - 22 October 1929 , Bispebjerg ) was a Danish inventor much associated with the English town of Dursley .
Henriette of Cleves ( 31 October 1542 -- 24 June 1601 ) was a French noblewoman and heiress of the Cleves - Nevers family .
Giovanni Sarnelli ( June 23 , 1714 in Naples -- 1793 in Naples ) was an Italian painter of the late - Baroque style .
Ernie Pye ( 25 April 1880 -- 3 May 1954 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
George Lawson Johnston , 1st Baron Luke , KBE ( 9 September 1873 -- 23 February 1943 ) , was a British businessman .
David Lennox ( 1788 -- 12 November 1873 ) was a Scottish - Australian bridge - builder and master stonemason born in Ayr , Scotland .
Rabbi Chaim Kamil ( 1933 - -2005 ) was the Rosh Yeshiva in the Yeshiva of Ofakim , Israel .
Károly Vántus ( 20 February 1879 -- 1927 ) was a Hungarian politician and carpenter , who served as People 's Commissar of Agriculture during the Hungarian Soviet Republic .
Margaretha Kirch ( b. ca . 1703 , d. after 1744 ) was a German astronomer .
Sir Robert Fagge , 2nd Baronet ( ca . 1649 -- 22 August 1715 ) was an English politician .
Lydia Gibson ( 1891 - 1964 ) was an American socialist illustrator who contributed work to The Masses , The Liberator , The Workers ' Monthly , The New Masses , and other radical publications .
Sir John Johnstone , 1st Baronet ( died 30 September 1711 ) was a Scottish Army officer and a politician .
Infante António of Portugal ( Portuguese pronunciation : ( ɐ̃ˈtɔniu ) ) ( Lisbon , 15 March 1695 - Lisbon , 20 October 1757 ) was a Portuguese infante ( prince ) , the third surviving son of Peter II , King of Portugal , and his wife Maria Sophia of Neuburg .
Neil Chotem ( 9 September 1920 , Saskatoon - 21 February 2008 , Greenfield Park , Quebec ) was a Canadian composer , arranger , conductor , pianist , and music educator .
Thomas Henry Barclay ( 12 October 1753 -- 21 April 1830 ) was an American lawyer who became one of the United Empire Loyalists in Nova Scotia and served in the colony 's government .
Wilfred Hawker ( 1955 -- 13 March 1982 ) was a sergeant - major in the Surinamese military who was involved in two unsuccessful coup d'états in the early 1980s .
Brigadier General Dr. Mikuláš Ferjenčík ( 6 December 1904 -- 4 March 1988 ) was a Czechoslovak military veterinarian , resistance fighter , and exiled politician .
General Sir Anthony Blaxland Stransham , GCB ( 22 December 1805 -- October 1900 ) , was a British military officer .
Vera Eugenia Andrus ( 1895 - 1979 ) was an American artist , and printmaker .
Juan Cuevas Perales ( 8 February 1782 in Guadassuar -- 1855 ) was a Valencian composer in the Classical style .
Johan Georg Geitel ( 1683 - -1771 ) , also Johann or Hans Jürgen Geitell , Geittel or Geittell , was a Finnish painter .
Thomas Monroe Campbell ( 1883 -- 1956 ) was the first Cooperative Extension Agent in the United States and headed the first Extension Program as a field agent for the U.S. Department of Agriculture .
( Arthur ) Paul Boissier ( 25 January 1881 -- 2 October 1953 ) was an English schoolmaster who was headmaster of Harrow School , and a war time civil servant .
Gaspar Dias ( died 1671 ) , a Portuguese painter , studied at Rome under Raphael and Michelangelo , and on his return home devoted himself to the production of church pictures .
Francesco Guarino or Guarini ( 1611 - 1651 or 1654 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , active mainly in the mountainous area east of Naples called Irpinia , and in other areas of the Kingdom of Naples , chiefly Campania , Apulia , and Molise .
Lou Lilly ( February 26 , 1909 -- August 9 , 1999 ) was an American animator , screenwriter and director best known for his work on the Looney Tunes and Merrie Melodies series of cartoons from Warner Bros ..
Carl Gottfried Woide ( German : Karl Gottfried Woide ) ( 4 July 1725 -- 9 May 1790 ) , also known in England as Charles Godfrey Woide , was an Orientalist and Biblical scholar .
Robert Gillow ( 1704 - -1772 ) was an English furniture manufacturer , who founded Gillow & Co.
John Jones Bateman ( 1817 - 1903 ) was an English architect , active in the town ( later city ) of Birmingham , where he designed a number of important civic buildings , and nonconformist churches , often in partnership with George Drury .
Jack Hale ( 2 January 1913 -- 25 June 2001 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the VFL during the 1930s before becoming a coach .
Fritz Klein ( 24 November 1888 -- 13 December 1945 ) was a German Nazi physician hanged for his role in atrocities at Bergen - Belsen concentration camp during the Holocaust .
James McMillan Shafter ( May 27 , 1816 - -August 29 , 1892 ) was an American politician who served in Vermont , Wisconsin , and California .
Angelos Pitzamanos ( Greek : Άγγελος Πιτζαμάνος ) ( 1467 - -1535 ) was a Greek Renaissance painter .
Abu al - Aswad al - Du'ali ( Arabic : أبو الأسود الدؤلي‎ ) ( ca . 603CE/16BH -- 688 or 689CE/69AH ) was a close companion of Ali ibn Abi Talib and a grammarian .
Henry Randall Waite ( born Copenhagen , New York , 16 December 1845 ; died East Orange , New Jersey , 8 May 1909 ) was a United States editor and clergyman .
Edward Solomon ( 25 July 1855 -- 22 January 1895 ) was a prolific English composer , as well as a conductor , orchestrator and pianist .
John Fleming , 5th Lord Fleming ( 1529 - -6 September 1572 ) supporter of Mary Queen of Scots .
Petro Stebnytsky ( 1862 -- 1923 ) was a Ukrainian political and public figure , diplomat and statesman .
Karel Breydel or Carel Breydel , called ' Le Chevalier ' ( 1678 , Antwerp - 1733 , Antwerp ) was a Flemish painter of battle pieces , equestrian paintings and landscapes .
Guglielma Pallavicini ( rarely Wilhelmina ; died 1358 ) , the Lady of Thermopylae , was the last Pallavicino heir to rule in Bodonitsa .
Elena Petrová , née Krupková ( 9 November 1929 -- 2002 ) was a Czech composer .
Dr. Murray Thurston Titus ( 1885 - -October 31 , 1964 ) was an American missionary in India especially known for encouraging understanding between Christians and Muslims .
Sándor Bihari ( 19 May 1855 , Rézbánya - 28 March 1906 , Budapest ) was a Jewish Hungarian genre painter .
Father Michael O'Flanagan ( Irish : An tAthair Mícheál Ó Flannagáin ) ( 1876 -- 7 August 1942 ) was a Roman Catholic priest , Irish language scholar and Irish republican active in Sinn Féin , of which he was President in 1933 - -35 .
Al Crowder ( 1904 - 1981 ) was an American radio host , music teacher and humorist , best known as the creator of the BunaB line of products .
Fleming Williams ( December 26 , 1943 in Flint , Michigan -- February 15 , 1998 in Flint , Michigan ) was an American singer known as a member of the group The Hues Corporation and as the lead singer on their hit `` Rock the Boat '' .
Princess Krystyna Radziwiłł ( 11 September 1560 - -28 February 1580 ) was a Polish - Lithuanian szlachcianka ( noblewoman ) .
Charles Jefferys ( 11 January 1807 - 9 June 1865 , in London ) was an English music publisher and composer of songs .
Florence Yoch ( 1890 - -1972 ) was an American landscape architect in California who was active from 1915 through the 1950s .
Ludwig Karl Schmarda ( 23 August 1819 -- 7 April 1908 ) was an Austrian naturalist and traveler , born at Olmütz , Moravia .
Om Prakash Aditya ( 5 November 1936 -- 8 June 2009 ) was a renowned hindi poet and satirist .
Yasovarman II ( Khmer : យសោវរ្ម័នទី២ ) was the ruler of the Khmer empire from 1160 to 1166 .
Brahmadeva ( 1060 - -1130 ) was an Indian mathematician .
Blessed Veronica of Milan ( c. 1445 -- 13 January 1497 ) was an Italian nun in the Augustinian Order .
Yu Hyeong - won ( 1622 - -1673 ) was a politician and Neo - Confucianism scholar and science scholar of the Korean Joseon Dynasty .
David Ellis Evans FBA ( 23 September 1930 -- 26 September 2013 ) was a Welsh scholar and academic .
K'ak ' Tiliw Chan Yopaat ruled the city from 724 to 785 AD .
Sir George Alfred Wills , 1st Baronet ( 3 June 1854 -- 11 July 1928 ) was a President of Imperial Tobacco and the head of an eminent Bristol family .
Chế Mân , or Jaya Simhavarman III ( r. 1288 - 1307 ) , Prince Harijit , son of King Indravarman V and Queen Gaurendraksmi , was a king of Champa during a time when the threat of the Mongols was imminent .
Edward Kassner ( 28 February 1920 -- 19 November 1996 ) was an Austrian - born music industry executive and songwriter who was responsible for establishing the music publisher Kassner Music and the President record label .
Manuel Herrera y Obes ( 1806 - -1890 ) was an Uruguayan politician and diplomat , and one of the main leaders of the government of Montevideo ( `` La Defensa '' ) during the Uruguayan civil war ( `` La Guerra Grande '' ) .
Julie von May ( von Rued ) ( 1808 - 1875 ) , was a Swiss feminist .
Xie Ai ( simplified Chinese : 谢艾 ; traditional Chinese : 謝艾 ; pinyin : Xiè ài , 301 - -354 ) was a general for the Chinese state Former Liang who served under Zhang Chonghua .
Nick Duncombe ( January 21 , 1982 -- February 14 , 2003 ) was an English rugby union footballer who played for Harlequins and England .
Sue Lloyd ( 7 August 1939 -- 20 October 2011 ) was an English model turned actress with numerous film and television credits .
Austin Dabney ( c. 1765 - 1830 ) was a slave who fought against the British in the American Revolutionary War .
Sir Eric Alexander Buchanan , 3rd Baronet ( 19 August 1848 -- 29 July 1928 ) was the 3rd Baronet Buchanan of Dunburgh .
Remişnaz Hanımefendi ( 1864 - 1934 , birth name Fehime , other names Rems - şinaz , Remzşinas ) was the wife of Murad V , Deposed Ottoman Sultan .
Adrián de Alesio ( also Adrián Alesio ) ( died 1650 ) was a Peruvian painter and poet .
William Howard Durham ( 1873 - -1912 ) was an early Pentecostal preacher and theologian , best known for advocating the Finished Work doctrine .
Giuseppe Silvestri ( 1841 - 1921 ) was an Italian classical composer and mandolin virtuoso .
Derek Oldbury ( 1924 - July , 1994 ) ( often known as DEO ) was a British draughts champion from Devon .
Clarence Preston Gillette ( 7 April 1859 , Maple Corners , Ionia County , Michigan--4 January 1941 , Fort Collins , Colorado ) was an American entomologist .
Gustav Adolf Wislicenus ( 20 November 1803 Battaune , Prussian Saxony - 14 October 1875 Zurich ) was a German theologian , one of the leaders of the Free Congregations .
Cú Connacht Ua Dálaigh , ( aka Cu Chonnacht na Sgoile , `` Cu Connacht of the school '' ) , died 1139 .
Benito Espinós ( 1748 - -1818 ) was a Spanish painter , active in Valencia and mainly painting still life floral arrangements .
Adrien Albert ( 19 November 1907 in Sydney -- 29 December 1989 in Canberra ) was a leading authority in the development of medicinal chemistry in Australia .
Egon Kornauth ( 14 May 1891 -- 28 October 1959 ) was an Austrian composer and music teacher .
Arie Nicolaas Habermann ( 26 June 1932 -- 8 August 1993 ) , often known as Nico Habermann , was a noted Dutch computer scientist .
Margaret Essex ( 1775 - -1807 ) was an English composer of chamber and vocal music .
William Abbotts ( 1736 -- 1 March 1805 ) was one of the founding fathers of Leamington Spa in Warwickshire , UK .
Jai Singh III ( 25 April 1819 -- 6 February 1835 ) , was the Maharaja of Jaipur State from 1819 until 1835 .
Charles Dalziel ( 1904 - -1986 ) was a professor of electrical engineering and computer sciences at UC Berkeley .
José María Jesús Carbajal ( 1809 - -1874 ) ( also spelled Carvajal , Caravajal , Carabajal and Carbahal ) was a Mexican freedom fighter , who opposed the Centralist government installed by Antonio López de Santa Anna .
Robert William Mylne , FRS ( 14 June 1817 -- 2 July 1890 ) was a British architect , civil engineer and geologist .
The Master of the Mansi Magdalen ( c.1490 -- 1530 ) , was an Early Netherlandish painter .
Francisco Parra Duperón ( 1827 - -1899 ) born in Mayagüez , Puerto Rico , was a lawyer and banker .
Edward Betham ( 1707 - -1783 ) was a scholar and divine and was educated at Eton college , and in 1728 proceeded to King 's College , Cambridge .
Ralph Emmerson ( 7 July 1913 -- 31 December 2007 ) was Bishop of Knaresborough from 1972 to 1979 .
John Deare ( 26 October 1759 , Liverpool -- 17 August 1798 , Rome ) was a British neo - classical sculptor .
Mary ' Ajami ( 1888−1965 ) was a feminist and pioneering Arabic - language writer .
Maulana Yakub Hasan Sait ( Urdu : یعقوب حسن سیت‎ ) or simply Yakub Hasan Sait ( 1875 -- 1940 ) was an Indian businessman , freedom - fighter and politician who served as the Minister for Public Works in the Madras Presidency from 1937 to 1939 .
Ann Pitt ( -- 18 December 1799 ) was a British actress .
Godfrey of Hohenstaufen , known in Italian as Goffredo , Gotofredo or Gotifredo ( died 9 October 1194 ) , was Patriarch of Aquileia in northern Italy from 1182 to 1194 .
Charles Thynne ( c 1568 - 1652 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1614 and 1629 .
Bernard D. Rubin ( c. 1893 -- July 6 , 1948 ) was president and chief executive officer of Sweets Company of America , makers of the famous Tootsie Rolls , from 1936 to his death in July 1948 .
Harmon Percy Marble ( born November 5 , 1870 in Pawnee County , Nebraska -- died 1945 ) was a mayor in Las Vegas and photographer of Native Americans .
William Rathbone III ( 1726 - -1789 ) was a member of the noted Rathbone family of Liverpool .
Ivan Lychov ( Russian : Иван Лычев ) ( 30 May 1881 - 16 November 1972 ) was a Soviet politician .
Tito Moretti ( Perugia , 1840 - 1913 ) was an Italian painter and manuscript illuminator .
Sheva Ausubel ( 1896 - -1957 ) was an American painter , and textile artist .
Redd Harper ( born September 29 , 1903 in Nocona , Texas , USA - d. February 16 , 1992 in Los Angeles , California , USA ) , also known as Mr. Texas , was an American composer , author , singer , actor , and evangelist .
William H. McElfatrick ( 1854 - 29 September 1922 ) was an American architect who specialized in theaters .
Agim Qirjaqi ( 1950 -- 28 March 2010 ) was an Albanian actor and television director .
Epaphroditos , Tiberios Klaudios Epaphroditos or Tiberius Claudius Epaphroditus or Epaphroditus ( Greek : Ἐπαφρόδιτος ; born c. 20 - -25 -- died c. 95 ) , was a freedman and secretary of the Roman Emperor Nero .
Carlyle Jones ( 3 April 1904 -- 2 February 1951 , referred to as Tom Jones in some sources ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne and St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Kate Cruise O'Brien ( 1948 -- 26 May 1998 ) was an Irish writer .
Salim Chishti ( 1478 -- 1572 ) ( Hindi : सलीम चिश्ती , Urdu : سلیم چشتی ‎ ) was a Sufi saint of the Chishti Order during the Mughal Empire in India .
Vishnupant Govind Damle ( 14 October 1892 -- 5 July 1945 ) was an Indian production designer , cinematographer , film director and sound engineer for Marathi films .
Helmut Newton ( born Helmut Neustädter ; 31 October 1920 -- 23 January 2004 ) was a German - Australian photographer .
George Leslie Norris FRSL ( 21 May 1921 -- 6 April 2006 ) , was a prize - winning Welsh poet and short story writer .
Élise Bruyère ( 1776 - -1847 ) was a French painter who specialized in portraits and floral still lifes .
Naz Khialvi ( 1947 -- 12 December 2010 ) was a Pakistani lyricist and radio broadcaster , who is mainly known for his Sufi verse Tum Ek Gorakh Dhanda Ho ( You are a Puzzle ) , later sung by Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan , a legendary Qawwali singer , making both of them a household name .
Emlen T. Littel ( 1840 - 1891 ) was an American architect active in New York City and Philadelphia .
Jacob Kamm ( 12 December 1823 -- 16 December 1912 ) was a prominent early transportation businessman in Oregon , USA .
Sir George Frederic Verdon ( 21 January 1834 - 13 August 1896 ) was an English Australian politician and public figure .
Elizabeth Raffald ( 1733 -- 19 April 1781 ) was an English businesswoman , remembered chiefly for her 1769 book The Experienced English Housekeeper .
James Ajibola Idowu Ige , SAN ( Yoruba : Bọ́lá Ìgè ; 13 September 1930 -- 23 December 2001 ) simply known as Bola Ige was a Nigerian lawyer and politician .
Horace Percy Smith ( 1858 -- 12 July 1928 ) was a British chartered accountant in Hong Kong .
Robert Fielding ( or Feilding ; also nicknamed Beau Fielding ; 1650/51 -- 12 May 1712 ) was an English bigamist and rake in the late 17th and early 18th centuries .
Percy Humphreys ( 3 December 1880 -- 13 April 1959 ) was an English international footballer , who played at inside - right , who later became a football manager .
Žarko Petan ( 27 March 1929 -- 2 May 2014 ) was a Slovenian writer , essayist , screenwriter , and theatre and film director .
Nguyễn Sinh Khiêm ( 1888 - -1950 ) , renamed Nguyễn Tất Đạt in accordance with Confucian tradition , was the brother of President Hồ Chí Minh of Việt Nam .
Jakob Christoph Blarer von Wartensee ( 11 May 1542 -- 18 April 1608 ) was a Bishop of Basel and a leader in the Counter - Reformation in the region around Basel .
Kalmi Baruh ( Serbian Cyrillic : Калми Барух ) ; 26 December 1896 - 1945 ) was a Bosnian Jewish scholar in the field of Judeo - Spanish language , pioneer of the Sephardic studies and Hispanic studies in former Yugoslavia .
James King , 5th Earl of Kingston ( 8 April 1800 - 8 September 1869 ) , styled The Honourable James King between 1839 and 1867 , was an Irish peer .
Rodney Needham ( 15 May 1923 -- 4 December 2006 in Oxford ) was one of the leading British social anthropologists .
Douglas Alexandra ( 6 February 1922 -- 19 February 2000 ) was an Australian architect , whose works were an important contribution to modernist architecture in Melbourne , Australia .
Al - Hadi Ali ( 1345/46 -- September 6 , 1432 ) was a claimant to the Zaidi state in Yemen , who posed as imam from 1393 to 1432 in rivalry with another prince .
Wilfred Gibson ( born 28 February 1942 -- October 2014 ) was an English violinist who played in the band Electric Light Orchestra , and had performed as a session musician .
Du Xinwu ( Chinese : 杜心武 ; Wade -- Giles : Tu Hsin - wu ; 1869 - -1953 ) , aka Ru Xia ( 儒侠 ) , Dou Mi Guan Jushi ( 斗米观居士 ) was a Chinese martial artist and an important figure in the development of Zi Ran Men kung fu .
Francisco Díaz Pimienta ( 1594 - -1652 ) was a Spanish naval officer who became Captain general of the Ocean Fleet .
Arthur S. Martin ( ? -1 February 1996 ) was a member of the British intelligence community and a primary investigator in the spy scandals in the post - war era .
Edward Powell ( c.1478 -- 30 July 1540 ) was a Welsh Roman Catholic priest and theologian , in opposition to Henry VIII of England .
May McKisack ( 1900 - -1981 ) was a British medieval historian .
Major Bakshi Tirath Ram Vaid , O.B.I , O.B.E. , ( 1857 - 1924 ) , was a soldier of the British Indian Army .
Gretchen Franklin ( 7 July 1911 -- 11 July 2005 ) was an English actress and dancer with a career in show business spanning over eighty years .
Djawoto ( Perfected Spelling : Jawoto ; August 10 , 1906 -- 1992 ) was an Indonesian journalist and diplomat .
Dith Pran ( Khmer : ឌិត ប្រន ; 27 September 1942 -- 30 March 2008 ) was a Cambodian photojournalist best known as a refugee and survivor of the Cambodian Genocide .
Artur Mkrtchyan ( Armenian : Արթուր Մկրտչյան ; 16 February 1959 -- 14 April 1992 ) was the First Chairman of Supreme Council of the Nagorno - Karabakh Republic , elected on January 7 , 1992 .
Sergeant Patrick Joseph Morrissey ( 7 March 1936 -- 27 June 1985 ) was a member of the Garda Síochána , the national police service of Ireland , killed in the line of duty by the INLA .
Tuhbenahneequay ( 1780 - -1873 ) was a Mississauga Indian from the Burlington Heights area of Upper Canada .
Wilfred Mitford Davies ( 23 February 1895 -- March 1966 ) was a Welsh artist and publisher , best known for his work with the Cymru'r Plant imprint to produce children 's reading matter in the Welsh language .
Francis Wilford - Smith ( 12 March 1927 - 4 December 2009 ) was a British cartoonist , graphic artist , and producer and archivist of blues music .
Denis T. O'Connor C.S.B. ( 28 March 1841 -- 30 June 1911 ) was the Roman Catholic Archbishop of Toronto from 1899 to 1908 and the first Canadian born Archbishop of Toronto and the first Canadian head of the diocese since Michael Power .
Liu Chengyou ( 劉承祐 ) ( 28 March 931 -- 2 January 951 ) , also known by his posthumous name Emperor Yin ( 隱皇帝 ) , was the 2nd and final emperor of imperial China 's short - lived Later Han during the Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period , reigning from 948 until his death .
Edida Nageswara Rao ( 24 April 1934 -- 4 October 2015 ) was an Indian film producer in Telugu cinema .
Ernst , Prince of Saxe - Meiningen ( Ernst , Prinz von Sachsen - Meiningen ; 27 September 1859 -- 29 December 1941 ) was the head of the house of Saxe - Meiningen from 1928 until his death .
Michael Forster ( 1907 - -2002 ) was an Anglo - Canadian abstract artist .
Narayan Singh Bhati ( 1930 - -2004 ) was a prominent writer in Rajasthani language .
Thomas Washbourne ( 1606 - -1687 ) was an English clergyman and poet , known for his 1654 book Divine Poems .
Iris von Roten - Meyer ( 2 April 1917 -- 11 September 1990 ) was a Swiss journalist , writer , feminist and jurist .
Manibhushan Bhattacharya ( 1938 - -2014 ) was a major poet who transformed the language of Bengali poetry in the late 1960s and early 1970s .
Yuan Ye ( 元曄 ) ( died 532 ) , courtesy name Huaxing ( 華興 ) , nickname Penzi ( 盆子 ) , often known as the Prince of Changguang ( 長廣王 ) , was briefly an emperor of the Xianbei dynasty Northern Wei .
Bimi Ombale ( 21 July 1952- 29 April 2011 , born Andre Bimi Ombale , also known as Andre Bimi , Bimi Ombale , Mwana Wabi ) was a Congolese singer , drummer and song writer .
Anatoly Cherepovich ( Ukrainian : Анатолій Черепович ; 30 July 1936 -- 2 August 1970 ) was a Ukrainian cyclist .
Cornelius Høyer ( 1741 -- 2 June 1804 ) was a Danish painter , mainly known for his work in miniatures .
Francisco Majewski ( 1 May 1939 -- 22 April 2012 ) was a professional footballer who played in the Uruguayan Primera División and Mexican Primera División .
Admiral The Honourable Duncombe Pleydell - Bouverie ( 28 June 1780 -- 5 November 1850 ) , was a British naval commander and Whig politician .
Hugh Kennedy ( 11 July 1879 -- 1 December 1936 ) was the only Attorney General of Southern Ireland and the first Attorney General of the Irish Free State , and later the first Chief Justice of the Irish Free State .
Antonino Caponnetto ( 5 September 1920 -- 6 December 2002 ) was an Italian Antimafia magistrate .
John Blake Powell , PC ( Ire ) , KC ( 1870 -- 13 September 1923 ) was an Irish solicitor , barrister and judge .
Samuel Hood Linzee ( 27 December 1773 -- 1 September 1820 ) was an admiral of the British Royal Navy who served during the French Revolutionary and Napoleonic Wars .
José Joaquín de la Santísima Trinidad Moraga ( August 22 , 1745 -- 1785 ) ( usually known as José Joaquín Moraga ) was a soldier in the army of New Spain , and member of an early expedition to Alta California .
Kyriakoulis Argyrokastritis ( Greek : Κυριακούλης Αργυροκαστρίτης ; died 1828 ) also known as Kyriakoulis Polychronis was a Greek resistance leader of the Greek War of Independence .
Sunifred II of Cerdanya ( 915 - Cuxa , 968 ) was count of Cerdanya ( 927 - 968 ) , Conflent ( 927 - 968 ) , and Besalú ( 957 - 968 ) .
Marie - Thérèse Figueur ( Talmay , 17 January 1774 -- Paris , hospice des Petits Ménages , 4 January 1861 ) , known by the nom de guerre Sans - Gêne ( literally `` unconstrained '' ) , was a French heroine who fought in the French Revolutionary Wars and Napoleonic Wars .
Watanabe Shōtei aka Watanabe Seitei ( 1851 in Edo -- 1918 ) was a Nihonga painter and one of the first to visit Europe , attending the 1878 International Exhibition in Paris and being awarded a medal .
Tufa Wugu ( Chinese : 禿髮烏孤 ; died 399 ) , formally Prince Wu of Wuwei ( 武威武王 ) , was the founding prince of the Xianbei state Southern Liang .
Simon Frug ( Russian : Семён Григо́рьевич Фру́г ; IPA : ( sʲɪˈmʲɵn ɡrʲɪˈɡorʲjɪvʲɪtɕ ˈfruk ) ; 15 November 1860 -- 22 September 1916 ) was a multi - lingual Russian poet , lyricist and author .
Amr ibn Khalid al - Bariqi al - Azdi(Arabic : عمرو بن خالد‎ ; died 680 ) was one of the Companions of Husayn ibn Ali , who was martyred along with him in the battle of Karbala .
John J. Dunnigan ( September 6 , 1883 - December 1965 ) was an American architect , builder and politician from New York .
Antonio De Santis , Totò ( Italian pronunciation : ( toˈtɔ ) ; 17 October 1931 - 4 April 2014 ) was an Italian poet , famous for his sonnets in Larinese , the dialect of Larino .
Enrique Dávila Pacheco ( 15 ? ? -- 1663 ) was a royal ambassador of Spain , Acting Governor and Captain General of Yucatán , Governor of Nueva Vizcaya and Governor of Tlaxcala .
Adrian Bell ( 4 October 1901 - -1980 ) was an English ruralist journalist and farmer , and the first compiler of The Times crossword .
John Spencer , 1st Earl Spencer ( 19 December 1734 -- 31 October 1783 ) was a British peer and politician .
Ivaz Mehmed Pasha ( died 1743 ) , also known as Hacı Ivaz Mehmed Pasha or Hacı Ivazzade Mehmed Pasha , was an 18th - century Ottoman grand vizier and provincial governor .
Conchobar mac Taidg Mór ( died 882 ) was a King of Connacht from the Uí Briúin branch of the Connachta .
Humphrey Senhouse ( 1731 - -1814 ) was a British Tory politician from a Cumberland family .
Clara Anna Korn ( born 1866 , d. 1941 ) was an American pianist , composer and music writer .
Irving Charles Velson ( June 3 , 1913 - 1976 ) was an American who had a long career in the Communist Party of the United States ( CPUSA ) secret apparatus and who allegedly worked for Soviet Military Intelligence ( GRU ) .
Sir Robert Bolles , 2nd Baronet ( 1619 - 3 August 1663 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1661 to 1663 .
Claude François Devosge ( 1697 - 5 December 1777 ) was a French sculptor and architect .
Chriselliam ( 2 February 2011 -- 7 February 2014 ) was an Irish - bred British - trained Thoroughbred racehorse .
George Spencer - Churchill , 5th Duke of Marlborough FSA ( 6 March 1766 -- 5 March 1840 ) , styled Marquess of Blandford until 1817 , was a British peer and collector of antiquities and books .
Stefan Ślopek was born on December 1 , 1914 in Skawa near Kraków and died in Wrocław on 22 August 1995 and is buried in the Grabiszyński Cemetery in Wrocław .
Rebecca Travers ( née Booth ; 1609 -- 15 June 1688 ) was a prominent London Quaker in the earliest development period of that religious movement .
Jean de Courbes ( 1592 -- 1641 ) , or Juan de Courbes , was a French engraver who was active in Spain .
Jane Anne Russell ( 1911 - -1967 ) was an endocrinologist .
Adam Thoroughgood ( 1604 - -1640 ) was a colonist and community leader in the Virginia Colony who helped settle the area of South Hampton Roads known in contemporary times as the independent city of Virginia Beach , Virginia .
Désiré Koranyi ( 28 January 1914 -- 9 January 1981 ) , aka Dezsõ Korányi or Dezsõ Kronenberger , was a Hungarian - French football player .
Andrew Ingraham ( New Bedford , MA , USA , 19 December 1841 - - Cambridge , MA , USA , 6 August 1905 ) was Headmaster of Swain School before 1903 .
Samuel Beal ( 27 November 1825 , Davenport -- 20 August 1889 , Greens Norton ) was an Oriental scholar , and the first Englishman to translate direct from the Chinese the early records of Buddhism , thus throwing light upon Indian history .
George William Torrance ( 25 July 1835 -- 20 August 1907 ) was an Irish composer , mainly of church music , who was resident in Australia for many years .
Sarah Bassett or more commonly Sally Bassett ( died 21 June 1730 ) was a mulatto slave in the British colony Bermuda in the North Atlantic .
Xu Jiyu ( Chinese : 徐繼畬 ; pinyin : Xú Jìyú ; 1795 - -1873 ) , native of Wutai County in Shanxi , high - ranking Chinese official and geographer during the late Qing dynasty .
Pietro Ferrero ( 2 September 1898 -- 2 March 1949 ) was the founder of Ferrero SpA , an Italian confectionery and chocolatier company .
Martin Sherwood ( 10 January 1942 -- 10 May 2011 ) was a British science fiction author , organic chemist and an editor of Chemistry & Industry .
Alessandro Bichi ( 1596 - 25 May 1657 ) was an Italian Catholic Cardinal and papal nuncio to France .
Niccolò Franchini ( 1704 - 1783 ) was an Italian painter , active in Siena , depicting mainly religious canvases in a late - Baroque style .
Giordano d'Anglano ( or Giordano d'Agliano ) , sometimes Jordan Lancia or Lanzia ( died 1267 ) was an Italo - Swabian count and soldier , who served as marshal to Manfred of Sicily and acted as his commander in the wars of the Guelphs and Ghibellines in Tuscany .
Dr Hugh Ernest Butler FRSE MRIA FRAS ( 1916 - 1978 ) was a Welsh - born astronomer .
Hans Järta ( originally Hans Hierta ) ( 11 February 1774 -- 6 April 1847 ) was a Swedish administrator and revolutionary .
John Burnyeat ( also spelled Burneyeat ) ( ca . 1631 in Crabtreebeck , Loweswater , Cumberland -- 1690 in Ireland ) was a British Quaker .
Henry Vincent ( 10 May 1813 -- 29 December 1878 ) was active in the formation of early Working Men 's Associations in Britain , a popular Chartist leader , brilliant and gifted public orator , prospective but ultimately unsuccessful Victorian member of parliament , and later an anti - slavery campaigner .
Eusebius of Emesa ( also Eusebius Emesenus ; Edessa , ca . 300 -- ca . 360 ) was a learned ecclesiastic of the Greek church , and a pupil of Eusebius of Caesarea .
Francis Gage ( 1621 - -1682 ) was an English Roman Catholic priest , who became President of the English College , Douai .
Franz Skarbina ( 24 February 1849 - 18 May 1910 ) was a German impressionist painter , draftsman , etcher and illustrator .
Harry Warburton ( April 10 , 1921 -- May 2005 ) is a Swiss bobsledder who competed in the mid-1950s .
John Bede Dalley ( 5 October 1876 -- 6 September 1935 ) was an Australian journalist and novelist , editor of Melbourne Punch .
Sir William Norris , 1st Baronet ( c. 1658 -- 10 October 1702 ) was an English politician and ambassador to Aurangzeb .
Sudhamoy Pramanick ( September 1884 -- October 1974 ) ( Bengali : সুধাময় প্রামাণিক ) was a Bengali advocate from Shantipur .
Robert Fayrfax ( 23 April 1464 -- 24 October 1521 ) was an English Renaissance composer , considered the most prominent and influential of the reigns of Kings Henry VII and Henry VIII of England .
Erminio Sipari ( 1 ° December 1879 -- 28 January 1968 ) was an Italian politician and naturalist , author of studies on the preservation of nature and founder of Parco Nazionale d'Abruzzo , which he chaired from 1922 to 1933 .
Gerhard Friedrich Müller ( Russian : Фёдор Ива́нович Ми́ллер , Fyodor Ivanovich Miller , 29 October 1705 -- 22 October 1783 ) was a historian and pioneer ethnologist .
Beardsley Ruml ( 5 November 1894 -- 19 April 1960 ) was an American statistician , economist , philanthropist , planner , businessman and man of affairs in the 1920s , 1930s and 1940s .
Fujiwara no Yoshikane ( 藤原 義懐 ) ( 957 - -1021 ) was a Japanese Heian era courtier .
Maud Pember Reeves ( 24 December 1865 -- 13 September 1953 ) ( born Magdalene Stuart Robison ) was a feminist , writer and member of the Fabian Society .
Harry Mundy ( 1915 - 1988 ) was a British car engine designer and motoring magazine editor .
Janelle Patton was a 29-year - old Sydney woman who was murdered on Norfolk Island on 31 March 2002 .
Matthew Gregson ( 1749 - -1824 ) , was an English antiquary .
Daniel Sedgwick ( 1814 - -1879 ) was an English hymnologist and bookseller .
Jean Fleury ( or Florin ) ( died 1527 ) was a 16th - century French naval officer and privateer .
Giulio Cesare Brancaccio ( 1515 - -1586 ) was a courtier , cavalier , actor , writer , and singer in a number of northern Italian courts throughout the sixteenth century , most notably the court at Ferrara .
Sir Harry Lewis ( 24 January 1984 -- 14 April 2009 ) was an American - bred Thoroughbred racehorse and sire best known for his win in the 1987 Irish Derby .

Wentworth FitzGerald , 17th Earl of Kildare PC ( I ) ( 1634 -- 5 March 1664 ) , styled Lord Offaly until 1660 , was an Irish politician who sat in the House of Commons of England in 1660 and from 1661 sat in the Irish House of Lords .
Rebecca Brewton Motte ( 1737 - -1815 ) was a plantation owner in South Carolina , patriot in the American Revolution , namesake of Fort Motte and mother - in - law of Major - General Thomas Pinckney .
James Halliday McDunnough ( 10 May 1877 , Toronto - 23 February , 1962 , Halifax , Nova Scotia ) was a Canadian entomologist best known for his work with North American Lepidoptera , but who also made important contributions about North American Ephemeroptera .
Shashidhar Mishra ( 1975 - -2010 ) was an Indian Right to Information Act ( RTI ) activist who was shot dead by unknown assailants near his house in Phulwaria Village , located near the Begusarai town of Bihar , on the night on 14 February 2010 .
Obadiah Shuttleworth ( died 1734 ) , English composer , violinist and organist , was the son of Thomas Shuttleworth of Spitalfields in London .
Norman Barron ( 15 May 1899 -- 25 September 1987 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Sturt in the South Australian National Football League ( SANFL ) .
Neta Harpaz ( Hebrew : נטע הרפז‎ , born Neta Goldberg in 1893 , died 11 October 1970 ) was a Zionist activist and Israeli politician .
Pierre Sadek ( died 24 April 2013 ) was a Lebanese caricaturist , considered a pioneer of political cartooning and a great defender of freedom of expression .
Liu Zhan ( 劉瞻 ) ( died September 29 , 874 ) , courtesy name Jizhi ( 幾之 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reigns of Emperor Yizong and ( briefly ) Emperor Yizong 's son Emperor Xizong .
Thomas Corser ( 1793 - -1876 ) was a British literary scholar and Church of England clergyman .
Cecilia Braslavsky ( 5 January 1952 -- 1 June 2005 ) was an Argentine educator , pedagogue , and author .
Arnold Frans Rubens or Rubbens ( 1687 - -1719 ) was a Flemish Baroque painter specialized in cabinet pictures of landscapes and battle scenes .
Afif Abdul Wahab ( 1915 - -2003 ) was a Lebanese doctor , general surgeon and urologist , businessman and philanthropist , born and raised in El Mina .

William Worfton ( c.1366 - 1408 ) , of Broad Hinton , Wiltshire , was an English politician .
Jean François Pons ( 1688 - -1752 ) was a French Jesuit who pioneered the study of Sanskrit in the West .

Colonel Maunsel White ( c. 1783 -- December 17 , 1863 ) was an Episcopalian Irish - American politician , merchant , and entrepreneur .

Anders Trulsson Bruland ( 1770 - -1818 ) was a Norwegian civil servant and politician .
Prince Feodor Ostrogski ( 1360 - -1446 ) was a powerful magnate in Volhynia of Rurikid stock , son of Daniil Ostrogski .

Bashir al - Azma , ( 1910 -- 1992 ) ( Arabic : بشير العظَمة‎ ) , was a Syrian doctor and politician .

James Thomas Milton Anderson ( 23 July 1878 , Fairbank , Ontario -- 29 December 1946 ) was Saskatchewan 's fifth Premier and the first Conservative to hold the office .
Essie Garrett ( 1947- 1 April 2014 ) was an American ultramarathon runner and instructor at Emily Griffith Opportunity School in Denver , Colorado .
Josiah Parker ( 11 May 1751 -- 11 March 1810 ) was an American politician who was a member of the United States House of Representatives from Virginia in the First through Sixth United States Congresses .

James Grubb was a delegate to the convention that wrote the first constitution for the U.S. state of Ohio in 1802 .

George Kennedy Young , CB , MBE , M.A. ( 1911 , Dumfriesshire -- 1990 , London ) was a deputy director of MI6 , and later involved in British conservative politics .
Sir Thomas Hanbury ( 21 June 1832 -- 9 March 1907 ) was an English businessman , gardener and philanthropist .
Juho Kinnunen ( 14 January 1865 , Rääkkylä - 9 September 1934 ) was a Finnish Lutheran clergyman and politician .
Murong Yao ( Chinese : 慕容瑤 ; died 386 ) was an emperor of the Xianbei state Western Yan .
Leroy Lansing Janes ( 1838 - -1909 ) was an American educator , hired by Kumamoto Domain in early Meiji period Japan .

Stephen Payne Adye ( ca . 1740 -- 1794 ) was an English brevet - major of the Royal Artillery .
Der Nister ( Yiddish : דער נסתּר ֹor דער ניסטער‎ , `` the hidden one '' ; 1 November 1884 -- 4 June 1950 the Soviet Gulag ) was the pseudonym of Pinchus Kahanovich ( פּנחס קאַהאַנאָוויטש ) , a Yiddish author , philosopher , translator , and critic .
Lee Moorhouse ( 1850 - -1926 ) of Pendleton , Oregon , United States , was a photographer and an Indian agent for the Umatilla Indian Reservation .

Brian Abel - Smith ( 6 November 1926 -- 4 April 1996 ) was a British economist and expert adviser and one of the most influential figures of the twentieth century in shaping health and social welfare .
Arthur O'Bryan ( 20 May 1923 -- 9 December 1990 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) during the 1940s .
Arnold von Siemens ( 13 November 1853 -- 29 April 1918 ) was a German telecommunications industrialist of the Siemens family , one of the successors on his family 's company Siemens .

James Joseph Lawlor ( 10 May 1933 -- 5 April 2012 ) , also known as Jimmy Lawlor or Jim Lawlor , was an Irish former professional footballer who played in both Ireland and England as a centre half .

Miloš Mikeln ( 23 May 1930 -- 2 April 2014 ) was a Slovene writer , playwright , theatre director and journalist .
Spiros Argiris ( Greek Σπύρος Αργύρης ) , born in Athens 24 August 1948 and died in Nice 19 May 1996 at the age of 48 of lung cancer,(1 ) was an orchestral and operatic conductor .

Tellef Dahll , born 10 April 1852 in Kragerø , died 17 June 1893 in Morgedal , was a Norwegian mineralogist and geologist .
Tom Ölander ( 17 August 1945 - 26 August 2002 ) was one of the main actors to kick - start an active fannish culture in Finland .
Thomas Blake Glover ( 6 June 1838 -- 16 December 1911 ) was a Scottish merchant in Bakumatsu and Meiji period Japan .
Periyapillai ( Tamil : பெரியபிள்ளை ) ( died 1582 ) was of one of the Aryacakravarti rulers of Jaffna kingdom who followed in the chaotic period after the death of Cankili I(1519 - -1561 ) .
Kieth O'dor ( 5 April 1962 -- 11 September 1995 ) was a British racing driver , born in Salisbury , who competed primarily in touring cars before being killed during a race at the AVUS circuit in Berlin .
Nikolaos Miaoulis ( Greek : Νικόλαος Μιαούλης , 1818 - 1872 ) was a Greek navy personnel .
James Cecil , 4th Earl of Salisbury ( 1666 - -1694 ) , until 1683 known by the courtesy title of Viscount Cranborne , was an English peer .
Alice of Hainault , Countess Marshal ( died 26 October 1317 ) , was the daughter of John de Avenes , Count of Hainault , and Philippine , daughter of the Count of Luxembourg .
Will Dockery ( 1865 - -1936 ) built from scratch the Dockery Plantation , the famous home of such original Delta blues musicians as Charley Patton , Robert Johnson , Son House , Howlin ' Wolf , Willie Brown , Tommy Johnson , and Pops Staples .

Paddy Waters ( born 31 January 1922 in Dublin ; died 2 March 2004 ) was an Irish soccer player during the 1940s and 1950s .
Giulio Marchetti ( 9 June 1911 - 1 December 1993 ) was an Italian stage , film and television actor and presenter .
Some Muge ( 1959 - -1997 ) was a Kenyan long - distance runner .
Theoklitos Setakis ( gr . Θεόκλητος Σετάκης ; 7 December 1930 -- 13 April 2014 ) was a Greek Orthodox bishop .
Charles le Moyne de Longueuil et de Châteauguay ( August 2 , 1626 -- February 1685 ) , as many people of his time , had a variety of occupations .
Henry Temple , 1st Viscount Palmerston ( c.1673 -- 10 June 1757 ) was an Irish nobleman and British politician , the eldest son of Sir John Temple , Speaker of the Irish House of Commons , and Jane Yarner .
Ivan Hlevnjak ( 28 April 1944 -- 28 November 2015 ) was a Croatian midfielder who played for Yugoslavia .

Sadiq Batcha ( c. 1963 -- 16 March 2011 ) was the Managing Director of real estate company Green House Promoters Private Limited .
Émile Vacher ( 1883 - 1969 ) was a French accordionist associated with , and often deemed the creator of , the bal - musette genre .
E.V. Durling ( 1893 - -1957 ) was one of the first journalists to cover the Hollywood motion picture industry and later became a nationally syndicated newspaper columnist in the United States , with his column `` On the Side . ''
Walter Coffin ( 1784 -- 15 February 1867 ) was a Welsh coalowner and Member of Parliament .

Paul Einzig ( 1897 - -1973 ) was an economic and political writer and journalist .

Karl Friedrich Emil zu Dohna - Schlobitten ( 4 March 1784 -- 21 February 1859 ) was a Prussian fieldmarshal .

Sir Edward Shepherd Creasy ( 12 September 1812 -- 17 January 1878 ) was an English historian and jurist .

Thomas Fell ( 1598 - -1658 ) , was a lawyer , member of parliament and vice - chancellor of the duchy of Lancaster .
Hugo Herrestrup ( 29 January 1933 -- 22 September 2009 ) was a Danish film actor .
Gaspard Bureau ( died 1469 ) was a French ballistics expert and inventor , as well as lord of Montfermeil , Nogent - sur - Marne , Villemomble and other places .
Levy Barent Cohen ( 1740s -- 1808 ) was an English financier and communal worker .
Blessed John Cornelius ( 1557 -- 4 July 1594 ) ( called also Mohun ) was an English Catholic priest and Jesuit .
Seamus Rafter ( 24 January 1873 -- 12 September 1918 ) was an Irishman who launched the Gaelic League in Enniscorthy , Wexford .
Adam Bothwell , Lord of Session ( c.1527 , Edinburgh -- 1593 , Edinburgh ) , was Scottish clergyman , judge and politician .
Arthur Pond ( 1705?--1758 London ) was an English painter and engraver .
Stephen Samuel Gordon ( 17 June 1970 -- 2 October 2014 ) , known as The Spaceape , was a British poet and MC .
Ralph Neville , 4th Earl of Westmorland KG , ( 21 February 1498 -- 24 April 1549 ) was an English peer and soldier .
Irshad Ahmed Haqqani ( 6 September 1928 -- 24 January 2010 ) was a senior editor , veteran journalist and reputed column writer for the Jang Group of Newspapers .
Mostafa Ahmadi - Roshan ( Persian : مصطفی احمدی روشن‎‎ , c. 1980 -- 11 January 2012 ) was an Iranian nuclear scientist and university professor and had several ISI ( Institute for Scientific Information ) articles .
George Napoleon Epps ( 1815 - -1874 ) was an English homœopathic practitioner and author .
Sir John Spilman ( also spelt Spielman ) ( died 1626 ) was a Lindau , German - born entrepreneur who founded the first commercially successful paper - mill in England , establishing a factory on the River Darenth in Dartford , Kent in 1588 .
Marie Maugeret ( 1844 - 1928 ) was a French novelist and conservative Catholic who became a feminist and was active in promoting Christian feminism as an antidote to socialism .
Alan A'Court ( 30 September 1934 -- 14 December 2009 ) was an English footballer who mostly played for Liverpool .
Colonel Sir Richard Ingoldsby ( 10 August 1617 -- 9 September 1685 ) was an English officer in the New Model Army during the English Civil War and a politician who sat in the House of Commons variously between 1647 and 1685 .
Reinier Nooms ( c. 1623 -- 1664 ) , also known as Zeeman ( Dutch for `` sailor '' ) , was a maritime painter known for his highly detailed paintings and etchings of ships .
D. António de Araújo e Azevedo , 1st Count of Barca ( 14 May 1754 -- 21 July 1817 ) was a Portuguese statesman , author and amateur botanist .
François Joseph Drouot de Lamarche ( 14 July 1733 -- 18 May 1814 ) briefly commanded a French army during the French Revolutionary Wars .
John of Ford ( c. 1140 -- 21 April 1214 ) was the prior of the Cistercian monastery of Forde , then from 1186 abbot of its daughter house of Bindon , and between 1191 and 1214 the abbot of Forde .
Porcius Festus was procurator of Judea from about AD 59 to 62 , succeeding Antonius Felix .
Aristotelis Kourtidis ( Greek : Αριστοτέλης Κουρτίδης , Myriofyto , 1858 -- Piraeus , 1928 ) was a distinguished Greek educator and writer .
John Thomas Lupton ( 1862 - -1933 ) was an American lawyer , industrialist and philanthropist who along with Benjamin Thomas and Joseph Whitehead , obtained exclusive rights from Asa Candler to bottle and sell Coca - Cola .
Philemon Bacon ( died 1 June 1666 ) , was a captain in the Royal Navy , was made a lieutenant in 1661 , and in 1664 was advanced to be captain of the Nonsuch .
Patritius Sporer ( died 29 May 1683 ) was a German Franciscan moral theologian .
Lars Vegard ( 3 February 1880 -- 21 December 1963 ) was a Norwegian physicist , especially known as an aurora borealis researcher .
Diego Polo the Younger ( 1620 - -1655 ) was a Spanish painter of the Baroque period .
Will Gould ( 1911 - -1984 ) was an American cartoonist best known for his comic strip Red Barry .
Albert Arlen AM ( 10 January 1905 -- 24 March 1993 ) was a Turkish Australian pianist , composer , actor and playwright .
Ram Bhankal ( Native Name : Ramdas Mahadev Bhankal ) ( Marathi - राम भंकाळ ) alias Ram Bhau ( 16 October 1946 - 17 April 2013 ) was an Indian politician and Social Worker of the party Shiv Sena , a right - wing Marathi ethnocentric party active mainly in the Western Indian state of Maharashtra .
Willy Haugli ( 2 August 1927 -- 12 February 2009 ) was a Norwegian jurist , university director and police chief .
Maude Cary ( 1878 - -1967 ) was a Christian American missionary to North Africa , specifically Morocco .
Francis Coates Jones ( 1857 - -1932 ) was an American painter from a wealthy Baltimore family who studied in Europe under painters such as Bouguereau .
Cornelis Willem Opzoomer ( 20 September 1821 , Rotterdam -- 23 August 1892 , Oosterbeek ) was a Dutch jurist , positivist philosopher and theologian .
František Wende ( June 3 , 1904 -- 1968 ) was a Czechoslovakian ski jumper and nordic combined skier who has competed in the 1920s .
Fr Zygmunt Gorazdowski died in Lviv on 1 January 1920 .
Christian V , Count of Oldenburg ( sometimes called Christian VI ; c. 1342 -- after 6 April 1399 ) was the ruling count of Oldenburg from 1368 until 1398 .
Gyula Szentessy ( b. Oradea , 18 December 1870 - d. Budapest , 30 October 1905 ) was a Hungarian poet .
John Rooke Corbett ( 27 September 1876 -- 13 August 1949 ) , better known as J. Rooke Corbett was one of the founder - members of The Rucksack Club and their Convener of Rambles .
Friedrich von Arnauld de la Perière ( 17 June 1888 in Breslau - 12 October 1969 in Friedrichshafen ) was a German aviator and Generalleutnant of the Luftwaffe .
Laurence Clarkson ( 1615 - -1667 ) , sometimes called Claxton , born in Preston , Lancashire was an English theologian and accused heretic .
Gajah Mada ( c. 1290 -- c. 1364 ) was , according to Javanese old manuscripts , poems and mythology , a powerful military leader and mahapatih or prime minister of the Majapahit Empire , credited with bringing the empire to its peak of glory .
Muhamed Mehmedbašić ( 1886 -- 29 May 1943 ) was a Bosnian revolutionary and conspirator in the assassination of Archduke Franz Ferdinand of Austria .
Fr . Franciszek Chalupka ( 1856 - -1909 ) - founder of the first Polish - American parishes in New England .
Denver Lindley ( 1904 - 1982 ) was an American translator noted for his translations of works by Thomas Mann , Hermann Hesse , Ernst Schnabel , André Maurois , and others .
Georgette Meunier ( October 7 , 1859 -- 1951 ) was a Belgian still life painter .
Samuel N. Mitchell ( 1846 - 1905 ) was an American song lyricist and newspaperman who wrote lyrics for a number of popular songs in the 1870s .
Nominoe or Nomenoe ( French : Nominoë ; Breton : Nevenoe ; d. 7 March 851 ) was the first Duke of Brittany from 846 to his death .
Rear Admiral Alec Julian Tyndale - Biscoe OBE ( 10 August 1906 -- 26 April 1997 ) was a distinguished naval engineer and a senior officer in the British Royal Navy .
Lazar Dobricz ( 1881 - -1970 ) was a Bulgarian circus artist , one of the first and most prominent circus performers of Bulgaria .
Jeremiah Colman ( 1777 - -1851 ) was an English miller who founded Colman 's Mustard , a business which merged into the conglomerate Reckitt & Colman , now represented by Reckitt Benckiser .
Shakespeare Hirst ( 26 February 1841 -- 20 May 1907 ) was an English actor , author , art collector and expert on the life and works of William Shakespeare .
Ira Hatch ( 5 August 1835 -- 30 September 1909 ) was a prominent Mormon missionary .
Major - General Dejazmatch Beyene Merid , Beine Merid , ( 1897 - 24 February 1937 ) was an Ethiopian army commander , a patriot , and the son - in - law of Emperor Haile Selassie I.
Béatrice Reinach ( 1894 -- 1944 ) was a French socialite and a Holocaust victim .
Almas Ildyrym ( Azerbaijani : Almas İldırım ) , born Ildyrym Almaszadeh ( 25 March 1907 , Baku -- 14 January 1952 , Elazığ , Turkey ) , was an Azerbaijani poet .
Alec Fyfe ( 12 August 1909 -- 1 December 1973 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sir James Stirling , 1st Baronet ( 1739 - -1805 ) was a Scottish banker and Lord Provost of Edinburgh .
Owen McGlynn ( 1878 - -1918 ) was an architect who practiced in Wilkes - Barre , Pennsylvania , at the end of the nineteenth century , and at the beginning of the twentieth .
Toni von Langsdorff ( 30 September 1884 -- 24 March 1976 ) was a German obstetrician / gynecologist known for her work as an early woman doctor and for her role as a pioneer member of the Medical Women 's International Association .
Jules - Robert de Cotte ( 1683 - -1767 ) was a renowned French architect , the son of one of the most highly regarded architect - administrators of his era , Robert de Cotte .
Keichi Kimura ( 1914 - -1988 ) was a painter and illustrator who was born in Waiʻanae , Hawaiʻi in 1914 .
Monsignor James MacCaffrey STL , PhD ( 1875 - 1935 ) was an Irish priest , theologian and historian ,
Philippe Étancelin ( 28 December 1896 -- 13 October 1981 ) was a French Grand Prix motor racing driver who joined the new Formula One circuit at its inception .
Anne Kirkbride ( 21 June 1954 -- 19 January 2015 ) was an English actress , known for her long - running role as Deirdre Barlow in the ITV soap Coronation Street , which she played for 42 years from 1972 to 2014 .
Johannes Ringk , or Ringck ( 26 June 1717 -- 24 August 1778 ) , was a German composer and organist .
Saint Thecla of Kitzingen ( Tecla of England , Heilga ) ( died ca . 790 AD ) was a Benedictine nun and abbess .
James Neil Hollingworth ( 1933 - -1996 ) was a beatnik , hippie , writer , and former manager of the psychedelic folk rock bands Quicksilver Messenger Service and Ace of Cups .
James Lumsden ( 1598 - -1660 ) was a Scottish soldier who served in the Swedish army of Gustavus Adolphus during the Thirty Years ' War , and subsequently commanded Scottish Covenanter armies .
Fei Mu ( 1906 - -1951 ) was a major Chinese film director of the pre - Communist era .
Hernando Arias de Saavedra ( September 10 , 1561 -- 1634 ) , commonly known as Hernandarias , was a soldier and politician of criollo ancestry .
Hendrick Danckerts ( c.1625 - 1680 ) was a Dutch Golden Age landscape painter and engraver .
Alexander McArthur ( 10 March 1814 -- 1 August 1909 ) was an Irish - born Australian and British businessman .
Heinz Weifenbach ( 11 July 1939 - -21 February 2015 ) was a German ice hockey executive best known for the 1987 advertising contract he negotiated in which his club , the ECD Iserlohn , advertised Muammar Gaddafi 's Green Book ( German : Das Grüne Buch ) on its shirts .
Anna Branzell , also Anna Lous - Mohr Branzell , ( née Mohr , 30 March 1895 -- 19 July 1983 ) was a Norwegian - born Swedish architect .
Carlos Gandolfo ( March 27 , 1931 -- January 12 , 2005 ) was an Argentine stage actor and director .
Vincenzo Marinelli ( June 5 , 1820 -- 18 January 1892 ) was an Italian painter , known best for his Orientalist canvases based on his travels in Greece , Crete , Egypt , and Sudan .
Alexander Scott Withers ( 12 October 1792 , near Warrenton , Virginia -- 23 January 1865 , near Parkersburg , West Virginia ) was the author of Chronicles of Border Warfare ( 1831 ) , a history of ( and important primary source on ) the early white settlement of western Virginia and consequent conflicts with American Indians .
Pauli Pitkänen ( 4 November 1911 -- 28 September 1941 ) was a Finnish cross - country skier who competed in the 1930s .
Mary Ann Oatman ( 1844 - -1851 ) was the sister of Olive Oatman , and a survivor of abuse by the Yavapai people ( though many historians argue that it is impossible to know whether or not these were Yavapai , or some other tribe ) .
Giovanni Battista Agnello ( fl . 1560 - -1577 ) was a Venetian alchemist working in London in the 1560s and 1570s .
John Anthon ( born in Detroit , 14 May 1784 ; died in New York City , 5 March 1863 ) was a United States jurist .
Thomas Bowrey ( d. 1713 ) was a British merchant sailor .
Claus Winter Hjelm , also known as Winter - Hjelm ( 21 May 1797 -- 22 October 1871 ) was a Norwegian legal scholar and judge .
Saint Philip of Gortyna ( died 180 ) was Bishop of Gortyna on Crete .
George Anne Bellamy ( née O'Hara ; 23 April 1727 -- 16 February 1788 ) was an Irish actress .
Sir George Baker , 1st Baronet , MD , FRS , FSA ( 1 January 1722 -- 15 June 1809 ) was an English physician .
Maria Thins ( ca.1593 -- 27 December 1680 ) was the mother - in - law of Johannes Vermeer and a member of the Gouda Thins family .
Mabel Fairbanks ( November 14 , 1915 -- September 29 , 2001 ) was an American figure skater and coach .
Lady Ruth Gollancz ( née Lowy ; 1892 - -1973 ) was a British artist and wife of Sir Victor Gollancz .
Dick Bayliss was manager of Coventry City F.C. between June 1945 and his death in April 1947 .
Valve Pormeister née Ulm ( 13 April 1922 -- 27 October 2002 ) was an Estonian architect .
Micheál O'Brien ( June 1923 - 14 May 2015 ) was an Irish Gaelic footballer and hurler who played for the Meath senior team .
Joseph Oxley ( ca 1779 -- March 18 , 1868 ) was a farmer and political figure in Nova Scotia .
Arsenije III Čarnojević ( Serbian Cyrillic : Арсеније III Чарнојевић , 1633 -- 27 October 1706 ) was the Archbishop of Peć and Patriarch of Serbs from 1674 to 1691 and Metropolitan of Sentandreja from 1691 to his death in 1706 .
Alfons Goldschmidt 28 November 1879 - 20 or 21 January 1940 ) was a German Journalist , economist and university lecturer .
Kivas Tully ( 1820 - -24 April 1905 ) was an Irish - Canadian architect .
Kaarlo Mäkinen ( 14 May 1892 -- 11 May 1980 ) was a Finnish wrestler who competed at the 1920 , 1924 and 1928 Olympics in freestyle wrestling .
Archbishop Francisco Ramón Herboso y Figueroa ( c. 1720 - -1782 ) was born in Lima .
Hans van Abeelen ( 20 November 1936 -- 21 August 1998 ) was the first Dutch behaviour geneticist .
William Longespée , 3rd Earl of Salisbury ( c. 1176 -- 7 March 1226 ) ( `` Long Sword '' , Latinised to de Longa Spatha ) was an English noble , primarily remembered for his command of the English forces at the Battle of Damme and for remaining loyal to his half - brother , King John .
Kris Ottman Neville ( 9 May 1925 -- 23 December 1980 ) was an American science fiction writer from California .
Charles Gilbert Heathcote ( 2 March 1841 -- 15 November 1915 ) was an English barrister and tennis player .
Robert Ayres Barnet or R. A. Barnet ( 1853 - 1933 ) was an American musical theatre lyricist in New York City and Boston , Massachusetts , in the late 19th and early 20th centuries .
Anna Russell , née Anna Claudia Russell - Brown ( 27 December 1911 -- 18 October 2006 ) was an English--
Nasr I ( died August 892 ) was amir of the Samanids ( 864/865 - -892 ) .
Sir Godfrey Baring , 1st Baronet DL , JP ( 18 April 1871 -- 24 November 1957 ) was a Liberal Member of Parliament for the Isle of Wight and later Barnstaple .
Geoffrey Lancashire ( 12 March 1933 -- 3 October 2004 ) was a British television scriptwriter .
Jacques de Champlain ( 13 March 1938 - 15 July 2009 ) was a scientist , doctor and professor from the Province of Quebec .
Dr. Mark Keppel served as County Superintendent of Schools of Los Angeles County from 1902 to 1928 .
Henry Chesewell ( died 1433 ) , of Totnes , Devon , was an English politician .
Theodosius of Sinai ( Bulgarian : Теодосий Синаитски , Teodosiy Sinaitski ; ? -- March 1843 ) was a Bulgarian priest , writer and printer .
James Spottiswood ( 1567 - -1645 ) was a Scottish courtier and Protestant bishop of Clogher .
Sorcha Boru was the assumed or studio name of Claire Everett ( née Jones ) Stewart ( 13 April 1900 -- 30 January 2006 ) , a potter and ceramic sculptor .
William Sandford ( 26 September 1841 -- 29 May 1932 ) was an English - Australian ironmaster .
Johannes Wolfgang Willy Friedlieb Heuer ( 1910 -- 14 September 1993 ) was born in Kiel and started his working life in Hamburg , Germany .
Philip Charles Hardwick ( London 1822 - -1892 ) was an English architect .
Sir William Oliphant , Lord Newton ( 1551 - -1628 ) was a Scottish judge .
Francis Armstrong ( 1813 -- 1897 ) was a Scottish Methodist pioneer and missionary to aborigines in Western Australia .
Albert II of Brunswick - Wolfenbüttel ( died 14 April 1395 ) was Prince - Archbishop of Bremen in the years 1361 - -1395 .
William King - Noel , 1st Earl of Lovelace FRS ( 21 February 1805 -- 29 December 1893 ) , known as the Hon . William King until 1833 and as the Lord King from 1833 to 1838 , was an English nobleman and scientist .
William Dade ( c.1740 - -1790 ) was an English cleric and antiquary .
Russel Crouse ( 20 February 1893 -- 3 April 1966 ) was an American playwright and librettist , best known for his work in the Broadway writing partnership of Lindsay and Crouse .
Edmund Law Lushington ( 10 January 1811 -- 13 July 1893 ) was a classical scholar , a Professor of Greek , and Rector of the University of Glasgow .
Julius Sagalowsky ( born May 13 , 1905 in Indianapolis , Indiana ; died October 1977 ) was an American amateur tennis player in the 1920s .
Giovanni Stefano Menochio ( 1575 -- 4 February 1655 ) was an Italian Jesuit biblical scholar .
Joanna Southcott ( or Southcote ) ( April 1750 -- 27 December 1814 ) , was a self - described religious prophetess .
Fernando de Buen y Lozano ( 1895 - 6 May 1962 ) was a Spanish ichthyologist and oceanographer .
Thomas Fermor - Hesketh , 1st Baron Hesketh ( 17 November 1881 -- 20 July 1944 ) , known as Sir Thomas Fermor - Hesketh , Bt , from 1924 to 1935 , was a British peer , soldier and Conservative Member of Parliament .
José Milton Benedito , also known as Miltão ( 1 July 1950 -- 22 December 2003 ) was a Brazilian professional football player .
Mounir Fourar ( born in Batna , Algeria , the November 28 , 1972 -- 3 January 2012 ) was one of the tallest men in the world .
Franz Xaver Gebel ( 1787 -- 3 May 1843 ) was a German composer , music teacher , and conductor .
On 27 November 2000 , Viji committed suicide in her home in Chennai .
Charles Farley ( 1771 - -1859 ) was an English actor and dramatist .
Sasbout Vosmeer ( Delft , 13 March 1548 -- Cologne , 3 May 1614 ) was the first apostolic vicar to the Dutch Mission .
Rufus Henry Underwood ( 31 December 1863 - -8 October 1945 ) , better known as Henry Underwood , was an Australian politician who represented the Western Australian Legislative Assembly seat of Pilbara from 1906 until 1924 .
George Tradescant Lay ( c. 1800 - November 6 , 1845 ) was a British naturalist , missionary and diplomat .
Dr John Kennall , LL.D. ( aka John Kenold ) ( 1511 - -1592 ) was Archdeacon of Oxford and a noted pluralist .
Franz Sacher ( 19 December 1816 -- 11 March 1907 ) was an Austrian - Jewish confectioner , best known as the inventor of the world - famous chocolate cake , the Sachertorte .
Thomas McPherson Brown ( 1906 - 1989 ) was a renowned rheumatologist who , over a medical career spanning 50 years , pioneered antibiotic treatments for rheumatoid arthritis , scleroderma , lupus and other collagen diseases .
Professor Sir Abraham Goldberg KB MD DSc FRCP FRSE ( 1923 - -2007 ) was Regius Professor of the Practice of Medicine at the University of Glasgow .
John Beeson ( 1803 - -1889 ) was an abolitionist and early Native American advocate .
Empress Dowager Bian ( 30 December 159 -- 9 July 230 ) , also known as Lady Bian , formally known as Empress Wuxuan , was an empress dowager of the state of Cao Wei during the Three Kingdoms period .
Wilhelm Eduard Schmid ( April 12 , 1893 -- June 1934 ) , better known as Willi Schmid , was a German music critic , and an accidental victim of the Night of the Long Knives in a case of mistaken identity .
Manly N. Cutter ( 1851 - 1931 ) was an architect and interior designer associated with work in New Jersey , Boston , New York City , the state of New York , and Alberta , Canada .
Le Yanzhen ( 樂彥禎 ) ( d. 888 ) , né Le Xingda ( 樂行達 ) , was a warlord late in the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , who ruled Weibo Circuit ( 魏博 , headquartered in modern Handan , Hebei ) as its military governor ( Jiedushi ) from 883 to 888 .
Christopher Andreas Holmboe ( 19 March 1796 , Vang , Oppland - 2 April 1882 ) was a Norwegian philologist .
Margery Fish died in South Petherton Hospital , Somerset , on 24 March 1969 , leaving her house and garden to a nephew , Henry Boyd - Carpenter .
James Hewitt , 4th Viscount Lifford ( 31 March 1811 - 20 November 1887 ) DL , of Meenglas , County Donegal , was Deputy Lieutenant for the County of Donegal .
Ernst Roth ( 1 June 1896 -- 17 July 1971 ) was a music publisher for Universal Edition in Vienna and Boosey & Hawkes in London , and became the company 's director in 1968 .
Eddie Melai ( 28 February 1941 -- 28 July 2004 ) was an Australian rules footballer most notable for his career with the Dandenong Football Club in the Victorian Football Association during the 1960s and 1970s .
John McKinnon Crawford DA died aged 73 on 20 March 2005 at Lossiemouth , survived by his wife Morag , and daughters Shuna , Cara ( also an artist ) and Rona .
Mauricio Borensztein ( 27 April 1927 -- 11 January 1996 ) , known by the stage name Tato Bores , was an Argentine film , theatre and television comedian , who specialized in political humor .
Bernard Picart ( 11 June 1673 -- 8 May 1733 ) , was a French engraver , son of Etienne Picart , also an engraver .
Dr. Tjipto Mangoenkoesoemo or Cipto Mangunkusumo ( 4 March 1886 in Pecangakan , Ambarawa , Semarang -- 8 March 1943 in Batavia ) was a prominent Indonesian independence leader and Sukarno 's political mentor .
Terry Scully ( 13 May 1932 -- 17 April 2001 ) was a British theatre and television actor .
Jacob Sahaya Kumar Aruni ( 4 June 1974 -- 4 November 2012 ) , popularly known as `` Chef Jacob '' , was an Indian celebrity chef born in Uthamapalayam , Tamil Nadu .
Acharya Ramamurti ( 1913 - -2010 ) was an Indian social activist , gandhian , educationist and academic .
Jakob Ebert ( 26 January 1549 -- 5 February 1614 ) was a German theologian and poet .
Aleksander Orłowski ( 9 March 1777 -- 13 March 1832 ) was a Polish painter and sketch artist , and a pioneer of lithography in the Russian Empire .
Giuseppe Bellenghi ( Bologna 1847-Florence Oct 17 , 1902 ) was a virtuoso violincellist and mandolinist , and a composer .
Cornelis de Graeff , also Cornelis de Graeff van ( Zuid-)Polsbroek ( 15 October 1599 -- 4 May 1664 ) was the most illustrious member of the De Graeff family .
John Wodehouse , 3rd Earl of Kimberley , CBE , MC ( 11 November 1883 -- 16 April 1941 ) , styled Lord Wodehouse from 1902 to 1932 , was a British peer and Liberal politician .
Anders Frandsen ( 8 December 1960 -- c. 1 January 2012 ) was a Danish musician , singer , actor and TV presenter .
Susan Francis - Wilkes , née Radford ( 14 October 1877 -- 22 April 1946 ) was an Australian midwife and women 's activist .
Carlos Antonio Carrillo ( 24 December 1783 -- 23 February 1852 ) , was Governor of Alta California from 1837 to 1838 .
Vito Fazzi ( 1851 - -1918 ) was an Italian doctor who lived in Lecce in the second half of the 19th century .
Mike Lesser ( 28 September 1943 -- 1 July 2015 ) was a mathematical philosopher and political activist .
M. Georges Valensi ( 1889 - -1980 ) was a French telecommunications engineer who , in 1938 , invented and patented a method of transmitting color images via luma and chrominance so that they could be received on both color and black & white television sets .
Bhagatji Maharaj ( Gujarati : ભગતજી મહારાજ ) ( 20 March 1829 -- 7 November 1897 ) , born as Pragji Darji , was the second spiritual successor of Swaminarayan in the BAPS Swaminarayan Sanstha , a Hindu denomination .
Walter Zapp ( Latvian : Valters Caps ; 4 September ( O.S. 22 August ) 1905 -- 17 July 2003 ) was a Baltic German inventor .
Laurence Hynes Halloran ( 29 December 1765 -- 8 March 1831 ) was a poet , unordained clergyman and felon who became a pioneer schoolteacher , journalist , and bigamist in Australia , founder of the Sydney Public Free Grammar School .
Dámaso Ruiz - Jarabo Colomer ( 20 June 1949 - 12 November 2009 ) was a Spanish jurist , judge at the Consejo General del Poder Judicial ( General Council of the Judiciary ) and the head of the Private Office of the President of the Consejo General del Poder Judicial .
Luis Molowny Arbelo ( 12 May 1925 -- 12 February 2010 ) was a Spanish football ( soccer ) striker and coach .
Reverend Samuel Rosewell ( 1679 -- 7 April 1722 ) was a Presbyterian minister born at Rotherhithe , Surrey .
Warren Tallman ( 17 November 1921 -- 1 July 1994 ) was an American - born poetry professor who influenced the Canadian Tish movement .
Jack Clayton ( 1 March 1921 -- 26 February 1995 ) was a British film director , who specialised in bringing literary works to the screen .
Wing Commander Dudley Lloyd - Evans MC , DFC * ( 1895 -- 20 March 1972 ) was a Welsh - born soldier and flying ace .
Alan Grenyer ( 1892 - 1953 ) was a footballer who played in The Football League for Everton and South Shields .
Edward Bartlett ( 1836 -- April 1908 ) was an English ornithologist and herpetologist .
Francis Bruen ( died 15 December 1867 ) was an Irish Conservative Party politician .
Kris Kirk , full name Christopher Pius Mary Kirk , ( 1950 , in Carlisle , England -- 27 April 1993 ) was a gay activist , journalist and author who became well known as a pop music journalist in the 1980s .
Cyril W. Beaumont , OBE ( 1 November 1891 -- 24 May 1976 ) was a British dance historian , critic , technical theorist , translator , bookseller , and publisher .
John O'Byrne ( 24 April 1884 -- 14 January 1954 ) was an Irish barrister , Attorney General and judge .
Surgeon Major Thomas Egerton Hale VC CB ( 24 September 1832 -- 25 December 1909 ) was an English recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Barry McSweeney ( died October 2014 ) was an Irish scientist who was the first Chief Science Advisor to the Government of Ireland .
The Reverend Thomas Henry Espinell Compton Espin or T. H. E. C. Espin ( 28 May 1858 -- 2 December 1934 ) was a British astronomer .
Michael Wening ( 11 July 1645 -- 18 April 1718 ) was a Bavarian engraver who is known for his many depictions of important places in the Bavaria of his day , including cityscapes and views of stately homes , castles and monasteries .
Thomas Chitty ( 1802 -- 13 February 1878 ) was an English lawyer and legal writer who was pupil master to a generation of eminent lawyers and played a significant role in documenting the legal reforms of the 19th century .
Zhao Yong ( simplified Chinese : 赵雍 ; traditional Chinese : 趙雍 ; pinyin : Zhào Yōng ; Wade -- Giles : Chao Yung ; style name Zhongmu ( 仲穆 ) ; 1289 -- c. 1360 ) , was a noted Chinese painter , calligrapher , and poet in the Yuan Dynasty .
