Hildebrand Dezső Várkonyi ( born 3 August 1888 -- 20 May 1971 ) was a monk and a teacher of Bencés order .
Domenico Grimani ( 19 February 1461 -- 27 August 1523 ) was an Italian nobleman , theologian and cardinal .
Arthur Calder - Marshall ( 19 August 1908 -- 17 April 1992 ) was an English novelist , essayist , critic , memoirist and biographer .
Håkan Malmrot ( 29 November 1900 -- 10 January 1987 ) was a Swedish breaststroke swimmer .
Alfred T. Palmer ( 1906 - -1993 ) was a photographer who is best known for his photographs depicting Americana during World War II , as he became an Office of War Information photographer from 1942 until 1943 .
Leonard Roth ( 29 August 1904 Edmonton , London , England -- 28 November 1968 Pittsburgh , Pennsylvania ) was a mathematician working in the Italian school of algebraic geometry .
Other Windsor , 2nd Earl of Plymouth ( 27 August 1679 -- 26 December 1727 ) was a British peer , styled Lord Windsor from his father';s death in 1684 to 1687 .
Shabtai Ben - Dov ( Hebrew : שבתי בן דב‎ ) ( born 1924 - 1978 ) was a member of Lehi and a philosopher .
Stylianos Mavromichalis ( Greek : Στυλιανός Μαυρομιχάλης ) ( 1902 -- 30 October 1981 ) was a Greek politician and Prime Minister .
Eddie Wainwright ( 22 June 1924 -- 2005 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football League for Everton and Rochdale .
Thomas Savin ( 1826 - 23 July 1889 ) was a British railway engineer who was the contractor who built many railways in Wales and the Welsh borders from 1857 to 1866 .
Agnes Zimmermann ( 5 July 1847 -- 14 November 1925 ) was a German concert pianist and composer who lived in England .
Adam Giede Böving ( July 31 , 1869 -- March 16 , 1957 ) was a Danish - American entomologist and zoologist .
Prince Alexander Ivanovich Bagration ( Georgian : ალექსანდრე ივანეს ძე ბაგრატიონი ) ( 1771 - 1820 ) was a Georgian royal prince ( batonishvili ) of House of Mukhrani of a collateral branch of the royal Bagrationi dynasty .
Gazi Husrev - beg ( Ottoman Turkish : غازى خسرو بیگ‎ Ghāzī Khuṣrow Beg ; Modern Turkish : Gazi Hüsrev Bey ; 1480 - -1541 ) was a Bosniak Ottoman sanjak - bey ( governor ) of the Sanjak of Bosnia in 1521 - -1525 , 1526 - -1534 , and 1536 - -1541 .
Saint Theodosia of Tyre , according to the historian of the early Christian church Eusebius , was a seventeen - year - old girl who deliberately sought to be executed as a martyr to Christianity in the city of Caesarea in 307 AD .
Niccolò Roselli ( Ferrara , active 1556 , died 1580 ) was an Italian painter of the Renaissance period .
Don Estelle ( 22 May 1933 -- 2 August 2003 ) was a British actor and singer best known as ' Lofty ' in It Ai n't Half Hot Mum .
Aziz Ullah Haidari ( 20 August 1968 in Kabul -- 19 November 2001 in Nangarhar Province ) was a Reuter 's correspondent and photo - journalist in Pakistan , killed among three foreign journalists by Taliban on 19 November 2001 .
Nick Estcourt ( 1942 -- 12 June 1978 ) , educated at Eastbourne College , was an outstanding British climber killed on K2 by an avalanche on the West Ridge route .
Emily Robin ( 1874 -- 29 October 1929 ) , also known as Lady Emily Robin or Madam Robin , was an infamous British bordello owner at the beginning of the 20th century .
Sir Watkin Williams - Wynn , 5th Baronet ( 25 October 1772 -- 6 January 1840 ) was a Welsh landowner and Tory politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1794 to 1840 .
Nicolae Costescu ( 1888 - 1963 ) was a Romanian Brigadier - General during World War II . He served as Director Higher Infantry Department in 1941 , and later that year became General Officer Commanding 18th Division .
Pál Balkay ( 1785 - -1846 ) was a Hungarian painter and teacher best known for his portrait of `` The Sister and Brother '' .
Alasdair Steele - Bodger , CBE , FRCVS ( 1 January 1924 -- 17 September 2008 ) was a British Veterinary Surgeon .
Donald James Winslow ( 1911 -- 10 July 2010 ) was a professor at Boston University in Boston , United States who specialized in the subject of biography .
Harmen Abma ( 21 November 1937 in Hilaard -- 30 November 2007 in Sneek ) was a Frisian abstract and conceptual artist and painter .
Sir Harry Fang Sin - yang , GBM , CBE , JP ( Chinese : 方心讓 , 2 August 1923 -- 24 August 2009 ) was a Hong Kong orthopaedic surgeon , legislator and campaigner who promoted rehabilitation services .
Gil Gavbara ( Persian : گیل گیلانشاه‎‎ ) , known in Arabic sources as Jil - i Jilanshah and Gavbarih , was king and founder of the Dabuyid dynasty in 642 , which he ruled until his death in 660 .
Jack Britto ( 16 August 1926 -- 16 September 2013 ) was a Pakistani Olympic field hockey player .
James Polkinghorne ( 1788 -- 15 September 1854 ) was a champion Cornish wrestler of the 19th century .
Damat Halil Pasha ( died 1629 , Istanbul ) , also known as Khalil Pasha , was an Ottoman Armenian statesman .
Egushawa ( c.1726 -- March 1796 ) , also spelled Egouch - e - ouay , Agushaway , Agashawa , Negushwa , and many other variants , was a war chief and principal political chief of the Ottawa tribe of North American Indians .
Solomon Stratton ( 1745 - 1818 ) was an American soldier and explorer born in New River , Amherst County , Virginia .
William Jethro Brown ( 29 March 1868 -- 27 May 1930 ) was an Australian jurist and professor of law .
Thomas Caius ( died in Oxford , May 1572 ) was an Oxford academic and administrator .
Henry George Raverty ( 31 May 1825 -- 20 October 1906 ) was a British Indian Army officer and linguist .
Alva Myrdal ( Swedish : ( ˌalːva ˈmyːɖɑːl ) ; née Reimer ; 31 January 1902 -- 1 February 1986 ) was a Swedish sociologist and politician .
Tarcisius Van Bavel , O.S.A. , ( 1923 - 2007 ) Roman Catholic priest and Augustinian friar , one was of the most important scholars in the thought of St. Augustine of Hippo .
John Emes ( 1762 - -1810 ) was a British engraver and water - colour painter .
Jean - Pierre Pescatore ( 11 March 1793 - 9 December 1855 ) was a Luxembourgish - French businessman , banker , art collector , and philanthropist .
William Walcher ( or just Walcher , sometimes Walchere or Walker ; died 14 May 1080 ) was the bishop of Durham from 1071 , a Lotharingian , the first non - Englishman to hold that see and an appointee of William the Conqueror following the Harrying of the North .
Zhang Jingyao , ( simplified Chinese : 张敬尧 ; traditional Chinese : 張敬堯 ; pinyin : Zhāng Jìngyáo ; Wade -- Giles : Chang1 Ch'ing4-yao2 ; IPA : ( ʈ͡ʂɑ̄ŋ t͡ɕìŋi̯ɑ́ʊ̯ ) ; 1881 - -1933 ) , was a Chinese General , the military governor of Chahar and later Hunan Province .
Hans Carl Knudtzon ( 29 January 1751 -- 16 December 1823 ) was a Norwegian merchant , ship - owner and politician .
William Graham , 2nd Earl of Montrose ( 1492 - 24 May 1571 ) was a Scottish nobleman and statesman , who successfully steered a moderate course through the treacherous waters of mid-16th century Scottish politics .
Thomas Barnard ( c. 1726/28 - -1806 ) was an Anglican clergyman who served in the Church of Ireland as Bishop of Killaloe and Kilfenora ( 1780 - -1794 ) and Bishop of Limerick , Ardfert and Aghadoe ( 1794 - -1806 ) .
John Akii - Bua ( 3 December 1949 -- 20 June 1997 ) was a Ugandan hurdler and the first Olympic champion from his country .
Jane Wheatley ( 1881 -- February 17 , 1935 ) was an actress of the American stage .
Bolesław of Kuyavia ( also known as Mieszkowic ) ( Polish : Bolesław kujawski ( Mieszkowic ) ) ( 1159 -- 13 September 1195 ) was a Duke of Kuyavia from 1186 until his death .
John Brisbane ( d. 1776 ? ) , was a Scottish physician .
Ba Win ( Burmese : ဘဝင်း , pronounced : ( ba̰ wɪ́ɴ ) ; 10 June 1901 -- 19 July 1947 ) was a Burmese politician , and Minister of Trade in the Interim Government of Burma .
Majid Kavian ( 1982 - -3 September 2011 ) ( Persian : مجید کاویان‎ ) , also known as Semko Sarholdan was the deputy commander of the militant Party of Free Life of Kurdistan ( PJAK ) until his death on 3 September 2011 , at the age of 29 .
Princess Dowager Helan ( 賀蘭太后 , personal name unknown ) ( 351 - -396 ) , formally Empress Xianming ( 獻明皇后 , literally `` the wise and understanding empress ) , was , according to official history of the Chinese / Xianbei dynasty Northern Wei , the mother of the founding emperor Emperor Daowu ( Tuoba Gui ) .
Armand Pien ( 1920 -- 2003 ) was a Belgian weatherman for 37 years .
Sir John Henry Puleston ( 2 June 1830 -- 19 October 1908 ) was a Welsh journalist and entrepreneur in the United States and later a Conservative politician who represented Devonport .
Sa'id al-'As ( Arabic : سعيد العاص‎ ) ( 1889 -- 6 October 1936 ) was a Syrian nationalist , a former officer in the Ottoman army and a high - ranking commander of rebel forces during the Great Syrian Revolt against French rule in Syria and the 1936 revolt against British rule in Palestine .
Charlton Wollaston ( 1733 - -1764 ) was an English medical doctor , physician to the Queen 's Household .
Mike Plant ( November 21 , 1950 -- 1992 ) was an American single - handed yachtsman .
Dr John Menzies Campbell FRSE FDS DDS ( 1887 -- 1974 ) was a Scottish dentist and dental historian , noted for his foundation of the Menzies Campbell Dental Museum , now known as the Menzies Campbell Collection : a collection of dental artefacts and pictures belonging to Edinburgh University and housed within Surgeon 's Hall .
Jakob Emanuel Lange ( 2 April 1864 -- 27 December 1941 ) , was a Danish mycologist who studied the systematics of gilled mushrooms .
Kaya Köstepen ( 12 December 1934 -- 29 June 2011 ) was a Turkish football player who played club football for Altay and Beşiktaş .
Sir Brian Tuke ( died 1545 ) , was the secretary of Henry VIII and Cardinal Wolsey .
Colin Strang , 2nd Baron Strang ( 12 June 1922 -- 19 December 2014 ) was a British Professor of Philosophy and hereditary peer .
Françoise Taylor ( née Wauters ) was a Belgian artist ( 1 January 1920 -- 24 January 2007 ) .
Francis Charles Nagot ( 1734 - -1816 ) was a French Roman Catholic priest , who worked for the Society of Saint - Sulpice .
Hermann Busenbaum ( or Busembaum ) ( 19 September 1600 -- 31 January 1668 ) was a Jesuit theologian .
Thomas Chase ( died 1449 ) was a 15th - century judge and cleric who was Chancellor of the University of Oxford in England and subsequently held the office of Lord Chancellor of Ireland .
Julius Paltiel ( 4 July 1924 -- 7 March 2008 ) was one of the 26 Norwegian Jews who returned from Auschwitz .
Indalencio Pascoal Froilano de Mello ( 17 May 1887 -- 9 January 1955 ) was a Goan - Portuguese microbiologist , medical scientist , professor , author and an independent MP in the Portuguese parliament .
Kim Mu - ryeok ( 518 ~ 16 October 579 ) was a Silla general under King Jinheung in the mid-6th century .
Coirpre Cromm mac Crimthainn ( died 577 ) was a King of Munster from the Eóganacht Glendamnach sept of the ruling Eoganachta dynasty .
John Darwall ( 1731 - -1789 ) was an English clergyman and hymnodist .
Enoch Wedgwood ( 1813 - 1879 ) was an English potter , founder in 1860 of the pottery firm Wedgwood & Co of Tunstall , Stoke - on - Trent .
Gilles Mureau ( also Mureue , as he spelled it himself ) ( c. 1450 -- July 1512 ) was a French composer and singer of the Renaissance .
Childs Frick ( 1883 - -1965 ) was an American vertebrate paleontologist .
Rick Fay ( December 25 , 1926 -- 1999 ) was an American jazz clarinetist and saxophonist .
Cato Bontjes van Beek ( 14 November 1920 -- 5 August 1943 ) was a German member of the Resistance against the Nazi regime .
Reginald Beddington CBE ( c. 1878 -- 11 March 1962 ) was an English angler and humanitarian .
Meng Caicheng ( 1859 - -1928 ) was one of the leaders of Railway Protection Movement , which contributed to the outbreak of the Xinhai Revolution that overthrow the Qing Dynasty and established the Republic of China .
Johan Henrik Rye ( 1 November 1787 , in Bø , Telemark -- 14 July 1868 ) was a Norwegian jurist and politician .
Santo Tagliafico , also known as Santino Fortunato Tagliafichi , ( 1756 - 1829 ) was an Italian painter , mainly active in Genoa .
Gao Yu ( 高郁 ) ( died 929 ) was a chief strategist for the Chinese Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms state Chu .
Carlo Arrigoni ( 6 December 1697 -- 19 August 1744 was an Italian composer and musician who was active in several countries during the first half of the 18th century .
Laurence Whitaker ( c. 1578 -- 15 April 1654 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1624 and 1653 .
Donald Victor Darwin ( 11 October 1896 - 8 March 1972 ) , M.M. , M.C.E. , M.I.C.E. , M.I.E. ( Aust . )
Colonel David Synnot ( alt Sinnot ) was Governor of Wexford during the Sack of Wexford by Oliver Cromwell in 1649 .
Hermann Crüger ( 11 February 1818 , Hamburg -- 28 February 1864 , San Fernando ) was a German pharmacist and botanist .
Eliyahu - Moshe Ganhovsky ( Hebrew : אליהו - משה גנחובסקי‎ , 23 June 1901 -- 19 July 1971 ) was an Israeli politician and Religious Zionist activist .
Francis Curteis ( 26 June 1856 -- 1 May 1928 ) was an English cricketer .
Rudolf von Beckerath ( 19 February 1907 -- 22 November 1976 ) was a German master organ builder .
Anders Franzén ( 23 July 1918 -- 8 December 1993 ) was a Swedish marine technician and an amateur naval archaeologist .
Sammy Johnson ( May 14 , 1949 , Gateshead -- November 1998 ) was an English actor .
Joseph Sunnen ( June 16 , 1897 - -April 1979 ) was born in the coal mining town of Thayer , Illinois .
David Landsborough ( 11 August 1779 -- 12 September 1854 ) was a Scottish clergyman and naturalist .
Barnabas Oley ( 1602 - -1686 ) was an English churchman and academic .
Colonel Richard Henry Beddome ( 11 May 1830 -- 23 February 1911 ) was a British military officer and naturalist in India who became chief conservator of the Madras Forest Department .
Nicoletta Rizzi ( 1 January 1940 -- 17 January 2010 ) was an Italian television , stage and film actress .
Vicente Carvallo y Goyeneche ( 1742 - -1816 ) was a Chilean soldier , author and historian of Basque descent , born in Valdivia .
Berkely Mather the pseudonym of John Evan Weston - Davies,(25 February 1909 -- 7 March 1996 ) was a British author who published fifteen novels and a book of short stories .
Oskar J. W. Hansen ( March 9 , 1891 -September 1971 ) was a Norwegian - born , naturalized American sculptor .
Antanas Impulevičius - Impulėnas ( 28 January 1907 -- 4 December 1970 ) was an officer of the Lithuanian Army , reaching the rank of major in 1937 .
Ma Chengxiang ( 1914 - -1991 ) ( simplified Chinese : 马呈祥 ; traditional Chinese : 馬呈祥 ; pinyin : Mǎ Chéngxiáng ; Wade -- Giles : Ma Chêng - hsiang ) was a Chinese Muslim general in the National Revolutionary Army .
Francisca Fernández - Hall Zúñiga ( 1921 - -2002 ) was a Guatemalan engineer and diplomat .
Cæsar Clement ( died 28 August 1626 ) was an English Catholic recusant .
The Right Honourable John Lubbock , 1st Baron Avebury PC FRS DCL LLD ( 30 April 1834 -- 28 May 1913 ) , known as Sir John Lubbock , 4th Baronet from 1865 until 1900 , was a banker , Liberal politician , philanthropist , scientist and polymath .
Per Skou ( 20 May 1891 -- 24 February 1962 ) was a Norwegian footballer , sports official and businessperson .
Myra Albert Wiggins ( 1869 - -1956 ) was an American painter and pictorial photographer who became a member of the important early 20th century Photo - Secession movement .
Michael Jacobi ( 1618 - -1663 ) was a North German composer and kantor .
Johann Nepomuk Hummel ( 14 November 1778 -- 17 October 1837 ) was an Austrian composer and virtuoso pianist .
Harjol ( 1609 -- 1641 ) was a consort of the Qing Dynasty ruler Hong Taiji .
Thomas Wijck ( also Thomas Wijk , or Thomas Wyck ; 1616 - -1677 ) was a Dutch painter of port views and genre paintings .
Cecilia Mujica ( nickname , `` known as ' ' The Martyr of Freedom `` '' ; died 1813 ) is a Venezuelan heroine noted for her support for the country 's independence and her work with the independence forces .
Kent Walton ( 22 August 1917 -- 24 August 2003 ) , born Kenneth Walton Beckett , was a British television sports commentator and presenter .
Dominick Arduin ( 1961 - -2004 ) was a Frenchwoman who disappeared in her attempt to ski to the North Pole .
Dirck or Theodoor Galle ( 16 July 1571 -- 18 December 1633 ) was a Flemish Baroque engraver .
Lyman Andrews died Friday 13 February 2009 at his apartment in Nottingham .
David Gwyn Francis ( 2 February 1896 -- 7 May 1987 ) was a Welsh international rugby union player , who played for the Welsh national side twice ( in 1919 and 1924 ) .
Carl Gustaf Roos ( before 1705 , Carl Gustaf Roos af Hjelmsäter ; 1655 - -1722 ) was a friherre and Major General of the Carolean Swedish Army .
Willem Huydecoper ( November 1788 -- 22 February 1826 ) was an important mulatto merchant , politician , and diplomat on the Dutch Gold Coast in the late eighteenth and early nineteenth century .
Willis Kent ( 1878 - 1966 ) was an independent American film producer .
Ahmed Francis ( 1912 - -1968 ) was an Algerian politician and nationalist .
Clara Rousby ( 1852?--1879 ) was an actress who made notable appearances on the London stage .
Georgette Harvey ( 1882 - -1952 ) was an American singer and actress , perhaps most famous for creating the role of Maria in the original 1935 Broadway production of George Gershwin 's opera Porgy and Bess .
Sir George Osborne Morgan , 1st Baronet PC , QC , ( 8 May 1826 -- 25 August 1897 ) was a Welsh lawyer and Liberal politician .
Adriaan Heereboord ( 13 October 1613 , Leiden -- 7 July 1661 , Leiden ) was a Dutch philosopher and logician .
Leif Raa ( 19 May 1931 -- 30 January 2003 ) was a Norwegian illustrator and cartoonist .
Edward Adam Strecker , M.D. ( 1896 - 1959 ) was an American physician , a psychiatric educator , a professor of psychiatry at several medical schools , and a leader in American psychiatry during the mid - twentieth century .
Rudy Williams ( nicknamed Looney ; 1909 - -1954 ) was an American jazz alto saxophonist , son of the well - known bandleader Fess Williams and cousin of the jazz great Charles Mingus .
James Witt Sewell ( 1865 - -1955 ) was a writer and professor of the English language at the Hume - Fogg High School in Nashville , Tennessee .
Thomas Erskine , 1st Baron Erskine KT PC KC ( 10 January 1750 -- 17 November 1823 ) was a British lawyer and politician .
Mzee Herman Kingori Maingi ( 1920 - - 30 December 2009 ) had a diversified career with strong bias towards the Cooperative movement and the Agricultural sector .
Hwang Jin ( Hangul : 황진 , Hanja : 黃進 , 1550 - -1593 ) was a general during Japanese invasions of Korea .
Richard Blakemore ( 8 August 1775 -- 17 April 1855 ) , MP was an ironmaster and politician .
Hendrick Berckman ( 1629 -- buried 27 March 1679 ) was a Dutch Golden Age painter .
Taw Sein Ko ( Burmese : တော်စိန်ကို ; Chinese : 杜成誥 ; pinyin : Dù Chénggào ; Pe̍h - ōe - jī : Tō͘ Sêng - kò ; 7 December 1864 -- 29 May 1930 ) was Burma 's first recorded archaeologist .
J. Roger Porter ( 1909 in Alma , Nebraska -- 1979 in Iowa City , Iowa ) was an internationally known microbiologist .
Siri Perera QC ( February 1910 -- 1995 ) was a Criminal lawyer , a Buddhist leader who was one time the President of the Colombo YMBA .
Lyman Belding ( 12 June 1829 - 22 November 1917 ) was a prominent American ornithologist .
Nagi Daifullah ( 1949 - August , 1973 ; Arabic : ناجي ضيف الله ) was a Yemeni migrant to the United States and union organizer with the United Farm Workers .
Juana María de Iturbide y Huarte ( 10 March 1812 -- 2 October 1828 ) , Princess of Mexico , known as Sister Margarita of Jesus , was the third child of Agustín I of Mexico ( Agustín de Iturbide ) and Empress Ana María .
Earl Richmond ( Real name John Dienn ) , was a broadcaster born in Highgate , London in 1928 , he died in May 2001 .
Kanji Morarji Rathor / Kanzi Morarji Rathore ( 1913 - -1989 ) was a Kutchi industrialist from Raipur , India .
Jean - François Théodore ( 5 December 1946 -- 18 May 2015 ) was a French businessman , President , Chairman and CEO of Euronext N.V. , deputy CEO and Head of Strategy of NYSE Euronext Inc. for Euronext N.V and chairman of its Managing Board .
Lord George Graham ( 26 September 1715 -- 2 January 1747 ) was an officer of the Royal Navy who saw service during the Wars of the Quadruple Alliance and Austrian Succession .
Sir Edward Barry , 1st Baronet FRS ( 1696 -- 29 March 1776 ) was an Irish physician and politician .
George Lovejoy ( died February 2003 ) was an Australian radio sports commentator who is known for his broadcasts of Queensland rugby league football matches in the 1950s and 60s .
Robin Mallapert ( fl . 1538 - -1553 ) was a French musician of the Renaissance , probably a composer , who spent most of his life in Rome .
Lauderic Caton ( 31 August 1910 -- 19 February 1999 ) was a Trinidadian guitarist who settled in Britain in 1940 .
Anita Elson ( 1898 - -1985 ) was an American dancer and singer who appeared in revues in New York City and London , England , in the early 20th century .
Michael Vincent O'Brien ( 9 April 1917 -- 1 June 2009 ) was an Irish race horse trainer from Churchtown , County Cork , Ireland .
Mael Ísu Ua Brolcháin ( died 1086 ) was a member of a high - class ecclesiastical family , based in what is now Donegal .
Stuart Paton ( 23 July 1883 -- 16 December 1944 ) was a British director , screenwriter and actor of the silent era .
Captain Cowper Phipps Coles , C.B. , R.N. ( 1819 -- 7 September 1870 ) , was an English naval captain and inventor ; he was the first to patent a design for a revolving gun turret .
Nicolas Steno ( Danish : Niels Steensen ; Latinized to Nicolaus Stenonis or Nicolaus Stenonius ; 1 January 1638 -- 25 November 1686 ( NS : 11 January 1638 -- 5 December 1686 ) ) was a Danish scientist , a pioneer in both anatomy and geology who became a Catholic bishop in his later years .
Casriel Dovid Kaplin , ( 1931 - -2006 ) , was a rabbi and a dayan in the London Beth Din .
Sargis I Jaqeli ( Georgian : სარგის I ჯაყელი ) ( died 1285 ) was a Georgian ruling prince ( mtavari ) of the House of Jaqeli who became the first sovereign Prince of Samtskhe in 1268 .
Xu Heng ( Chinese : 許衡 ) ( 1209 - -1281 ) was a Confucianist and educator of the Yuan Dynasty in China .
John Wiles ( 20 September 1925 -- 5 April 1999 ) was a television writer and producer , now best known for being the second producer of the popular science fiction serial Doctor Who , succeeding Verity Lambert .
Lieutenant - General Davidson Masuku SSAS MMM KStJ ( 8 March 1940 - 17 April 2000 ) was a South African military commander and physician .
Alec Eason ( 8 November 1889 -- 5 May 1956 ) was an Australian rules football player , coach and administrator in the Victorian Football League and Victorian Football Association .
Girolamo Muziano ( c. 1532 -- 1592 ) , was one of the most prominent Italian painters , active in the mid - to - late sixteenth century .
Princess Htake Hsu Myat Phaya ( Burmese : ထိပ္စုမြတ်ဖုရား ; 7 March 1886 - 21 July 1962 ) , born in Madras , was the third daughter of the last ruling king of Burma , King Thibaw .
Michael C. Sedgwick ( 1926 - -1983 ) was a British motoring writer .
Jackie Gilroy ( 1942 - -2007 ) is a former Gaelic footballer for Dublin and St Vincents .
Song Qi ( 宋祁 , 998 - -1061 ) was a Chinese statesman , historian , essayist and poet of the Song Dynasty .
Norman Lind ( 1920/1921 -- 23 October 1985 ) was a British - Norwegian military officer and consul .
Saleh Suleiman ( Arabic : صالح سليمان‎ , Hebrew : צאלח סלימאן‎ ; born 1888 , died 24 November 1980 ) was an Israeli Arab politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Progress and Work between 1955 and 1959 .
Charles William Barkley ( 1759 -- 16 May 1832 ) was a ship captain and maritime fur trader .
Raymond Sarif Easmon ( 15 January 1913 - -2 May 1997 ) was a prominent Sierra Leonean doctor known for his literary work and political agitation .
Barney Josephson ( 1902 - -1988 ) was the founder of Café Society in Greenwich Village , New York 's first integrated nightclub .
Nikola Kesarovski ( Bulgarian : Никола Кесаровски ) ( c. 1935 -- 29 August 2007 ) was a Bulgarian science - fiction writer .
Maria Vittoria of Savoy ( Maria Vittoria Filiberta ; 29 September 1814 -- 2 January 1874 ) was a Princess of Savoy by birth and later a princess of the Two Sicilies by virtue of her marriage to Prince Leopold of Two Sicilies , Count of Syracuse , a younger son King Francis I of the Two Sicilies .
Monika Kinley OBE ( 24 August 1925 -- 9 March 2014 ) was a British art dealer , collector and curator , particularly noted for her championing of the work and integrity of outsider artists .
Dick Chama ( 11 February 1946 -- 21 March 2006 ) was a Zambian footballer and coach who has been described as Zambia 's best ever centre - back .
Homer Eon Flint ( 1888 as Homer Eon Flindt --1924 ) was a writer of pulp science fiction novels and stories .
Jerzy Wyrobek ( 17 December 1949 -- 26 March 2013 ) is a Polish football player and coach .
Viktoras Biržiška ( February 23 , 1886 , Viekšniai - 27 January 1964 Chicago ) was a Lithuanian mathematician , engineer , journalist , and encyclopedist of noble extraction .
Alberto Lupo ( byname of Alberto Zoboli ; 19 December 1924 - 13 August 1984 ) was an Italian film and television actor best known for his roles in swash - buckling and actions films of the 1960s .
Giuseppe Petrilli ( 1913 ? -- 13 May 1999 ? ) was an Italian professor and European Commissioner .
Munir Ahmed Shakir ( also spelled Muneer Shakir or Munir Shakar ) ( 1967 ? -- 14 August 2011 ) was an online journalist for the Online News Network and was also a TV correspondent for Sabzbaat , also known as Sabzbagh , a Baluch television station .
Ethel Rolt Wheeler ( July 12 , 1869 , Lewisham , London -- October 1958 , Glasgow ) was an English poet , author and journalist .
Al Ferguson ( 19 April 1888 -- 4 December 1971 ) was an Irish - born American film actor .
Madge Davison ( 13 June 1950 -- 27 January 1991 ) was a member of the National Executive Committee of the Communist Party of Ireland in the 1970s and was the first general secretary of the Connolly Youth Movement after it became an all - Ireland body in 1970 .
Olav Roots ( 26 February 1910 -- 30 January 1974 ) was an Estonian pianist and composer .
David Ross Lietch ( c1809 - 1881 ) was a 19th - century Tyneside born poet and songwriter .
David Bruce Dill ( 1891 - 1986 ) was an American physiologist specializing in exercise science and environmental physiology .
Johann Matthäus Bechstein ( 11 July 1757 -- 23 February 1822 ) was a German naturalist , forester , ornithologist , entomologist , and herpetologist .
Matthew Le Marinel ( 1883 or 1884 -- 22 January 1963 ) was a Jersey clergyman , who became Dean of Jersey .
John Garstang ( 5 May 1876 -- 12 September 1956 ) was a British archaeologist of the ancient Near East , especially Anatolia and the southern Levant .
Alexander Stewart , 1st Earl of Galloway ( c. 1580 - 9 October 1649 ) was the son of Sir Alexander Stewart , 6th Laird of Garlies , and his 1st wife Christian Douglas , daughter of Sir James Douglas , 7th Baron Drumlanrig .
Eric Clauesson ( or Erik Klasson ) ( died 1492 ) was a Swedish man executed for sorcery , theft and heresy , though in reality , this was an execution for Paganism .
Alasdair mac Mhaighstir Alasdair ( lit . Alexander , Son of the Reverend Alexander ) ( c. 1698 - -1770 ) was a Scottish poet , lexicographer , political writer and memoirist , respected as perhaps the finest Gaelic language poet of the 18th century .
Antonio Bonvisi ( died 1558 ) was an Anglo - Italian merchant in London .
Richard Michael Fox ( 1891 - -December 1969 ) , better known as R. M. Fox , was a journalist and historian of the Irish left .
Saucisse ( c. 1998 - -2014 ) was a dachshund who gained fame in France as the protagonist of a book series .
Luigi Pasquarelli ( Marsiconovo , Basilicata , died 1889 ) was an Italian sculptor .
Prince Jagat Singh(15 October 1949 -- February 5 , 1997 ) also known in his native state as Maharaja Jagat Singh of Jaipur , Raja of Isarda , was the fourth and youngest son of Sawai Man Singh II , last ruling Maharaja of Jaipur .
Nathaniel Eaton ( 1610 - -1674 ) was the first schoolmaster of Harvard College in Cambridge , Massachusetts , and later became a clergyman .
Timoleon Vassos or Vasos ( Greek : Τιμολέων Βάσσος or Βάσος ; 1836 - -1929 ) was a Greek Army officer and general .
Martha Grey , Countess of Stamford ( c. 1838 -- 21 August 1916 ) was born Martha Solomons in Cape Town , South Africa .
George Edward Ayscough ( died 1779 ) was an English dramatist and traveller .
Osmond Gilles ( 24 August 1788 -- 25 September 1866 ) was a settler , pastoralist , mine owner and South Australia 's first colonial treasurer .
Annia Fundania Faustina ( died 192 ) was a noble Roman woman who lived in the 2nd century during the Roman Empire .
Orazio Grassi , S.J. ( 1 May 1583 -- 23 July 1654 ) , was an Italian Jesuit priest , who is best noted as a mathematician , astronomer and architect .
Kwesi Akwansah Andam ( died 14 December 2007 ) was a Ghanaian academician and former Vice Chancellor of the Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology .
Lorenzo Gordin Yates ( 1837 - 1909 ) was an American paleontologist .
Anthony Leigh ( died 1692 ) was a celebrated English comic actor .
Karl Münchinger ( 29 May 1915 -- 13 March 1990 ) was a German conductor of European classical music .
Edward Manton ( ca.1760 - 1820 ) was a delegate to the Hartford Convention in 1814 - 15 .
Alexander Strausz ( 1829 - -1905 ) was a Hungarian - born American brewer , cartographer , architect , mining engineer , industrialist and school superintendent .
Arthur Bird ( 23 July 1856 -- 22 December 1923 ) was an American composer , for many years resident in Germany .
Petar Perunović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Петар Перуновић ) ( 1880 -- 10 June 1952 ) , nicknamed Perun , was a famous Serbian gusle player from Montenegro .
Aryeh Sheftel ( Hebrew : אריה שפטל‎ , born 1905 , died 28 September 1980 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset and mayor of Rishon LeZion .
Sir Dafydd ap Llewelyn ap Hywel ( c. 1380 -- 25 October 1415 ) , better known as Dafydd Gam or Davy Gam , was a Welsh medieval nobleman , a prominent opponent of Owain Glyndŵr .
Esther Eberstadt Baldwin ( 1894 - -1987 ) , better known as Esther Eberstadt Brooke , was an author and vocational counselor .
Thomas Herle ( 29 December 1622 -- c. June 1681 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1659 and 1679 .
Thalia Mara ( 1911 - -2003 ) was an American ballet educator and author of books on the subject .
Sir John Johnson , 2nd Baronet of New York ( 5 November 1741 -- 4 January 1830 ) was a Loyalist leader during the American Revolution , a politician in Canada and a wealthy landowner .
François Thijssen or Frans Thijsz ( died 13 October 1638 ? ) was a Dutch explorer who explored the southern coast of Australia .
Carlo Asinari ( 3 November 1884 -- 17 May 1962 ) was an Italian show jumping rider , that won a bronze medal at the Olympic Games .
Sir Ernest Daryl Lindsay ( 31 December 1889 , Creswick , Victoria -- 25 December 1976 , Mornington ) was an Australian artist and member of the creative Lindsay family .
Ray Brew also known as John Raymond Brew ( 14 January 1903 -- 21 August 1979 ) was an Australian rules footballer in the Victorian Football League .
José Luis Paris , better known as Don José ( Ferrol , 1936 - -2003 ) was a Spanish musician , and singer who from the 1970s lived in London .
Elon Howard Eaton ( sometimes Elon Eton ; 8 October 1866 -- 27 March 1934 ) was an American ornithologist , scholar , and author .
Arthur Machen ( /ˈmækən/ ; 3 March 1863 -- 15 December 1947 ) was a Welsh author and mystic of the 1890s and early 20th century .
Heinrich Rudolf Hildebrand ( 13 March 1824 -- 28 October 1894 ) was a Germanist , contributor to , and then , editor of the Grimm brothers ' Deutsches Wörterbuch .
Antoine Favre , baron of Pérouges ( 5 October 1557 -- 1624 ) was a Savoisian nobleman and jurist .
Paul - Alexis Dubois ( 27 January 1754 -- 4 September 1796 ) commanded French divisions during the War of the First Coalition and was killed in action fighting against Habsburg Austria .
Joseph Thomas Hector Gratton ( 13 August 1900 -- 16 July 1970 ) was a Canadian composer , arranger , conductor , pianist , and music educator .
Walter Goodman ( 11 May 1838 -- 20 August 1912 ) was an English painter , illustrator and author .
Pedro de San Superano ( also spelled San Superán , in French Pierre de Saint - Superan ; died 1402 ) was one of the captains of the Navarrese Company in the Morea from 1379 until he was made Prince of Achaea in 1396 , a post he held to his death .
Thomas Pingo ( 1714 - -1776 ) was an English medallist and die engraver .
Benjamin Smith Lyman ( 11 December 1835 -- 30 August 1920 ) was an American mining engineer , surveyor , and an amateur linguist and anthropologist .
William Salkeld ( 1671 - -1715 ) , legal writer , was the son of Samuel Salkeld of Fallowden , Northumberland , who died in 1699 , and came of an ancient Cumberland family .
Edward Daniel Leahy ( 1797 -- 9 February 1875 ) was an Irish portrait and subject painter .
Friedrich Ramm ( 1744 - -1813 ) was a German oboist for whom Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart wrote several works .
Peter Herbolzheimer ( 31 December 1935 -- 27 March 2010 ) was a German jazz trombonist and bandleader .
Arthur Hugh Chaplin CB ( 1905 - -1996 ) was Principal Keeper of Printed Books at the British Museum .
Catherine Sinclair ( 17 April 1800 -- 6 August 1864 ) was a Scottish novelist and writer of children 's literature .
Xia Qin ( Chinese : 夏勤 ) ( 1892 - -1950 ) was President of the Supreme Court of the Republic of China ( February 3 , 1945 -- July 13 , 1948 ) .
Fritz Quednow ( 6 April 1914 -- 27 April 1943 ) was a Hauptmann in the Wehrmacht during World War II .
Joakim Lehmkuhl ( 22 September 1895 -- 15 October 1984 ) was a Norwegian engineer , industrialist and politician .
Horace Ridler ( March 26 , 1882 - -1969 ) was a professional freak and sideshow performer , a tattooed man exhibiting himself as The Great Omi or The Zebra Man .
Piter Poel ( 17 June 1760 - 3 October 1837 ) was a diplomat who in his later years became the publisher if the `` Altonaischer Mercurius '' ( newspaper ) .
John de Sècheville ( or John de Sicca Villa ) ( died 1302 ) was a philosopher in the thirteenth century ; his most famous work was his `` De Principiis Naturae '' .
Enrique Guerra ( 1871 - -1922 ) was a Mexican sculptor from Xalapa , Veracruz .
Cornelius Heinrich Dretzel ( 18 September 1697 ( bapt . ) -- 7 May 1775 ) was a German organist and composer .
George Whalley ( 25 July 1915 -- 27 May 1983 ) was a scholar , poet , naval officer and secret intelligence agent during World War II , CBC broadcaster , musician , biographer , and translator .
Sigerson Clifford ( 1913 -- 1 January 1985 ) was an Irish poet , playwright and civil servant .
Sigismund Bachrich ( 23 January 1841 -- 16 July 1913 ) , aka Sigmund Bachrich or Siegmund Bachrich , was a Hungarian composer of Jewish origin , violinist , and violist .
Johannes Georg Smith Harder , known as Hans Harder ( born Copenhagen , 12 August 1792 - died Sorø , 25 November 1873 ) was a Danish painter and drawing master .
Charles Loring Elliott ( 1812 - -1868 ) was an American painter known for his portraits .
Sir Walter Beauchamp ( died 1 January 1430 ) was an English lawyer and Speaker of the House of Commons of England between March and May 1416 .
Sir Walter Calverley Trevelyan ( 31 March 1797 -- 23 March 1879 ) was an English naturalist and geologist .
Pavel Vranický , later Germanized as Paul Wranitzky ( 30 December 1756 -- 29 September 1808 ) , was a Moravian classical composer .
Seymour Gates Pond ( 1896 - -1976 ) was an American adventurer and writer .
Robert Plutchik ( 21 October 1927 -- 29 April 2006 ) was professor emeritus at the Albert Einstein College of Medicine and adjunct professor at the University of South Florida .
Piero Vivarelli ( 26 February 1927 -- 7 September 2010 ) was an Italian film director , screenwriter and lyricist .
Drypetis or Drypteis ( died 323 BCE ) , was a princess of the Achaemenid dynasty in Persia .
Vidal Vega ( 1964 -- 1 December 2012 ) was a Paraguayan political leader .
Ruth Sawtell Wallis ( 15 March 1895 -- 21 January 1978 ) was an American academic and physical anthropologist .
Robert Hope - Jones ( 9 February 1859 -- 13 September 1914 ) is considered to be the inventor of the theatre organ in the early 20th century .
Marie Kraja or Marie Paluca ( 24 September 1911 -- 21 November 1999 ) was an Albanian opera singer , who is particularly known for her delivery of Albanian folk songs .
Stanisław Abłamowicz ( 1844 - 1901 ) was a Polish political activist and lawyer .
Edmund George Lind ( June 18 , 1829 -- 1909 ) was an English - born American architect , active in Baltimore , Atlanta , and the American south .
Horrie Jenkin ( 14 February 1893 -- 17 January 1985 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the VFL .
Yusuf Hamdan ( died December 1939 ) was a Palestinian rebel commander during the 1936 - 1939 Arab revolt in British Mandatory Palestine .
Sir Charles Tilston Bright ( 8 June 1832 -- 3 May 1888 ) was a British electrical engineer who oversaw the laying of the first transatlantic telegraph cable in 1858 , for which work he was knighted .
Owen Hall ( 10 April 1853 -- 9 April 1907 ) was the principal pen name of the Irish - born theatre writer , racing correspondent , theatre critic and solicitor , James `` Jimmy '' Davis , when writing for the stage .
Walter Rye ( 31 October 1843 -- 24 February 1929 ) was a British athlete and antiquary , who wrote over 80 works on Norfolk .
Edward Digby , 2nd Earl Digby ( 6 January 1773 -- 12 May 1856 ) , known as Viscount Coleshill from 1790 to 1793 , was a British peer .
Robin Dey ( Assamese : ৰবিন দে ; 18 March 1922 -- 22 July 1980 ) was a noted Assamese thriller novelist and actor from Assam .
Friedrich Albrecht Anton Meyer ( 29 June 1768 -- 29 November 1795 ) was a German doctor and naturalist .
Sir Edward Gerald Butler ( 1770 - -1824 ) ( named as Edward Gerard Butler in the Dictionary of National Biography ) was an Irish soldier .
Hans Heiberg ( 28 January 1904 -- 6 December 1978 ) was a Norwegian journalist , literary critic , theatre critic , essayist , novelist , playwright , translator and theatre director .
Tom Nickalls ( 1827 - -1899 ) who was a stockjobber on the stock exchange and one of the founding members of London Rowing Club .
José María Reyes Mata ( 1943 - 1983 ) was a Honduran revolutionary sympathizer of Fidel Castro and trained as both a doctor and in internationalist revolutionary thought in Cuba .
José do Telhado ( 1818 - 1875 ) was a Portuguese bandit .
W. A. Robinson ( died 11 June 1895 ) was a British administrator who was appointed the first Principal of Aitchison College , Lahore , then in British India , on 20 November 1886 .
Francis Bernasconi ( 1762 -- 1 January 1841 ) , aka Francisco Bernasconi , was an English ornamental carver and plasterer of Italian descent .
Clark Bentom ( c. 1774 -- c. 1820 ) was an English missionary and surgeon , who was a missionary in Canada at Quebec City , Quebec , from 1800 to 1805 .
Charles A. Kelly ( died 6 September 1962 ) was the last person executed by Iowa .
Lock Crowther ( c. 1940?--1993 ; first name by birth Lachlan ) was an Australian multihull sailboat designer .
François Leclerc du Tremblay ( 4 November 1577 -- 17 December 1638 ) , also known as Père Joseph , was a French Capuchin friar , confidant and agent of Cardinal Richelieu .
Nicholas Lockyer ( 1611 - -1685 ) was an English clergyman and Independent minister , a close supporter of Oliver Cromwell and Provost of Eton College , and later an ejected minister and nonconformist .
Michel Sarrazin , ( 5 September 1659 - -8 September 1734 ) , was an early Canadian surgeon , physician , scientist and naturalist .
John Buxton Marsden ( 1803 -- 16 June 1870 ) was an English cleric , known as a historical writer and editor .
Enrico Fonda ( 1892 - - 1929 ) was an Italian painter born in Fiume ( now in Croatia ) .
Emma Smock ( 4 June 1920 - -1995 ) , better known as Ginger Smock , was a violinist , orchestra leader , and local Los Angeles television personality .
Beatrice Edgell ( 26 October 1871 -- 10 August 1948 ) was a British psychologist , researcher and university teacher .
Panagiotis Doxaras ( Greek : Παναγιώτης Δοξαράς ) ( 1662 - -1729 ) was a Greek painter who founded the Heptanese School of Greek art .
Raymond Caruana was a Maltese Nationalist Party activist , murdered at the Gudja club headquarters on 5 December 1986 , at the age of 26 .
Dorothy Bentinck , Duchess of Portland ( née Lady Dorothy Cavendish ; 27 August 1750 - 3 June 1794 ) was Duchess of Portland as wife of William Cavendish - Bentinck , 3rd Duke of Portland , the Prime Minister of Great Britain .
Otto I , Count of Scheyern ( some authors call him Otto II of Scheyern ; c. 1020 -- before 4 December 1072 ) was the most ancient ancestor of the House of Wittelsbach whose relation with the House can be properly verified .
George Mackenzie Brown ( 1869 -- 14 July 1946 ) was a Canadian - born Scottish publisher who also followed a political career .
Asma Belkhodja ( 1930 -- 2011 ) was a pioneer of the Tunisian feminist movement .
Rheinallt Nantlais Williams MBE ( 1911 -- 1993 ) was a Welsh professor of the philosophy of religion and principal of the Presbyterian United Theological College Aberystwyth in Wales .
Ingolf Mork ( 4 June 1947 -- 1 February 2012 ) was a Norwegian ski jumper who was born in Molde , and represented IL Hjelset - Fram and SFK Lyn in Oslo .
Oswald Bertram Lower ( born 1863 in Adelaide , South Australia -- died 18 March 1925 in Wayville , South Australia ) was an Australian chemist and pharmacist who is best known for his contributions to entomology , in particular butterflies and moths .
Margaret Kelly Leibovici ( 24 June 1910 -- 11 September 2004 ) , known as Miss Bluebell , was an Irish dancer who was the founder of the Bluebell Girls dance troupe .
Shao Hua ( 30 October 1938 -- 24 June 2008 ) , formerly known as Zhang Shao Hua ( 张少华 ) , born Chen Anyun ( 陈安云 ) , was a Chinese photographer and a major general in the People 's Liberation Army .
Roger I of Tosny or Roger of Hispania ( d. ca . 1040 ) was a Norman nobleman of the House of Tosny who took part in the Reconquista of Iberia .
Deloss Barnum ( 1825 - 1873 ) was a photographer in New York and Boston , Massachusetts in the mid-19th century .
Yu Shiji ( 虞世基 ) ( died 618 ) , courtesy name Maoshi ( 懋世 or 茂世 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasties Chen Dynasty and Sui Dynasty .
Jomar Brun MBE ( 18 June 1904 -- 26 August 1993 ) was a Norwegian chemical engineer .
Nguyễn Huy Tưởng ( làng Dục Tú , Từ Sơn , Bắc Ninh , 6 May 1912 -- 25 July 1960 ) was a Vietnamese revolutionary , writer and playwright .
Robert Dick Douglas ( 1875 - 1960 ) was a North Carolina attorney who served as North Carolina Attorney General briefly in 1900 - 1901 .
Kostandin Boshnjaku ( 1888 - -1953 ) was an Albanian banker , and politician .
Sir William Gore Ouseley ( 26 July 1797 -- 6 March 1866 ) was a British diplomat who served in various roles in Washington , D.C. , Rio de Janeiro and Buenos Aires .
Katharine Goodson ( 18 June 1872 -- 14 April 1958 ) was an English pianist .
Rai Bahadur Sir Badridas Goenka CIE ( 29 July 1883 - 26 February 1973 ) was an Indian industrialist and business tycoon who served as the Chairman of the Imperial Bank of India from 1933 to 1955 and the first Chairman of the State Bank of India upon its formation in 1955 .
Robert Kirby ( 16 April 1948 -- 3 October 2009 ) was a British - born arranger of string sections for rock and folk music .
Edward Martyn ( 30 January 1859 -- 5 December 1923 ) was an Irish playwright and early republican political and cultural activist , as the first president of Sinn Féin from 1905 to 1908 .
Hans - Jürgen Stammer ( born 21 September 1899 in Pötrau near Büchen ; died 24 Oktober 1968 in Erlangen ) was a German zoologist , ecologist and director of the Zoological Institute of the University Erlangen .
Synnøve Lie ( 22 August 1908 -- 9 July 1980 ) was a Norwegian speed skater .
Jakob Friedrich Caflisch ( 3 March 1817 -- 9 May 1882 ) was a German botanist born near Memmingen .
Nikolay Tess ( Latvian : Nikolajs Tess , Russian : Николай Тэсс ; born 1921 , died 2006 in Riga , Latvia ) was one of the few functionaries in charge of political repressions in the former Soviet Union who were convicted for this activity .
Börje Tapper ( 19 May 1922 -- 8 April 1981 ) was a Swedish footballer .
Percy Sheehan ( 5 July 1883 -- 30 May 1946 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy , Carlton and Richmond Football Clubs in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Harihar Vaman Deshpande ( 5 March 1905 -- 20 April 1965 ) was born at Chendkapur ( Amravati ) Maharashtra , India .
William Broderick Cloete ( 1851 -- 7 May 1915 ) was a British industrialist active in the border zones between Mexico and the United States in the late 19th century .
Saint Alban of Mainz ( b. unknown , Greece or Albania ; d. c. 406 in Mainz ) was a priest , missionary , and martyr .
Taklung Thangpa Tashi Pal ( 1142 - -1210 ) is the Founder of the Taklung Kagyu lineage .
Namdev , also transliterated as Namdeo and Namadeva , ( traditionally , c. 1270 -- c. 1350 ) was a poet - saint from Maharashtra , India who is significant to the Varkari sect of Hinduism .
Mike Mahaffey ( 1967 - -2005 ) was a founding member of the power pop band Self .
Eleanor Robson Belmont ( 13 December 1879 -- 24 October 1979 ) was an English actress and prominent public figure in the United States .
Francis Tate ( 1560 - -1616 ) was an English antiquary and politician , Member of Parliament for Northampton and Shrewsbury .
Margaret Young Taylor ( 24 April 1837 -- 3 May 1919 ) was a member of the inaugural general presidency of what is today the Young Women organization of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter - day Saints ( LDS Church ) from 1880 to 1887 .
Henry Gardinn ( died in Heusden or Maastricht , 1605 ) was an alleged sorcerer and werewolf .
Mariangela Melato ( 19 September 1941 -- 11 January 2013 ) was an Italian cinema and theater actress .
Chaekgye of Baekje ( died 298 , r. 286 - -298 ) was the ninth king of Baekje , one of the Three Kingdoms of Korea .
James L. O'Connor ( 1858 - -1931 ) was the Wisconsin Attorney General 1891 - 1895 .
Bartolommeo Salvestrini ( died Florence 1630 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , active mostly in Florence .
Janusz Jan Niemojewski ( 1531 - -1618 ) was a Polish nobleman , and theologian of the Polish Brethren .
Lina Tsaldari ( Greek : Λίνα Τσαλδάρη ; 1887 -- 17 October 1981 ) was a right - wing Greek politician .
Lorentz Eldjarn ( 23 March 1920 -- 11 February 2007 ) was a Norwegian biochemist and medical doctor .
Hasan Zvizdić ( 1892 - -1980 ) was a commander of a detachment of Muslim militia from Sjenica ( in Sandžak ) during the Second World War .
Godfrey Baseley ( 2 October 1904 -- 2 February 1997 ) , was a radio executive , who is most famous as being the creator of the soap opera The Archers .
Michael Bernhard Valentini ( 26 November 1657 -- 18 March 1729 ) was a German doctor and a collector .
Danguolė Rasalaitė ( 19 May 1983 -- 10 January 2000 ) was a Lithuanian girl who was sold as a sex - slave in Sweden late 1999 .
George Vaughan ( New Hampshire ) ( 13 April 1676 -- 20 November 1725 ) may be best known for being Lieutenant Governor of the Province of New Hampshire for only one year .
William Domville ( 1609 - 1689 ) was a leading Irish politician and barrister of the Restoration era .
Dr. Mallikarjun Goud ( 1941 -- 24 December 2002 ) was a Union Minister , President of Andhra Pradesh Congress Committee , and six - term member of the Parliament of India .
Minnie Kallmeyer ( 30 May 1882 -- 22 March 1947 ) was an American - born artist who spent most of her life in Canada .
Paul Panzer ( 3 November 1872 -- 16 August 1958 ) was a German - American silent film actor .
Jacob van Oudshoorn ( died ca . 18 September 1322 ) was bishop of Utrecht in 1322 .
Admiral Sir Israel Pellew , KCB , RN ( 25 August 1758 -- 19 July 1832 ) , was an English naval officer who spent his career under the shadow of his more successful older brother Edward Pellew .
Johann Michael Heineccius ( 14 December 1674 -- 11 September 1722 ) was a well - known German preacher and theologian , the brother of Johann Gottlieb Heineccius .
Michele Bianchi ( 22 July 1883 -- 3 February 1930 ) was an Italian revolutionary syndicalist leader .
Heinrich Petraeus ( Henricus Petraeus ) ( 1589 - -1620 ) was a German physician and writer .
Frans Wouters ( 1612 - -1659 ) was a Flemish Baroque painter who translated the monumental Baroque style of Peter Paul Rubens into the small context of cabinet paintings .
Taxile Doat ( 1851 - 1939 ) was a French potter who is primarily known for his experimentation with high - fired porcelain ( grand feu ) and stoneware using the pâte - sur - pâte technique .
Gianni Gallo ( Dogliani , 1935 -- Cuneo , 2011 ) was an Italian artist and engraver .
Henry Frederick Werker ( April 16 , 1920 - -May 10 , 1984 ) was an American lawyer and a judge of the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York .
Katharine Krom Merritt ( Stamford , Connecticut , 9 January 1886 -- Stamford , Connecticut , 5 August 1986 ) was an American physician specializing in pediatrics .
Dr Bernard Price , OBE , ( 1877 -- 9 July 1948 ) was the founding Chief Engineer and later General Manager of the Victoria Falls and Transvaal Power Company in South Africa between 1911 and 1936 .
Charles Louis von Doussa ( 17 May 1850 - 27 May 1932 ) , generally referred to as Louis von Doussa , was an Australian lawyer and politician .
Jacob Cohen Bakri ( born in Algiers in 1763 ; died Paris Nov. 23 , 1836 ) was involved in the Fly - whisk Incident which led to the French conquest of Algeria .
Rex Distin Martienssen , ARIBA , CIAM , 26 February 1905 Queenstown - 23 August 1942 Pretoria , was a South African architect who was greatly influenced by Le Corbusier and spearheaded a modernist architectural movement in South Africa .
Laurence Eusden ( bapt . 6 September 1688 -- 27 September 1730 ) was an English poet who became Poet Laureate in 1718 .
Conrad Bernier ( b. Quebec City 9 May 1904 , d. Washington , DC , 7 Nov 1988 ) was a French - Canadian organist , composer , and teacher .
Junius Henri Browne ( 14 October 1833 Seneca Falls , New York - 2 April 1902 New York City ) was an American journalist .
Thomas Helwys ( c. 1575 -- c. 1616 ) , an Englishman , was one of the joint founders , with John Smyth , of the General Baptist denomination .
Tursun Uljabayevich Uljabayev ( Tajiki : Турсун Ӯлҷабоев ) ( 1 May 1916- 31 May 1988 ) was First Secretary of the Communist Party of Tajikistan between May 24 , 1956 and April 12 , 1961 .
Armando Brancia ( 9 September 1917 -- 20 June 1997 ) is an Italian film and television actor .
Karol Wolfram ( * 5 November 1899 in Warsaw , died 21 September 1965 in Warsaw ) - was a polish evangelical priest , and professor of the Christian Theology Academy in Warsaw .
Forrest Reid ( born 24 June 1875 , Belfast , Ireland ; d. 4 January 1947 , Warrenpoint , County Down , Northern Ireland ) was an Irish novelist , literary critic and translator .
Samuel Tyszkiewicz ( 1889 - -1954 ) was a Polish typographer , member of the once powerful Tyszkiewicz noble family .
The Rt Rev Richard Rawle , DD , was Bishop of Trinidad and Tobago from 1872 , and Dean of its cathedral from 1878 , until his death in 1889 .
Maurice Guibert ( 1856 -- 1913 ) was a French photographer best known today as a friend of Henri de Toulouse - Lautrec .
Ruby Lindsay ( 20 March 1885 -- 12 March 1919 ) was an Australian illustrator and painter , sister of Norman Lindsay and Percy Lindsay .
John David Booth , ( 4 November 1950 -- 17 November 2011 ) was a Liberal Party member of the New South Wales Legislative Assembly , representing the electorate of Wakehurst from 24 March 1984 to 3 May 1991 .
Mohammad Aslam Watanjar ( 1946 -- 24 November 2000 ) was an Afghan general and politician .
Al - Mutawakkil Muhammad ( died 11 December 1849 ) was an Imam of Yemen who reigned from 1845 to 1849 .
William Maitland of Lethington ( 1525 -- 9 June 1573 ) was a Scottish politician and reformer , and the eldest son of poet Richard Maitland .
Shikaripura Ranganatha Rao ( Kannada : ಶಿಕಾರಿಪುರ ರಂಗನಾಥ ರಾವ್ ) ( 1 July 1922 -- 3 January 2013 ) , commonly known as Dr. S. R. Rao , was an Indian archeologist who led teams credited with the discovery of a number of Harappan sites including the port ciy Lothal and Bet Dwarka in Gujarat .
Anna Constantia von Brockdorff ( 17 October 1680 -- 31 March 1765 ) , later the Countess of Cosel , was a German noblewoman and mistress of Augustus the Strong , King of Poland and Elector of Saxony .
Brian Backhouse ( 7 May 1948 -- 13 September 2003 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with North Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Arthur William Moore CVO SHK JP MA ( 1853 - -1909 ) was a Manx antiquarian , historian , linguist , folklorist , and former Speaker of the House of Keys in the Isle of Man .
Dr. Kyaw Thet ( Burmese : ကျော်သက် , pronounced : ( tɕɔ̀ θɛʔ ) ; 1921 - -2008 ) was a historian of Burma , and longtime professor of Burmese and Eastern History Studies at the University of Rangoon .
Aurel Băeșu ( 1896 - 1928 ) was a Romanian Impressionist landscape and portrait painter .
Ursula Moray Williams ( 19 April 1911 -- 17 October 2006 ) was an English children 's author of nearly 70 books for children .
Ángel Bossio ( 5 May 1905 -- 31 August 1978 ) was an Argentine football ( soccer ) player who competed in the 1928 Olympic games .
Fateh Chand Badhwar OBE , MBE ( Mil . ) ( 1900 - 10 October 1995 ) was an Indian civil servant and the first Indian to become Chairman of the Railway Board .
Carlo Evasio Soliva ( 27 November 1791 -- 20 December 1853 ) was a Swiss - Italian composer of opera , chamber music , and sacred choral works .
Thorild Wulff ( born April 1 , 1877 in Gothenburg , died late August or early September 1917 in Northwest Greenland ) was a Swedish botanist and polar explorer .
Sir Walter Maude KCIE CSI ( 1862 -- 2 May 1943 ) was a British administrator in India .
James Cooley Fletcher ( 1823 - -1901 ) was a Presbyterian minister and missionary with strong activities in Brazilian lands .
Count Albin Csáky de Körösszeg et Adorján ( 19 April 1841 -- 15 December 1912 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as Minister of Religion and Education between 1888 and 1894 .
Dr. Levi Fox OBE , DL , MA , FSA , FRHistS , FRSL ( 28 August 1914 -- 3 September 2006 ) , was the son of a Leicestershire smallholder .
Mahmud Muhtar Pasha ( Turkish : Mahmut Muhtar Paşa ; 1867 -- 15 March 1935 ) , known as Mahmut Muhtar Katırcıoğlu after 1934 , was a Ottoman soldier and diplomat , and later a Turkish citizen , and the son of the grand vizier Veysel Pasha .
Gustav Otto ( 12 January 1883 -- 28 February 1926 ) was a German aircraft and aircraft - engine designer and manufacturer .
Drill Sergeant Mindstrong ( Brain Cadets in the PAL region ) is a military recruit training - themed party video game developed by Xseed Games for WiiWare .
Pathway to Glory is a tactical turn - based game for the Nokia N - Gage , by Nokia and RedLynx , released in late 2004 .
Outlast is a first - person survival horror video game developed and published by Canadian video game developer Red Barrels .
Soltrio Solitaire is an Xbox Live Arcade title developed by Silver Creek Entertainment for the Xbox 360 , which is a bundle of 18 separate solitaire card games , which was released on May 16 , 2007 .
Sun Microsystems acquired MySQL AB in 2008 .
It was originally developed in the early 1970s by Stephen C. Johnson at AT&T Corporation and written in the B programming language , but soon rewritten in C. It appeared as part of Version 3 Unix , and a full description of Yacc was published in 1975 .
Monster Truck Madness is a racing video game developed by Terminal Reality and published by Microsoft for Windows 95 .
The King of Fighters XI is a 2D competitive fighting game produced by SNK Playmore originally released in 2005 as a coin - operated arcade game for the Atomiswave platform .
Graham Gooch 's Test Cricket is a 1985 cricket game released for the Acorn Electron , BBC Micro , Commodore 64 and ZX Spectrum by Audiogenic .
Logitech Media Server ( formerly SlimServer , SqueezeCenter and Squeezebox Server ) is a streaming audio server supported by Logitech ( formerly Slim Devices ) , developed in particular to support their Squeezebox range of digital audio receivers .
High Performance Storage System ( HPSS ) is a flexible , scalable , policy - based Hierarchical Storage Management product developed by IBM in collaboration with various DOE National Labs .
Swingerz Golf ( Ace Golf in Europe and Wai Wai Golf ( わいわいゴルフ Wai Wai Gorufu , `` Wai Wai Golf '' ) in Japan ) is a sports video game released by Telenet Japan in 2002 .
Air Gallet , released in Japan as Akuu Gallet ( アクウギャレット ) is a vertically scrolling shoot 'em up arcade game developed by Gazelle ( one of the offshoots of Toaplan ) and released by Banpresto in 1996 .
Chopper Command is a video game by Activision released for the Atari 2600 in June 1982 .
Dragon Empires was a fantasy massively multiplayer online role - playing game developed by UK - based Codemasters .
Polarium Advance was developed by Mitchell Corporation for the Game Boy Advance .
Space Hawk is a video game released by Mattel for its Intellivision video game system in 1981 .
Frogger ( フロッガー ) is a 1981 arcade game developed by Konami and licensed for North American distribution by Sega - Gremlin and worldwide by Sega itself .
Adobe Photoshop is a raster graphics editor developed and published by Adobe Systems for Windows and OS X. Photoshop was created in 1988 by Thomas and John Knoll .
Mount & Blade is a medieval action role - playing game for Microsoft Windows , developed by the Turkish company TaleWorlds , and published by the Swedish company Paradox Interactive .
Earth Defense Force 2017 , known in Japan as Chikyû Boueigun 3 ( 地球防衛軍3 , lit . `` Earth Defence Force 3 '' ) is a third - person shooter developed by Sandlot , and published by D3 Publisher , for the Xbox 360 .
SUPER - UX , sometimes also annotated SuperUx or Super - UX , is the version of the Unix operating system that is used on NEC SX architecture supercomputers .
Fallout Shelter is a free - to - play mobile simulation video game developed by Bethesda Game Studios , with assistance by Behaviour Interactive , and published by Bethesda Softworks .
OGame was created in 2000 and is produced and maintained by Gameforge .
X - Squad ( X - Fire /Crossfire in Japan ) is a PlayStation 2 launch title developed by Electronic Arts Square and published by EA Games .
Marlow Briggs and the Mask of Death is an action - adventure hack and slash video game developed by Microsoft Studios and ZootFly for the Xbox 360 and Microsoft Windows .
AV-8B Harrier Assault is a combat flight simulator / realtime strategy game developed by Simis and first published by Domark in 1992 .
Shadow Madness is a turn - based RPG and the first video game released by Crave Entertainment .
Arcade Hoops Basketball ( also called Arcade Hoops ) is a basketball video game developed and published by Skyworks Interactive .
STM32 is a family of 32-bit microcontroller integrated circuits by STMicroelectronics .
Bit . Trip Beat , marketed as BIT.TRIP BEAT , is an arcade - style music video game developed by Gaijin Games and published by Aksys Games for the Wii 's WiiWare download service .
NHL 2K11 is an ice hockey video game , developed by Visual Concepts and published by 2 K Sports .
Halo 2 is a 2004 first - person shooter video game developed by Bungie Studios .
Baldur 's Gate is a fantasy role - playing video game developed by BioWare and published in 1998 by Interplay Entertainment .
F.E.A.R. Perseus Mandate is a stand - alone expansion pack for the psychological horror first - person shooter video game F.E.A.R. The expansion was developed by TimeGate Studios , the same development team behind the first expansion , F.E.A.R. Extraction Point .
Soul Blazer , known in Japan as Soul Blader ( ソウルブレイダー Sōru Bureidā ) , is an action role - playing game for the Super NES developed by Quintet and published by Enix ( now Square Enix ) .
The High - Level Shader Language or High - Level Shading Language ( HLSL ) is a proprietary shading language developed by Microsoft for the Direct3D 9 API to augment the shader assembly language , and went on to become the required shading language for the unified shader model of Direct3D 10 and higher .
Alter Echo is a third - person action - adventure video game developed by Outrage Entertainment and published by THQ .
Ambermoon is a 1993 video game by Thalion Software which was released in 1993 for the Amiga .
Rival Turf ! , released in Japan as Rushing Beat ( Japanese : ラッシング・ビート ) , is a beat'em up video game that was released by Jaleco in 1992 for the Super Nintendo Entertainment System and later on Nintendo 's Virtual Console .
JDeveloper is a freeware IDE supplied by Oracle Corporation .
Emergency Heroes is a mission - based driving game developed by Ubisoft Reflections and Ubisoft Barcelona and published by Ubisoft .
GT Advance Championship Racing ( known as Advance GTA in Japan ) is a racing game developed by MTO and published by THQ .
Epic Mickey is a platform video game designed by Warren Spector and developed by Junction Point Studios for the Wii console .
Fury3 ( also known as : Fury³ ; full name : Microsoft Fury3 ) is a simulation video game developed by Terminal Reality and published by Microsoft Game Studios for Windows 95 .
Virtual Bart is a video game developed by Sculptured Software and published by Acclaim .
Maziacs , written by Don Priestley , was based on his earlier ZX81 game Mazogs which was published by Bug Byte in 1982 .
Dashin ' Desperadoes is a platform game by Data East for the Sega Genesis released in 1993 .
UEFA Challenge is a football video game for PlayStation , PlayStation 2 and Microsoft Windows , developed and published by Infogrames Entertainment in 2001 .
Hidden Expedition is a series of ten hidden object casual games developed by the internal studios of Big Fish Games for the first five installments , and by Eipix Entertainment for all subsequent installments .
The SIL Open Font License ( or OFL in short ) is a free and open source license designed for fonts by SIL International for use with many of their Unicode fonts , including Gentium Plus , Charis SIL , and Andika .
Open Kart is a racing video game released in 2001 , developed and published by Microïds .
Windows 2.0 is a 16-bit Microsoft Windows GUI - based operating environment that was released on December 9 , 1987 , and is the successor to Windows 1.0 .
Un peu de soleil dans l'eau froide , internationally released as A Few Hours of Sunlight and A Little Sun in Cold Water , is a 1971 French film directed Jacques Deray adapted from the novel of Françoise Sagan .
Il sindacalista ( The Trade Unionist ) is a 1972 Italian comedy film directed by Luciano Salce .
Il richiamo nella tempesta ( i.e. `` Call in the storm '' , also known as Gli amanti dell'infinito and ... E le stelle non attesero invano ) is a 1950 Italian melodrama - fantasy film written and directed by Oreste Palella .

Soft and Hard is a video piece created by Jean - Luc Godard and Anne - Marie Miéville in 1985 .
His Last Dollar is a 1914 American comedy silent film directed by Frank Powell and written by David Higgins .

Greetings Bait ( 1943 ) is a seven - minute Academy Award - nominated Merrie Melodies cartoon , directed by Friz Freleng .
Little Fish , Strange Pond ( alternate title : Frenemy ) is a 2009 direct - to - DVD indie film directed by Gregory Dark and written by Robert Dean Klein .

The Germany Foundation ( German : Deutschland - Stiftung ) was a German organisation associated with the Christian Democratic Union and Christian Social Union , that existed from 1966 to 2007 .

The Prince - Bishopric of Paderborn ( German : Fürstbistum Paderborn ) was a principality ( Hochstift ) of the Holy Roman Empire from 1281 to 1802 .
In 1995 , the Rank Group acquired all the outstanding shares of the Rank Organisation .
Portuguese Guinea ( Portuguese : Guiné ) , called the Overseas Province of Guinea from 1951 , was a West African colony of Portugal from the late 15th century until 10 September 1974 , when it gained independence as Guinea - Bissau .
The British Eastern Fleet ( also known after 1944 as the East Indies Fleet and the Far East Fleet ) was a fleet of the Royal Navy which existed between 1941 and 1971 .
Transcontinental Air Transport ( T - A - T ) was an airline founded in 1928 by Clement Melville Keys that merged in 1930 with Western Air Express to form what became TWA .
It was purchased by BMW in 1966 , mainly to gain access to Glas 's patents , they were the first to use a timing belt with an overhead camshaft in an automotive application , with its limited model range shortly phased out by its new parent .
The Emirate of Sicily was an Islamic state ( emirate ) on the island of Sicily which existed from 831 to 1072 .
The Kingdom of Slavonia ( Croatian : Kraljevina Slavonija ; German : Königreich Slawonien ; Latin : Regnum Sclavoniae ; Hungarian : Szlavón Királyság ) was a province of the Habsburg Monarchy and the Austrian Empire that existed from 1699 to 1868 .

The Taifa of Arjona was a medieval Islamic taifa kingdom of Al - Andalus that ruled from 1232 to 1244 .
The Irish Republican Brotherhood ( IRB ; Irish : Bráithreachas Phoblacht na hÉireann ) was a secret oath - bound fraternal organisation dedicated to the establishment of an `` independent democratic republic '' in Ireland between 1858 and 1924 .
The Khilji dynasty ( Persian : سلسله خلجی‎‎ ; Hindi : सलतनत ख़िलजी ) or Khalji was a Muslim dynasty of Turkic origin , which ruled large parts of South Asia between 1290 and 1320 .
By 1018 , the last Bulgarian strongholds had surrendered to the Byzantine Empire , and the First Bulgarian Empire had ceased to exist .

Areshsky Uyezd ( Russian : Арешский уезд ) was one of the uyezds ( administrative units ) of Elisabethpol Governorate of the Russian Empire and then of Azerbaijan Democratic Republic with its center in Agdash from 1874 until its formal abolition in 1929 by Soviet authorities .

Marti G. Subrahmanyam is the Charles E. Merrill Professor of Finance at the Stern School of Business at New York University .

William Guy Banister ( March 7 , 1901 -- June 6 , 1964 ) was an employee of the Federal Bureau of Investigation , an Assistant Superintendent of the New Orleans Police Department , and a private investigator .

MetaDesign is an international design consultancy known for branding and brand strategy , founded by Erik Spiekermann , Uli Mayer - Johanssen and Hans Ch . Krüger .

The Asia Society was founded in 1956 by John D. Rockefeller III . Friedrich Wilhelm Ernst Hardt ( 9 May 1876 -- 3 January 1947 ) , born Ernst Stöckhardt , was a German playwright , poet , and novelist .
Enrico Giusti ( born Priverno , 1940 ) , is an Italian mathematician mainly known for his contributions to the fields of calculus of variations , regularity theory of partial differential equations , minimal surfaces and history of mathematics .
Pierre Prévost ( French : ( pʁevo ) ; 3 March 1751 -- 8 April 1839 ) was a Genevan philosopher and physicist .
Leopold Sonnemann ( 29 October 1831 -- 30 October 1909 ) was a journalist , newspaper publisher , and political party leader in Germany during the periods of the North German Confederation and the German Empire .

Jacques Boyvin ( c. 1649 -- 30 June 1706 ) was a French Baroque composer and organist .

Alfred Wiener ( 16 March 1885 , Potsdam -- 4 February 1964 , London ) was a German Jew , who dedicated much of his life to documenting antisemitism and racism in Germany and Europe , and uncovering crimes of Germany 's Nazi government .
Sir Robert Loder , 1st Baronet , DL , JP ( 7 August 1823-May 1888 ) was an English landowner , magistrate and Conservative politician .
Smbat Shahaziz ( Armenian : Սմբատ Շահազիզ , 1840 , Ashtarak , Armenia - January 5 , 1908 , Moscow , Russia ) was an Armenian educator , poet and publicist .
Karol Mikuli , often seen as Charles Mikuli ( Armenian : Կարոլ Միկուլի or Կարոլ Պստիկյան ; 20 October 1819 -- 21 May 1897 ) was an Polish pianist , composer , conductor and teacher .
Franz Ernst Neumann ( September 11 , 1798 -- May 23 , 1895 ) was a German mineralogist , physicist and mathematician .
Luis María Balanzat de Orvay y Briones ( 1775 - -1843 ) was a Spanish military man , engineer and writer .
Edoardo Zavattari ( 21 October 1883 , Tortona -- 17 February 1972 ) was an Italian zoologist who was a director at the Institute of Zoology in the Sapienza University of Rome from 1935 to 1953 .
Pierre Jacques Antoine Béchamp ( October 16 , 1816 -- April 15 , 1908 ) sometimes writing under M. A. Bechamp , was a French chemist and biologist now best known as a rival of Louis Pasteur .
Arghiri Emmanuel ( Greek : Αργύρης Εμμανουήλ ; June 22 , 1911 , Patras , Greece -- December 14 , 2001 , Paris , France ) was a Greek - French Marxian economist who became known in the 1960s and 1970s for his theory of ' unequal exchange ' .
James Whitbread Lee Glaisher FRS FRAS ( 5 November 1848 , Lewisham -- 7 December 1928 , Cambridge ) , son of James Glaisher , the meteorologist , was a prolific English mathematician and astronomer .
Rafael Torres Campos ( 1853 - -1904 ) was one of the most important Spanish geographers at the end of the nineteenth century .
Angelo Maria Cicolani ( 4 April 1952 -- 27 October 2012 ) was an Italian politician .
Sayantika Banerjee is an Indian Bengali language film actress .
Edward Falkener ( 1814 - -1896 ) was an English architect and author .
Jean Béraud ( French : ( beʁo ) ; January 12 , 1849 -- October 4 , 1935 ) was a French painter , noted for his paintings of Parisian life during the Belle Époque .
Jacques Nicolas Bellavène ( 20 October 1770 , in Verdun -- 8 February 1826 , in Milly ) was a French general .
Paul Rohrbach ( 29 June 1869 - 19 July 1956 ) was a German writer , concerned with `` world politics . ''
Barbara Skarga ( October 25 , 1919 -- September 18 , 2009 ) was a Polish philosophy historian and philosopher who worked mainly in ethics and epistemology .
Ignacio Velázquez Rivera ( born 1953 ) is a Spanish politician who served as mayor of Melilla from 1991 and became the first Mayor - President on 14 March 1995 when the enclave on the north coast of Africa became an autonomous community .
Friedrich Karl Dörner ( born February 28 , 1911 in Gelsenkirchen , died March 10 , 1992 ) was a German classics , epigrapher and Classical Archeologist .
Nathan Rotenstreich ( Hebrew : נתן רוטנשטרייך‎ ; born 31 March 1914 , died 11 October 1993 ) was an Israeli professor of philosophy .
Gergely Czuczor ( 17 December 1800 - 9 September 1866 ) was a Hungarians Benedictine monk , a poet and linguist , member of the Hungarian Academy of Sciences .
William Sherlock ( c. 1641 -- June 1707 ) was an English church leader .
Gottfried Wilhelm Sacer ( 11 July 1635 -- 8 September 1699 ) was a German jurist , poet , satirist and Protestant hymn writer .
Richard Milles ( c. 1735 -- 14 September 1820 ) was an English landowner , horticulturalist and Tory politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1761 to 1780 .
Henri Cernuschi ( Enrico Cernuschi in Italian ) ( February 19 , 1821 -- May 11 , 1896 ) , was a major French banker , economist and Asian art collector , who started off as an Italian politician in 1848 - 1850 .
Johann Philipp Palm or Johannes Philipp Palm ( 17 December 1768 - -26 August 1806 ) was a German bookseller executed during the Napoleonic Wars .
Francesco Ingoli ( 1578 - 1649 ) was an Italian priest , lawyer and professor of civil and canon law .
Manuel Prado y Colón de Carvajal ( 1931 - 5 December 2009 ) was a Spanish diplomat , businessman and politician .

Thomas Coningsby , 1st Earl Coningsby PC ( 2 November 1656 -- 1 May 1729 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times from 1679 until 1716 when he was created a peer and sat in the House of Lords

Karl Gunnar Harding ( born 11 June 1940 ) is a Swedish poet , novelist , essayist and translator , considered ' one of Sweden 's foremost poets ' .
Andrea Calmo ( 1510 in Venice -- 1571 ) was an Italian actor and author ( dramatist ) of Commedia dell'Arte , and one of the pioneers of this type of masked theater , as created for the 16th century Venetian audience .
Miles Pinkney ( 1599 - -1674 ) , alias Thomas Carre or Carr , was an English Catholic priest of the Old Chapter .

Ernst - Marcus Thomas ( born March 23 , 1973 ) is a German television host , radio DJ and journalist .

Jean - Camille Formigé ( 1845 - 1926 ) was a French architect during the French Third Republic .
Juliana Horatia Ewing ( née Gatty ) ( 3 August 1841 -- 13 May 1885 ) was an English writer of children 's stories .
Michel Wieviorka ( born 23 August 1946 , Paris ) is a French sociologist , noted for his work on violence , terrorism , racism , social movements and the theory of social change .
Leo Baeck ( 23 May 1873 -- 2 November 1956 ) was a 20th - century German rabbi , scholar and theologian .
The Abbé Claude Yvon ( 15 April 1714 -- November 1789 ) was a French encyclopédiste , a savant who contributed to the Encyclopédie edited by Denis Diderot and Jean le Rond d'Alembert .
Charles Higounet ( 13 January 1911 -- 8 April 1988 ) was a French historian medievalist , specialising in bastides and the Middle Ages in the southwest of France .
Roman Vlad ( 29 December 1919 -- 21 September 2013 ) was an Italian composer , pianist , and musicologist of Romanian birth .

Prasad Babu is a South Indian film actor , who acted in Telugu and Tamil films .

Henri Marie Ducrotay de Blainville ( 12 September 1777 -- 1 May 1850 ) was a French zoologist and anatomist .
Nicolas - Henri Tardieu , called the `` Tardieu the elder '' , ( 18 January 1674 - 27 January 1749 ) was a prominent French engraver , known for his sensitive reproductions of Antoine Watteau 's paintings .
Josep Maria Rañé ( born Barcelona , 15 June 1954 ) is a Catalan politician .
Élisabeth Platel is a French prima ballerina , born in Paris on 10 April 1959 .

Bruno Arpaia , born in Naples ( Italy ) in 1957 , is an Italian writer and journalist .
Benjamin Haskins - Stiles ( c.1684 - 1739 ) , of Bowden Park , near Chippenham , Wiltshire and Moor Park , Hertfordshire , was an English politician .
Maria - Pia Boëthius ( born 1947 ) is a Swedish journalist , novelist , non - fiction writer and activist .
William Edward Briggs ( 24 September 1847 -- 1903 ) was an English cotton manufacturer and a Liberal politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1874 to 1885 .
Faltonia Betitia Proba ( c. 306/c . 315 - c. 353/c . 366 ) was a Latin Roman Christian poet , possibly the most influential Latin poet of Late Antiquity .

Toshio Kimura ( 1909 -- 1983 ) was a Japanese politician who served as foreign minister for six months in 1974 .

Sirkka - Liisa Anttila ( born December 20 , 1943 , Marttila ) is a Finnish politician and was the Minister of Agriculture and Forestry in Matti Vanhanen 's second cabinet and Mari Kiviniemi 's cabinet .

Adriano Lualdi ( March 22 , 1885 - January 8 , 1971 ) Italian composer and conductor .

Paul Phélypeaux de Pontchartrain ( 1569 -- 21 October 1621 ) , lord of Pontchartrain and Villesavin , was a French statesman .

Sophie Dahl ( born Sophie Holloway ; 15 September 1977 ) is an English author and former fashion model .

Helen Beatrix Potter ( 28 July 1866 -- 22 December 1943 ) was an English author , illustrator , natural scientist , and conservationist best known for her children 's books featuring animals such as those in The Tale of Peter Rabbit .
Sandra Kalniete ( born 22 December 1952 ) is a Latvian politician , author , diplomat and independence movement leader .
Jean Laplanche ( French : ( laplɑ̃ʃ ) ; 21 June 1924 -- 6 May 2012 ) was a French author , psychoanalyst and winemaker .
Alexis Boyer ( March 1 , 1757 -- November 23 , 1833 ) was a French surgeon , born in Corrèze .
Reichsfreiherr and Reichsgraf Marshal Johann Matthias von der Schulenburg ( 8 August 1661 -- 14 March 1747 ) was a German aristocrat and general of Brandenburg - Prussian background who served in the Saxon and Venetian armies in the early 18th century and found a second career in retirement in Venice , as a grand collector and patron .
Ismar Elbogen ( September 1 , 1874 -- August 1 , 1943 ) was a Jewish - German rabbi , scholar and historian .
Barbara Rosiek ( born June 25 , 1959 in Częstochowa ) is a Polish writer , poet and clinical psychologist .

Oskar Bie ( 9 February 1864 -- 21 April 1938 ) was a German art historian and author of Jewish origin .

Nicolás de Cardona was a Spanish entrepreneur and adventurer with residence in Seville , who was involved in the exploration of the Western coast of the North American continent In 1610 , Nicolas sailed from Spain to the Americas , as a captain in the fleet of General Juan Gutiérrez de Garibay .

Eugen Grosche ( 11 March 1888 , in Leipzig -- 5 January 1964 ) , also known as Gregor A. Gregorius , was a German occultist and author .
Thomas Ruff ( born 10 February 1958 ) is a German photographer who lives and works in Düsseldorf , Germany .
