Capt . Levett Landon Boscawen Ibbetson was the father of Major Henry Levett Boscawen Ibbetson of the 77th ( East Middlesex ) Regiment of Foot of the British Army .
VP-8 served as a land - based anti - submarine patrol squadron in the Battle of the Atlantic during World War II . VP-8 also became the first operational P-3 Orion squadron in the United States Navy , occurring in October 1962 just prior to the Cuban Missile Crisis .
Admiral Sir Charles Ekins GCB ( 1768 -- 2 July 1855 ) was an officer of the Royal Navy who served in the Fourth Anglo - Dutch War , the French Revolutionary and Napoleonic Wars , and rose to the rank of admiral .
Captain Arnold J. Isbell , USN ( September 22 , 1899 -- March 19 , 1945 ) was a United States Navy officer and Naval Aviator who was killed near the end of World War II .
General William Nelson Hutchinson ( 1803 - -1895 ) was a British Army officer who became General Officer Commanding Western District .
Michael A. McAuliffe ( born 1941 ) was a Brigadier General in the United States Air Force .
Admiral Sir Astley Cooper Key GCB ADC FRS ( 18 January 1821 -- 3 March 1888 ) was a Royal Navy officer .
The 43rd ( Wessex ) Reconnaissance Regiment ( The Gloucestershire Regiment ) ( 43 Recce ) was a regiment of the British Army 's Reconnaissance Corps , itself part of the Royal Armoured Corps , during World War II . It fought in North West Europe with the 21st Army Group in 1944 - -1945 .
The Household Cavalry Mounted Regiment ( HCMR ) is a cavalry regiment of the British Army tasked primarily with ceremonial duties .
Cadwalader Ringgold ( 1802 - -1867 ) was an officer in the United States Navy who served in the United States Exploring Expedition , later headed an expedition to the Northwest and , after initially retiring , returned to service during the Civil War .
Charles Cochran Kirkpatrick ( June 20 , 1907 -- March 12 , 1988 ) was a rear admiral in the United States Navy who was Superintendent of the United States Naval Academy in Annapolis , Maryland from August 18 , 1962 to January 11 , 1964 .
Major General James G. Jones ( born 1934 ) is a retired United States Air Force general and former commander of the Keesler Technical Training Center , Keesler Air Force Base , Mississippi .
August Coppola was the son of composer and flutist Carmine Coppola ( 1910 - 1991 ) and Italia Coppola ( 1912 - 2004 ) , a lyricist and matriarch of the Coppola family .

Kaributas was born some time after 1350 ( exact date is unknown ) to Algirdas of Lithuania and Uliana of Tver .
Joan of Acre ( April 1272 -- 23 April 1307 ) was an English princess , a daughter of King Edward I of England and Queen Eleanor of Castile .

Born in Turin , Emanuel Filibert of Savoy was the third son of Charles Emmanuel I , Duke of Savoy and Infanta Catherine Michelle of Spain .
The Tudovka River ( Russian : река́ Тудовка ) is a river in Oleninsky , Nelidovsky , Selizharovsky , and Rzhevsky Districts of Tver Oblast of Russia , a right tributary of the Volga River .
Moloma River ( Russian : Моло́ма ) is a river in Kirov Oblast in Russia , an arm of the Vyatka River .
The Piscataquis River is a major tributary of the Penobscot River , found in Piscataquis County , Maine , United States .
La Grande River ( French : La Grande Rivière , Cree : Chisasibi , both meaning `` great river '' ) is a river in northwestern Quebec , Canada , which rises in the highlands of north central Quebec and flows roughly 900 kilometres ( 560 mi ) west to drain into James Bay .
Krutynia is a river of Masurian Lake District in Poland , a tributary of the Pisa .
The Sefīd - Rūd ( Persian : سفیدرود‎‎ , pronounced : ( sefiːdruːd ) , `` White River '' Azerbaijani : قزل اؤزؤن ) is a river approximately 670 kilometres ( 416 mi ) long , rising in northwestern Iran and flowing generally northeast to meet the Caspian Sea at Rasht .
The Tom River ( Russian : Томь ; IPA : ( tomʲ ) , Shor : Том ) is a river in Russia , a right tributary of the Ob River in Central Siberia .
The Lepenac ( Albanian : Lepenci ; Macedonian : Лепенец ; Serbian : Лепенац , Lepenac ) is a river in southern Kosovo and northern Macedonia , a 75 km ( 47 mi ) long left tributary to the Vardar river .
The Berowra Creek rises near Pennant Hills and flows generally north northeast before reaching its confluence with the Hawkesbury River about 7 kilometres ( 4.3 mi ) west of Brooklyn , and about 25 kilometres ( 16 mi ) from the Tasman Sea .
The Schwarze Laber is a river in Bavaria , Germany , and a left tributary of the Danube .
A Soxhlet extractor is a piece of laboratory apparatus invented in 1879 by Franz von Soxhlet .
In mathematics , Laplace 's equation is a second - order partial differential equation named after Pierre - Simon Laplace who first studied its properties .

The Descartes Prize is an annual award in science given by the European Union , named in honour of the French mathematician and philosopher , René Descartes .
Linus 's Law is a claim about software development , named in honor of Linus Torvalds and formulated by Eric S. Raymond in his essay and book The Cathedral and the Bazaar ( 1999 ) .
Koninklijk Horeca Nederland is the Dutch trade association for the hotel and catering industry .

Sarah Hopkins Bradford ( August 20 , 1818 -- June 25 , 1912 ) was an American writer and historian , best known today for her two pioneering biography books on Harriet Tubman .
Jean Fagan Yellin is an historian specializing in Women 's History and African - American History , and Distinguished Professor Emerita of English at Pace University .
György Surányi ( born January 3 , 1954 ) is Hungarian economist the CEO and chairman of CIB Bank and former president of the Hungarian National Bank between 1990 - -1991 and again in 1995 - 2001 .
Jeanne Selmersheim - Desgrange ( 1877 - -1958 ) was a French neo - impressionist painter who used the art technique of pointillism with her main themes of flowers and gardens .
Stanley Siegel , LCSW , is a psychotherapist , author , lecturer , and former Director of Education and Senior Faculty member of New York 's Ackerman Institute for Family Therapy .
Olivier Aurenche is a French archaeologist working in the prehistory of the Levant and Near East .
Freda Warrington is a British author , known for her epic fantasy , vampire and supernatural novels .
Gulyayev Dmitry Igorevich ( born January 22 in 1986 ) , better known by his stage name Dimal /dɪmʌl/ ( Russian : Димал ) , is a half - Russian , half - Ukrainian rapper , songwriter and entertainer based in Malta .
Leon Feingold ( born May 1 , 1973 ) is a baseball player from Oceanside , New York .
Mircea Grosaru ( June 30 , 1952 -- February 3 , 2014 ) was a Romanian politician , MP ( 2000 - -2014 ) , and jurist .
Olga Wisinger - Florian ( 1844 -- 1926 ) was an Austrian impressionist painter , mainly of landscapes and flower still lifes .
Halil Mete Soner is a Turkish mathematician born in Ankara .

Wang Shansheng ( Chinese : 王善生 ; born 1942 ) , is a Chinese painter , known predominantly for his works , depicting country life in China .

Buxus microphylla ( Japanese box or littleleaf box ) is a species of Buxus native to Japan and Taiwan .

The Ryukyu spiny rat ( Tokudaia osimensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Commerson 's dolphin ( Cephalorhynchus commersonii ) , also referred to by the common names skunk dolphin , piebald dolphin or panda dolphin , is a small oceanic dolphin of the genus Cephalorhynchus .
Olbitherium is an extinct mammal of the order Perissodactyla ( an early ancestor of modern - day horses , rhinos , and tapirs ) from the early Eocene epoch of Shangdong , China .
Forteyops is a trilobite in the order Phacopida , that existed during the lower Ordovician in what is now the United States .
The Nicodamidae are a spider family with 29 species in nine genera .
Arrhenophanidae is a family of moths in the Lepidoptera order .
Astata is a cosmopolitan genus of solitary predatory wasps in the subfamily Astatinae .
Tanea is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Naticidae , the moon snails or necklace shells .
Talazac 's shrew tenrec ( Microgale talazaci ) is a species of mammal in the family Tenrecidae .
The Eldon 's galaxias ( Galaxias eldoni ) is a galaxiid of the genus Galaxias , endemic to New Zealand .
Ecphora is the common name for a group of extinct predatory marine gastropod mollusks in the family Muricidae , the rocks snails or murexes .
Microspathodon is a genus of fish in the family Pomacentridae .
The Solomons boobook ( Ninox jacquinoti ) , also known as the Solomons hawk - owl , is a small to medium - sized hawk owl , measuring 23 - -31 cm ( 9.1 - -12.2 in ) in length .
Greater scissortail or Rasbora caudimaculata is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Rasbora .
Oxypselaphus is a genus of beetle in the family Carabidae , that contains the following species :
Steneofiber is among earliest known members of the subfamily Castorinae , which includes beavers more closely related to the two living species than to the recently extinct giant beaver .
The Ethiopian dwarf mongoose ( Helogale hirtula ) , also known as the desert dwarf mongoose or Somali dwarf mongoose , is a mongoose found in eastern Africa , particularly Ethiopia , Kenya , and Somalia .
Roche 's snake blenny ( Ophidion rochei ) is a fish species in the genus Ophidion and the family Ophidiidae .
Grewcock 's sportive lemur ( Lepilemur grewcockorum ) , or the Anjiamangirana sportive lemur , is a sportive lemur endemic to Madagascar .
Arthropodium is a genus of herbaceous perennial plants in the subfamily Lomandroideae of the family Asparagaceae .
The Ranongga white - eye or splendid white - eye ( Zosterops splendidus ) is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
Tanycyttara is a monotypic genus of Australian moths in the family Gelechiidae containing the sole species Tanycyttara xanthomochla , which is found in Australia , where it has been recorded from Queensland .
Poteria is a genus of tropical land snails with gills and an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Neocyclotidae .
Plakobranchus is a genus of sea slugs , sacoglossans , marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks in the family Plakobranchidae .
The Wallacean drongo or Greater Wallacean drongo ( Dicrurus densus ) is a species of bird in the Dicruridae family .
The Tibetan eared pheasant ( Crossoptilon harmani ) , also called Elwes ' eared pheasant , is a species of bird in the Phasianidae family .
Paulianites nidicola is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Paulianites .
The Norfolk kaka ( Nestor productus ) is an extinct species of large parrot , belonging to the parrot superfamily Strigopoidea .
Bechstein 's bat ( Myotis bechsteinii ) is a species of vesper bat found in Europe and western Asia , living in extensive areas of woodland .
Amblyjoppa is a genus of wasps belonging to the family Ichneumonidae .
The Karok hesperion also known as the Karok Indian snail , scientific name Vespericola karokorum , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Polygyridae .
The clade of Euarchontoglires and Laurasiatheria is recognized as Boreoeutheria .
Conosa is a grouping of Amoebozoa .
The De Winton 's shrew ( Chodsigoa hypsibius ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Zapater 's ringlet ( Erebia zapateri ) is a member of the Satyrinae subfamily of Nymphalidae . It is found only in the Montes Universales mountain range in central Spain , above 1300 m above sea level in open forests .
The Namaqua caco or Namaqua dainty frog ( Cacosternum namaquense ) is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family found in Namibia and South Africa .
The Red Sea bannerfish ( Heniochus intermedius ) is a Perciform fish which is found in waters around Africa and the Middle East .
Macleay 's dorcopsis ( Dorcopsulus macleayi ) , also known as the Papuan dorcopsis or the Papuan forest - wallaby , is a species of marsupial in the family Macropodidae .
Paramylodon is an extinct genus of ground sloth of the family Mylodontidae endemic to North America during the Pliocene through Pleistocene epochs , living from around ~4.9 Mya--11,000 years ago .
Xenosphingia is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing one species , Xenosphingia jansei , which is known from arid bush in western Zimbabwe and adjoining Botswana .
Pseudodipsas is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae with six species .
Commelina mosaic virus ( CoMV ) is a plant pathogenic virus in the genus Potyvirus and the virus family Potyviridae .
Platylesches is a genus of skippers in the family Hesperiidae , commonly called Hoppers , found in Africa .
The Luzon hornbill ( Penelopides manillae ) , sometimes called Luzon tarictic hornbill , is a species of hornbill in the Bucerotidae family .
The Moluccan goshawk or Halmaheran goshawk ( Accipiter henicogrammus ) is a species of bird of prey in the Accipitridae family .
The Christii fly ( Ectaetia christii ) is a fly species named after the late Iain Christie , a farmer and amateur entomologist from Dunbartonshire .
Euphonias were once considered members of the tanager family , Thraupidae .
The Far Eastern myotis or bombinus bat , ( Myotis bombinus ) , is a species of mouse - eared bat found in East Asia .
Eratigena is a genus of spider in the Agelenidae family .
Phoronopsis is a genus of horseshoe worm in the family Phoronidae , in the phylum Phoronida .
Ariophantidae is a taxonomic family of air - breathing land snails and semi - slugs , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Helicarionoidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Trigonostigma hengeli or Glowlight rasbora is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Trigonostigma .
Adapiformes is an extinct group of early primates .
Pebbled butterflyfish ( Chaetodon multicinctus ) are marine , perciform fish often found near reefs .
Dirca ( Leatherwood ) is a genus of three or four species of flowering plants in the family Thymelaeaceae , native to North America .
Pronotogrammus is a genus of colourful fishes in the subfamily Anthiinae .
Marley 's golden mole ( Amblysomus marleyi ) is a species of burrowing mammal in the golden mole family , Chrysochloridae .
The Taiwan tube - nosed bat ( Murina puta ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
Long - eared hedgehog ( Hemiechinus auritus ) Indian long - eared hedgehog ( Hemiechinus collaris )
Sigapatella is a genus of small to medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Calyptraeidae , the slipper snails , Chinese hat snails , and cup - and - saucer snails .
Ateliotum is a small genus of the fungus moth family , Tineidae .
Turiasorex is an extinct genus of shrew which existed in east central Spain , during the middle and late Miocene .
Decticus is a genus of bush - cricket in the family Tettigoniidae .
Setchelliogaster is a genus of fungi in the order Agaricales .
Nyctibatrachus kempholeyensis or the Kempholey night frog is a species of frog in the Nyctibatrachidae family .
The Australian blacktip shark ( Carcharhinus tilstoni ) is a species of requiem shark , in the family Carcharhinidae , endemic to northern and eastern Australia .
Tiphia is a genus of wasps belonging to the family Tiphiidae subfamily Tiphiinae .
Callobius is a spider genus in the family Amaurobiidae with 28 species that occur in North America and Eurasia .
Legler 's stream frog , Ptychohyla legleri , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Costa Rica and Panama .
Diphylleia is a group of small herbs in the Berberidaceae family described as a genus in 1803 .
Thyreochaetus hirsutus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Thyreochaetus .
The Cape clapper lark ( Mirafra apiata ) is a small passerine bird which breeds in southern Africa .
Ampittia is the genus of bush hoppers in the skipper butterfly family , Hesperiidae .
Xenentodon cancila ( F. Hamilton , 1822 ) ( Freshwater Garfish ) Xenentodon canciloides ( Bleeker , 1854 )
The Arabian bustard ( Ardeotis arabs ) is a species of bird in the bustard family .
Elaphe quadrivirgata , commonly known as the Japanese four - lined ratsnake or the Japanese striped snake ( Japanese : shimahebi = striped snake ) , is a species of nonvenomous colubrid snake native to Japan .
Metisella is a genus of skippers , commonly called sylphs , in the family Hesperiidae found in Africa .
Metapanax is a genus of flowering plant of family Araliaceae , comprising 2 species .
Cannaphila is a small Neotropical genus of dragonflies in the Libellulidae family .
Sibangea is a plant genus of the family Putranjivaceae , first described as a genus in 1883 .
The Tyrrhenian wall lizard ( Podarcis tiliguerta ) is a species of lizard in the Lacertidae family .
The Kalombo suckermouth ( Chiloglanis kalambo ) is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Tanzania where it occurs in the Kalambo River .
Colugos are fairly large for a tree - dwelling mammal : at about 35 to 40 cm ( 14 to 16 in ) in length and 1 to 2 kg ( 2.2 to 4.4 lb ) in weight , they are comparable to a medium - sized possum or a very large squirrel .
Geomyces is a genus of filamentous fungi in the family Myxotrichaceae .
The genus Halictus is a large assemblage of bee species in the family Halictidae .
The Clarión wren ( Troglodytes tanneri ) is a species of bird in the Troglodytidae family .
Ithomeis is a genus in the butterfly family Riodinidae present only in the Neotropical ecozone .
Chordeiles is a genus of nighthawks in the Caprimulgidae family .
Schistonchus is a plant - parasitic nematode genus in the family Aphelenchoididae .
Zamioculcadoideae is a subfamily of flowering plants in the Araceae family that consists of two genera , Zamioculcas and Gonatopus .
Euphrictus is a genus of tarantula ( family Theraphosidae ) which is found in Africa .
The Aholibah underwing ( Catocala aholibah ) is a moth of the `` owlet '' family Erebidae , which has over 25,000 known members , and more than that yet undescribed .
The Japanese butterfish ( Psenopsis anomala ) is a marine fish also known by such names as melon seed , wart perch , ibodai ( Japanese name , イボダイ ) or simply but ambiguously as butterfish .
Oxymormyrus is a small genus of elephantfish in the family Mormyridae .
Malpighiaceae Malpighiaceae - description , taxonomy , phylogeny , and nomenclature Malpighiodes Anderson , W. R. 2006 .
Phenacoceratidae is one of three families of the Dimeroceratoidea Superorder , a member of the Goniatitida order .
The São Tomé grosbeak was formerly placed in the genus Neospiza but was assigned to the genus Crithagra based on a phylogenetic analysis of mitochondrial and nuclear DNA sequences .
The Swainson 's crow ( Euploea swainson ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
Chalcothore is a genus of damselfly in family Polythoridae .
Bianchi 's warbler ( Seicercus valentini ) is a species of leaf warbler ( family Phylloscopidae ) .
The Kosrae crake or Kusaie Island crake ( Porzana monasa ) , sometimes also stated as Kittlitz 's rail , is an extinct bird from the family Rallidae .
Ammoselinum is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae , with 3 species known commonly as sandparsley .
In taxonomy , the Pycnococcaceae are a family of green algae , specifically of the Pseudoscourfieldiales .
Volema is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Melongenidae , the crown conches and their allies .
Drepaninae are by far the largest subfamily of the Drepanidae moths .
Centrolepis is a genus of small herbaceous plants in the family Centrolepidaceae known as thorn grass scales , with about 25 species native to Australia , New Zealand , New Guinea , and south - east Asia as far north as Hainan Dao .
The Alabama clubshell , scientific name Pleurobema troschelianum , was a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Aleocharini is the type tribe of the subfamily Aleocharinae .
Dorst 's cisticola ( Cisticola guinea ) , also known as the plaintive cisticola , is a bird in the family Cisticolidae .
Gilmania luteola ( called golden carpet or goldencarpet ) is a rare annual plant in the Buckwheat family ( Polygonaceae ) .
Horsfield 's bat ( Myotis horsfieldii ) is a species of vesper bat .
The Alabama lamp naiad , Alabama lamp pearly mussel , or Alabama lampmussel , scientific name Lampsilis virescens , is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Emperoptera is a genus of flightless flies in the Dolichopodidae family .
Plagiosauroidea is a superfamily of Temnospondyli that lived in the Triassic period .
Hodgsoniola is a genus of herbs in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae , first described as a genus in 1860 .
The Andaman horseshoe bat ( Rhinolophus cognatus ) is a species of bat in the family Rhinolophidae .
The La Gomera giant lizard ( Gallotia bravoana ; Spanish : Lagarto Gigante de la Gomera ) is a lacertid ( wall lizard ) species that can be found on the island of La Gomera , one of the Canary Islands .
Trachypteris picta is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Trachypteris .
Biomphalaria is a genus of air - breathing freshwater snails , aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails and their allies .
The American black duck ( Anas rubripes ) is a large dabbling duck .
The Chinese edible frog , East Asian bullfrog , or Taiwanese frog ( Hoplobatrachus rugulosus ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
Baturitia trispinosa is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
The Convex - vented horned toad , also Gelin spadefoot toad or Huang 's spadefoot toad ( Xenophrys pachyproctus ) is a species of amphibian in the Megophryidae family .
Eastern spadefoot toads ( Leptobrachium , also known as large - eyed litter frogs ) is a genus of the Megophryidae family in the order Anura , and are found in southern China , northeast India , Southeast Asia , and islands of the Sunda Shelf as well as the Philippines .
The Kurrichane thrush ( Turdus libonyana ) is a species of bird in the family Turdidae .
The Iraq babbler ( Turdoides altirostris ) is a species of bird in the Leiothrichidae family .
The Venezuelan yellow frog ( Atelopus carbonerensis ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae endemic to Venezuela .
The Dinagat gymnure ( Podogymnura aureospinula ) is a species of mammal in the family Erinaceidae .
Dentalion is a genus of Neotropical hymenopteran insects of the family Eulophidae .
Sarkastodon is an extinct genus within the family Oxyaenidae that lived during the upper Eocene , approximately 35 million years ago .
Sea spiders have long been considered to belong to the Chelicerata , together with horseshoe crabs , and the Arachnida , which includes spiders , mites , ticks , scorpions , and harvestmen , among other , lesser known orders .
Krattaspis is a trilobite in the order Phacopida ( family Cheiruridae ) , that existed during the lower Ordovician in what is now Estonia .
Rhytidosporum is a genus of flowering plants within the family Pittosporaceae .
Acridoidea is a superfamily of grasshoppers including locusts in the order Orthoptera .
Gould 's mouse ( Pseudomys gouldii ) lived in eastern inland Australia , and was named after John Gould .
The Mekong freshwater stingray , Dasyatis laosensis , is a species of stingray in the family Dasyatidae , restricted to the Mekong and Chao Phraya Rivers in Laos and Thailand ; the occurrence in Chao Phraya is considered an introduction .
The Tessmann 's flycatcher ( Muscicapa tessmanni ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
The California newt or orange - bellied newt , with scientific name Taricha torosa , is a newt species endemic to California , in the Western United States .
Plagioscion is a genus of hardheads , ray - finned fish in the family Sciaenidae .
The Aba roundleaf bat ( Hipposideros abae ) , also known as the Aba leaf - nosed bat is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
Steere 's spiny rat , Proechimys steerei , is a spiny rat species from South America .
The Australian ringneck ( Barnardius zonarius ) is a parrot native to Australia .
Opuntioideae is a subfamily of the cactus family , Cactaceae .
Nashia is a genus of flowering plants in the vervain family , Verbenaceae .
Loveridge 's tree frog , Myersiohyla loveridgei , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Venezuela .
Vallicula is a genus of Ctenophora in family Coeloplanidae , containing a single species , Vallicula multiformis .

Pyritis is a genus of hoverfly , from the family Syrphidae , in the order Diptera .
Chalarostylis is a genus of cumacean crustaceans in the family Lampropidae , containing two species , including the one formerly placed in Dasylamprops , which is now considered a synonym of Chalarostylis .
Adenostemma is a genus of flowering plant in the Asteraceae family described as a genus in 1775 .
Salvin 's spiny pocket mouse ( Liomys salvini ) is a small to medium - sized rodent .
Warburgia is a genus of plant in family Canellaceae described as a genus in 1895 .
Thamnocera is an genus of moths in the family Lymantriidae .
Notoclinops is the name of a genus of triplefins in the family Tripterygiidae .
Dryophthorinae is a weevil subfamily within the family Curculionidae .
The Chilean hawk ( Accipiter ( bicolor ) chilensis ) is a bird of prey species belonging to the typical hawks .
Pachypalpella is a genus of brown moth in the family Geometridae .
Sphaerostylis is a genus of plant of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1858 .
Weraroa is a genus of mushrooms in the Strophariaceae family .
Blepharistemma serratum is a species of plant in the family Rhizophoraceae , and the only species of its genus .
Stenogobius polyzona , the Chinestripe goby , is a species of goby native to streams and rivers on Madagascar and Réunion .
Russelia is a genus of flowering plants in the plantain family , Plantaginaceae .
The Angolan lark ( Mirafra angolensis ) is a species of lark in the Alaudidae family .

The Titan beetle ( Titanus giganteus ) is a neotropical longhorn beetle , the only one in the genus Titanus , and the second - largest known beetle .

Myriacantherpestes differs from other members of Euphoberiidae in part by having much longer lateral spines .
The Panay forest frog ( Platymantis panayensis ) is a species of frog in the Ceratobatrachidae family .
Chazyoceras ( `` Horn of the Chazyan '' ) is a moderately large endocerid included in the Endoceratidae with a Nanno type apex and a ventral siphuncle with a holochoanitic ( where `` holo '' is entire , and `` choan '' refers to its funnel - shaped opening ) wall , characteristic of the family .
Ellenbeckia is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , consisting of one species Ellenbeckia monospila , which is known from arid areas in Kenya and Somalia .
The Portuguese oyster , Crassostrea angulata , is a species of oyster found in the southwest Iberian Peninsula , closely related to the Pacific oyster .
The Sumatran puddle frog ( Occidozyga sumatrana ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
Hydrocleys is a genus of aquatic plants in the Alismataceae , native to the Western Hemisphere , though one is naturalized elsewhere and sold as an ornamental for decorative ponds and artificial aquatic habitats .
Ceriops is a genus of mangroves in family Rhizophoraceae .
The Peruvian treehunter or buff - throated treehunter ( Thripadectes scrutator ) is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family .

Permoceras , the sole member of the Permoceratidae , is a coiled nautiloid with a smooth , compressed involute shell , whorls higher than wide , earlier whorls hidden from view .

The Isabela oriole ( Oriolus isabellae ) is an endemic species of the oriole family found on Luzon in the Philippines .

The Flores woolly bat ( Kerivoula flora ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
Pseudectatomma is an extinct genus of ants in the formicid subfamily Ectatomminae described by from fossils found in Europe .
Henricia is a large genus of slender - armed sea stars belonging to the family Echinasteridae .

Undopterix is an extinct genus of moths within the family Eolepidopterigidae , containing two species .
Buccinum is a genus of medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
The Yangochiroptera , or Vespertilioniformes , is a proposed suborder of Chiroptera that includes most of the microbat families , except the Rhinopomatidae , Rhinolophidae , Hipposideridae and the Megadermatidae .
Kaempfer 's tody - tyrant ( Hemitriccus kaempferi ) is a rare species of bird in the family Tyrannidae .
Myiotrixa is a genus of tachinid flies in the family Tachinidae from Western Australia .

The New Zealand black angelfish or the black scalyfin , Parma alboscapularis , is a damselfish of the family Pomacentridae , found around northeastern New Zealand to depths of a few metres , over shallow rocky reef areas .

The Java razorfish ( Xyrichtys javanicus ) is a doubtful species of wrasse about which little is known .

Beccari 's free - tailed bat or Beccari 's mastiff bat ( Mormopterus beccarii ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae , the free - tailed bats .

Tisona is a monotypic genus of butterflies in the family Nymphalidae that contains the species Tisona saladillensis found in South America .
The Bantam caecilian , Ichthyophis hypocyaneus , is a species of amphibian in the Ichthyophiidae family .

Araneites is a genus belonging to the Sporadoceratinae subfamily of the Prionoceratidae family , a member of the Goniatitida order .
Weymer 's crow ( Euploea latifasciata ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly , endemic to Indonesia .

Welwitsch 's bat ( Myotis welwitschii ) is a species of vesper bat native to Africa .
Cyclocoeloma is a genus of crabs in the family Majidae , containing the single species Cyclocoeloma tuberculata .
Hexaplex is a genus of medium - sized to large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Muricidae , the murex shells or rock snails .
Gemmula , common name the gem turrids , is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Turridae , the turrids .

The Brazilian batfish or Seadevil , Ogcocephalus vespertilio , is a species of batfish .
Ambrosiella is a genus of ambrosia fungi within the Ceratocystidaceae family .
Bakoa is a genus of plants in the Araceae It has three known species , all endemic to the Island of Borneo .
The Rubeho warbler ( Scepomycter rubehoensis ) is a threatened species of bird in the Cisticolidae family .
The Ethiopian siskin or Abyssinian siskin ( Serinus nigriceps ) is a species of finch in the Fringillidae family .
Muticaria is a genus of small , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Clausiliidae , the door snails , all of which have a clausilium .
The docks and sorrels , genus Rumex L. , are a genus of about 200 species of annual , biennial and perennial herbs in the buckwheat family Polygonaceae .
It differs from Cartonema , however , in having raphides , which all other members of the Commelinaceae have , although they occur in a unique position next to the leaf veins in Triceratella .
Neritopsidae is a family of small sea snails and freshwater snails in the clade Cycloneritimorpha ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Borhyaenidae is an extinct metatherian family of low - slung , heavily built predatory mammals in the order Sparassodonta .
The Tortonese 's stingray ( Dasyatis tortonesei ) is a species of stingray in the family Dasyatidae , endemic to the Mediterranean Sea .
Semidelitschia is a genus of coprophilous fungi in the family Delitschiaceae that contains three species .
Garcinia is a plant genus of the family Clusiaceae native to Asia , Australia , tropical and southern Africa , and Polynesia .
Coloborhynchus is a genus in the pterosaur family Ornithocheiridae , and is known from the Lower Cretaceous of England ( Albian age , 98 million years ago ) , and possibly the Aptian age ( 112 - 99 million years ago ) of Brazil and Texas , depending on which species are included .
Phalanta is a genus of butterflies , called leopards , in the family Nymphalidae .
Basidiomycota ( /bəˌsɪdi.oʊmaɪˈkoʊtə/ ) is one of two large phyla that , together with the Ascomycota , constitute the subkingdom Dikarya ( often referred to as the `` higher fungi '' ) within the kingdom Fungi .
Scolopia is an Old World genus of plants in family Salicaceae .
The Indian cormorant or Indian shag ( Phalacrocorax fuscicollis ) is a member of the cormorant family .
Polystachyinae is a subtribe within the tribe Vandeae in family Orchidaceae .
Claytonia ( spring beauty ) is a genus of 26 species of flowering plants in the family Montiaceae , primarily native to North America , with a few species extending south to Guatemala in Central America , and northwest to northeastern Asia .
Catasetum , abbreviated as Ctsm in horticultural trade , is a genus of showy epiphytic Orchids , family ( Orchidaceae ) , subfamily Epidendroideae , tribe Cymbidieae , subtribe Catasetinae , with 166 species , many of which are highly prized in horticulture .
Coot fossils from the Middle Pleistocene of California have been described as Fulica hesterna but can not be separated from the present - day American coot .
Varnia is a small genus of moth lacewings , in the family Ithonidae .
Carnaby 's black cockatoo ( Calyptorhynchus latirostris ) , also known as Carnaby 's cockatoo or short - billed black cockatoo , is a large black cockatoo endemic to south - western Australia .
The Neomphalidae was removed from the subclass Eogastropoda where it was the only family in the superfamily Neomphaloidea McLean , 1981 and order Neomphalida ( McLean , 1981 ) .
Septidelphis is an extinct genus of oceanic dolphins belonging to the family family ( Delphinidae ) .
Lepyrotica is a genus of insect , belonging to the family Tineidae .
Diplosolenodes is a genus of air - breathing land slugs , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Veronicellidae , the leatherleaf slugs .
The Caracas tapaculo ( Scytalopus caracae ) is a species of bird in the Rhinocryptidae family .
The Loxsomataceae are a family of ferns in the order Cyatheales .
Mastiphanes was a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family .
The Aeolian wall lizard ( Podarcis raffonei ) is a species of lizard in the Lacertidae family .
The Easter Island butterflyfish or white - tip butterflyfish ( Chaetodon litus ) is a species of subtropical fish in the family Chaetodontidae .
The American pickerels are two subspecies of Esox americanus , a species of freshwater fish in the pike family ( family Esocidae ) of order Esociformes : the redfin pickerel , E. americanus americanus Gmelin , 1789 , and the grass pickerel , E. americanus vermiculatus Lesueur , 1846 .
Acacieae is a wide - ranging , polyphyletic tribe of legumes in the Mimosoideae , that is native to the tropics , subtropics and warm - temperate regions .
The Dicranidae are a widespread and diverse subclass of mosses in class Bryopsida , with many species of dry or disturbed areas .
The Cumberland bean pearly mussel , Cumberland bean , or purple bean ( Villosa trabalis ) is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae .
The Christmas white - eye ( Zosterops natalis ) is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
The Tenerife gecko or Tenerife wall gecko ( Tarentola delalandii ) is a species of lizard in the Gekkonidae family .
Amphistichus argenteus , the Barred surfperch , is a species of surfperch native to inshore waters from northern California , USA to southern Baja California , Mexico .
The Sumatran giant shrew ( Crocidura lepidura ) is a shrew of the genus Crocidura .
The Tennessee cave salamander ( Gyrinophilus palleucus ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae , endemic to the United States .
Panthera onca hernandesii ( Mearns , 1901 ) was proposed as a subspecies of jaguar , native to Mexico and the United States , before later research failed to find evidence for it .
Cook 's rattail , Coelorinchus cookianus , is a species of rattail found around New Zealand at depths of between 250 and 900 m. Its length is between 10 to 25 cm .
The Cordoba cinclodes or Comechingones cinclodes ( Cinclodes comechingonus ) is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family .
Chamaecyparis , common names cypress or false cypress ( to distinguish it from related cypresses ) , is a genus of conifers in the cypress family Cupressaceae , native to eastern Asia ( Japan + Taiwan ) and to the western and eastern margins of the United States .
Ifridytes mateui is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Ifridytes .
Rhytidocystidae is a family within the order Agamococcidiorida of the phylum Apicomplexa .
Xenosmilus hodsonae ( from Greek , ξένος , xenos , `` strange '' + σμίλη , smilē , `` chisel '' ) is an extinct member of the Machairodontinae , or saber - toothed cat .
Feral pigeons ( Columba livia domestica ) , also called city doves , city pigeons , or street pigeons , are derived from domestic pigeons that have returned to the wild .
The Tickell 's brown hornbill ( Anorrhinus tickelli ) , also known as the rusty - cheeked hornbill , is a species of hornbill found in forests in northeastern India , Burma and adjacent western Thailand .
The Cairns rainbowfish ( Cairnsichthys rhombosomoides ) is a species of rainbowfish endemic to Australia .
The Atitlán grebe ( Podilymbus gigas ) , also known as giant grebe , giant pied - billed grebe , or poc , is an extinct water bird , a relative of the pied - billed grebe .
The Papuan black myzomela ( Myzomela nigrita ) is a species of bird in the Meliphagidae family .
Paratropididae is a small spider family with eight species , known as baldlegged spiders .
Barbouria is a genus of shrimp in the family Barbouriidae , comprising two species .
The Guianan gnatcatcher ( Polioptila guianensis ) is a species of bird in the Polioptilidae family .
Tchapinius malaisei is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Phalangiidae .
Bean leaf roll virus ( BLRV ) is a plant pathogenic virus of the family Luteoviridae .
Catuana spinicornis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Catuana .
The Charazani tree frog , Hyloscirtus charazani , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Bolivia and possibly Peru .
The Bolivian blackbird ( Oreopsar bolivianus ) is a species of bird in the family Icteridae .
Pyranthrene is a genus of moths in the Sesiidae family containing only one species , Pyranthrene flammans , which is known from Malawi .
The genus Cunninghamia is a genus of one or two species of evergreen coniferous trees in the cypress family Cupressaceae .
The Gambian epauletted fruit bat ( Epomophorus gambianus ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .
The spider family Deinopidae consists of stick - like elongate spiders that build unusual webs that they suspend between the front legs .
The Cenarchaeaceae are a family of the Archaea order , the Cenarchaeales .
Pararistolochia is a genus of plant family Aristolochiaceae .
Hyophorbe is a genus of five known species of flowering plants in the Arecaceae family , native to the Mascarene Islands in the Indian Ocean .
The Colorado pikeminnow ( formerly squawfish ) Ptychocheilus lucius is the largest cyprinid fish of North America and one of the largest in the world , with reports of individuals up to 6 ft ( 1.8 m ) long and weighing over 100 pounds ( 45 kg ) .
Meliacanthus cupreomarginatus is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Meliacanthus .
Voatamalo is a plant genus in the family Picrodendraceae first described as a genus in 1976 .
Gurney 's eagle ( Aquila gurneyi ) is a large eagle in the family Accipitridae .
Human cytomegalovirus is a species of the Cytomegalovirus genus of viruses , which in turn is a member of the viral family known as Herpesviridae or herpesviruses .
The Mogollon mountain wolf ( Canis lupus mogollonensis ) is a possible subspecies of gray wolf whose range once included southern and western Texas and northeastern Mexico .
Toxicodendron vernicifluum ( formerly Rhus verniciflua ) , also known by the common name Chinese lacquer tree , is an Asian tree species of genus Toxicodendron ( formerly Rhus ) native to China and the Indian subcontinent , and cultivated in regions of China , Korea and Japan .
The Meliceae are a tribe of grasses near the base of the Pooideae .
The Asiatic rhinoceros beetle or coconut rhinoceros beetle , ( Oryctes rhinoceros ) is a species of rhinoceros beetle belonging to the Scarabaeidae family .
Crossochelys is an extinct genus of South American turtle from the family Meiolaniidae .
The Gallaceaceae are a family of fungi in the order Hysterangiales , containing species found in Australia and New Zealand .
Theba is a taxonomic genus of air - breathing land snails , medium - sized pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Helicidae , the true snails .
Korora oliveri , also referred to as Oliver 's penguin , is a genus and species of extinct penguin from the Waitakian Stage ( Late Oligocene to Early Miocene ) of New Zealand .
The Pepsinae are a subfamily of the spider wasp family , Pompilidae , including the tarantula hawks , as well as smaller species .
Within the Urticaceae , Myriocarpa is characterized by long pendulous string - like female inflorescences of apparently naked flowers and stems which release a watery latex when cut .
Amos Kash ( Russian : Амос Каш , 2 June 1868 ( OS)/15 June 1868 ( NS ) -- 4 December 1948 ) was a Russian sports shooter who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics .
Charly Grosskost ( 5 March 1944 -- 19 June 2004 ) was a French racing cyclist who in 1968 won the prologue time - trial of both the Giro d'Italia and the Tour de France .
Islam Bayramukov ( born June 12 , 1971 ) is a Kazakh wrestler who competed in the Men 's Freestyle 97 kg at the 2000 Summer Olympics and won the silver medal .
Georges Aeby ( 21 September 1913 -- 15 December 1999 ) was a Swiss footballer who played for Switzerland in the 1938 FIFA World Cup .
Les Perry ( Leslie John Perry ; 29 January 1923 -- 17 September 2005 ) was an Australian long - distance runner who competed in the 1952 Summer Olympics and in the 1956 Summer Olympics .
Natalya Zasulskaya ( born 28 May 1969 in Kaunas , Lithuanian SSR ) is a Russian former basketball player who competed in the 1988 Summer Olympics , in the 1992 Summer Olympics , and in the 2000 Summer Olympics .
The Quietly Confident Quartet was the self - given name of the Australian men 's 4 × 100 m medley relay swimming team that won the gold medal at the 1980 Summer Olympics in Moscow .
Marcos Rivera ( born 20 April 1983 ) is a Spanish former swimmer who competed in the 2004 Summer Olympics and in the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Valéria Gyenge ( born 3 April 1933 ) is a Hungarian swimmer who won the 400 m freestyle event at the 1952 Summer Olympics .
Tibor Cservenyák ( born 8 August 1948 in Szolnok ) is a Hungarian former water polo player who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics and in the 1976 Summer Olympics .
The Silent Generation is the debut album by The Dimes , released on December 11 , 2007 via the label , Timber Carnival Records .
`` One Dream '' is a Korean - language song performed by South Korean pop singer BoA.
`` Starless '' is a piece by British progressive rock band King Crimson .
Solo un grande sasso is the second album by the Italian alternative - rock band Verdena , released in 2001 .

Ilona Eibenschütz ( 8 May 1872 in Budapest , Hungary -- 21 May 1967 in London , England ) was a Hungarian pianist .
Matteo di Cione ( 1330 - -1380 ) was an Italian sculptor , notable for being the brother of three of the great painters of Gothic Florence , Nardo di Cione , Jacopo di Cione and Andrea di Cione .
In 1922 , Ove Arup began work with a Danish firm in Hamburg called Christiani & Nielsen , and in December 1923 he moved to their London office as chief engineer .
Sir Walter Fraser Oakeshott FBA ( 11 November 1903 -- 13 October 1987 ) was a schoolmaster and academic , who was Vice - Chancellor of the University of Oxford .

Megalagrion jugorum is an extinct species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae that was endemic to the island of Maui in Hawaii .
Voluta virescens , common name the green music volute , is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Amanita eliae is an inedible species of fungi in the family of Amanitaceae found in Europe .
Potamon is a genus of freshwater or semi - terrestrial crabs mainly found from Southern Europe through the Middle East , and as far east as north - western India .
Lindapterys is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Garthasia americana is a species of crabs in the family Xanthidae , the only species in the genus Garthasia .
Lotus oblongifolius is a species of legume known by the common name streambank bird's - foot trefoil .
The Saccharomycetales are an order in the kingdom of fungi that comprises the budding yeasts and includes 15 families .
Nebria heegeri is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Chornagora , and Gorgany Mountains of Ukraine .
Leptolepidae ( `` Delicate Scales '' ) is an extinct family of herring - like Mesozoic teleosts found throughout the world .
Dicranopteris linearis is a common species of fern known by many common names , including Old World forked fern , uluhe ( Hawaiian ) , and dilim ( Filipino ) .
Xerocrassa rhithymna is a species of air - breathing land snail , a pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae .
Orthotylus obscurus is a species of bug in the Miridae family that is can be found in Austria , Bulgaria , Croatia , France , Germany , Italy , Romania , Switzerland , Sweden , and European part of Turkey .
Vertigo bollesiana , common name the delicate vertigo snail , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Vertiginidae , the whorl snails .
Tonestus graniticus , common names granite serpentweed and Lone Mountain serpentweed , is a rare endemic plant species known only from the east side of Lone Mountain in Esmeralda County , Nevada , about 20 km ( 12.5 miles ) west of Tonopah .
Microchrysa cyaneiventris , the black gem , is a European species of soldier fly .
Rawsonia reticulata is a species of plant in the Achariaceae family .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Leprieuria bacillum .

Agamyxis is a genus of thorny catfishes .

Pseudomugil tenellus , commonly known as the delicate blue - eye , is a species of fish in the family Pseudomugilidae .
Stefania marahuaquensis ( Spanish : rana stefania del Marahuaka ) is a species of frog in the family Hemiphractidae .
Allium lehmannii is a plant species endemic to southern Italy .
Rhomaleosaurus ( meaning `` strong lizard '' ) is an extinct genus of Early Jurassic ( Toarcian age , about 183 to 175.6 million years ago ) rhomaleosaurid pliosauroid known from Northamptonshire and from Yorkshire of the United Kingdom .
Diloxia belohalis is a species of snout moth in the genus Diloxia .
Gayophytum is a genus of annual herbs in the evening primrose family known commonly as groundsmoke .
Ningchengopterus is a genus of pterodactyloid pterosaur from the Early Cretaceous - age Yixian Formation of China .
Badhamia panicea is a species of slime mold in the family Physaraceae .

Blidingia marginata is a species of seaweed in the Ulvaceae family .
The Bradynobaenidae are a family of wasps similar to the Mutillidae .
Tatisaurus is a genus of ornithischian dinosaur from the Early Jurassic from the Lower Lufeng Formation in Yunnan Province in China .
Sagittaria longiloba is a species of flowering plant in the water plantain family known by the common name longbarb arrowhead and Gregg arrowhead .
Norelona pyrenaica is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Elonidae .

Hyperoptica ptilocentra is a moth in the Xyloryctidae family , and the only species in the genus Hyperoptica .
Raorchestes manipurensis or Leimatak 's bush frog is a species of frog of the genus Raorchestes found around the Tumzane river near Leimatak , Churachandpur district in the state of Manipur in India .

Bathyagonus is a genus of poachers ( bottom - dwelling cold - water marine fish ) native to the Pacific Ocean .

Ogcocephalus notatus , the oval batfish , is a species of batfish in the family Ogcocephalidae .

In taxonomy , Astrephomene is a genus of green algae , specifically of the Goniaceae .
Divales bipustulatus is a species of beetle belonging to the family Melyridae .

Hippidion ( meaning little horse ) is an extinct genus of horse that lived in South America during the Pleistocene epoch , between two million and 10,000 years ago .
Trichomycterus brachykechenos is a species of pencil catfish endemic to Brazil , where it occurs in the dos Sinos river , part of the Laguna dos Patos system , in the state of Rio Grande do Sul .

Missulena pruinosa , commonly known as the northern mouse spider , is a species of spider belonging to the family Actinopodidae native to Australia .

Bdellovibrio is a genus of Gram - negative , obligate aerobic bacteria .
Pterostylis metcalfei , commonly known as the large kinked greenhood orchid or Ebor greenhood is a species of orchid which is endemic to the Northern Tablelands of New South Wales .

Parectypodus ( `` beside Ectypodus '' ) is a genus of extinct mammal that lived from the Paleocene to the Eocene of North America .

Vanda tessellata is a species of orchid occurring from the Indian subcontinent to Indochina .

Fuyuansaurus is an extinct genus of long - snouted protorosaur reptile known from the Middle Triassic ( Ladinian stage ) Falang Formation of southern China .
Nesolagus is a genus of rabbits containing three species of striped rabbit , the Annamite Striped Rabbit , the Sumatran Striped Rabbit , and that of the extinct species `` sinensis '' .
Pheidole dodo ( named after the dodo , an extinct bird of Mauritius ) is a species of ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Cymbium pachyus , commonly known as the dilated baler volute is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Conandron is a genus that consists of 3 species of small ornamental alpine perennials , native to Japan and Taiwan .

The lone species , Actinorhytis calapparia , is a rain forest inhabitant and has the largest fruit of any palm in the Iguanurinae .

Steyskalomyza is a Monotypic genus of flies from the family Dryomyzidae .

Pneumocystis murina is a species of fungus , first isolated from lab mice , hence its name .
Alberada parabates is a species of snout moth in the genus Alberada .

It includes only the single species Geothallus tuberosus .
It is in the rose family ( Rosaceae ) , and is the only species in the monotypic genus Coleogyne .

Dactylopteryx flexuosa is a species of praying mantis in the genus Dactylopteryx in the order Mantodea .
Cerioidini is a widespread tribe of around 197 species of hoverfly .
Psydrax oleifolia , commonly known as Wild Lemon or Brush Myrtle , is a species of shrub or small tree in the Rubiaceae family .
Baileya multiradiata is a North American species of sun - loving wildflowers native to the deserts of northern Mexico and the Southwestern United States .
Uintatherium ( `` Beast of the Uinta Mountains '' ) is an extinct genus of herbivorous mammal that lived during the Eocene epoch ; two species are currently recognized , U. anceps from the United States during the Early to Middle Eocene , and U. insperatus of Middle to Late Eocene China .
Acantholycosa zinchenkoi is a species of wolf spider only known from the Katun Mountain Range in the southwestern Altai Mountains of Russia and Kazakhstan .
Phyllosticta manihotis is a plant pathogen originating from the Philippines that forms on the leaves of several cassava species like Manihot dichotoma , M. glaziovii and M. heterophylla .
Lobosculum pustula is a species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Polygyridae .
Oxychilus oglasicola is a species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Oxychilidae , a family of glass snails .
Alocolytoceratinae is a subfamily of lytoceratids that comprises genera characterized by many deep constrictions in the shell resulting in capricorn - like ( goat 's horm ) ornamention , especially in the middle whorls , but becoming smooth and more involute in the outer whorls .
Alvesia is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae , first described in 1869 .
Fiordichthys is a genus of viviparous brotula native to the southwest Pacific Ocean .
Senecio blochmaniae is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names dune ragwort and Blochman 's ragwort .
Megachile angelarum is a species of bee in the Megachilidae family .
Leucorchestris is a genus of huntsman spiders occurring in Namibia and Angola .
Choristhemis olivei , more commonly known as delicate tigertail , is a species of Odonata spanning from the family Corduliidae and the genus Choristhemis .
Magnirostris , from the Latin magnus `` large '' and rostrum `` beak '' , is the name given to a genus of dinosaur from the Late Campanian epoch in the Late Cretaceous .
Nostoc verrucosum is a species of cyanobacteria usually found in colonies and in globose racks .
Barbilophozia is a liverwort genus in the family Scapaniaceae .
Diuris pardina ( Leopard Orchid ) is a species of orchid which is endemic to Australia .
Sphaerolipoviridae is a family of double - stranded DNA viruses that infect thermophilic bacteria and halophilic archea , formally approved by the International Committee on Taxonomy of Viruses in 2015 .
The Pospiviroidae are a family of viroids , including the first viroid to be discovered , PSTVd .
Ahytherium is an extinct genus of megalonychid sloth found in Brazil .
Podocarpus costalis , locally known as Arius , is a species of conifer in the family Podocarpaceae .
Nundasuchus is an extinct genus of archosaur , possibly suchian , known from the Middle Triassic Manda beds of southwestern Tanzania .
Eotebenna is a genus of helcionellid from the Early to Middle Cambrian of Greenland , Denmark and Australia , with sail - like `` snorkels '' , similar to Latouchella .
Conotrachelus elegans , the pecan gall curculio , is a true weevil species in the genus Conotrachelus .
Meckelia confluens is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Meckelia of the family Tephritidae .
It contains the single species Hyperthagylla mira , which is found in the Amazon region and Costa Rica .
Microseris douglasii is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Douglas ' silverpuffs .
Fountainea nobilis , common name noble leafwing , is a species of Neotropical butterflies belonging to the Nymphalidae family , Charaxinae subfamily .
Beharus is a monotypic genus of assassin bugs belonging to the family Reduviidae .
Mohavea was a plant genus consisting of two species native to the deserts of the southwestern United States and northern Mexico .
Euonymus angulatus is a species of tree in the family Celastraceae .
Arenysaurus is a genus of hadrosaurid dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous ( 66 million years ago ) .
Nahida coenoides is the sole species in the monotypic genus Nahida in the butterfly family Riodinidae present only in the Neotropical ecozone .
Auchenipterichthys is a genus of driftwood catfishes found in South America .
Opuntia littoralis is a species of prickly pear cactus known by the common name coastal pricklypear .
Dicoelosia is an extinct genus of brachiopod that lived from the Late Ordovician to the Early Devonian in Asia , Australia , Europe , North America , and South America .
Salix eleagnos the bitter willow , olive willow , hoary willow , rosemary willow , or elaeagnus willow , is a species of flowering plant in the family Salicaceae , native to central and southern Europe and south west Asia .
Penicillium rugulosum is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which produces inulinase , luteoskyrin and ( + ) rugulosin .
Some treat Cupressus pigmaea as a distinct species , following Sargent , including Wolf ( 1948 ) , Griffin & Critchfield ( 1976 ) , Lanner ( 1999 ) , and Little et al .
Artedius corallinus or the Coralline sculpin is a species of intertidal sculpin in the family Cottidae .
Triviella aperta , common name the baby 's toes , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Triviidae , the false cowries or trivias .
Brachylophosaurini is a tribe of saurolophine hadrosaurs with known material being from N. America and potentially Asia .
Nannostomus marginatus , commonly known as the dwarf pencilfish , is a freshwater species of fish belonging to the genus Nannostomus in the Lebiasinidae family of characins .
Austroagrion cyane , the south - western billabongfly , is a species of damselfly commonly found in Australia .
Oecomys catherinae , also known as the Atlantic Forest oecomys , is a species of rodent in the genus Oecomys from eastern Brazil .
Lithraea caustica is a species of flowering plants in the soapberry family Anacardiaceae .
Mongolicosa songi is a species of wolf spider found in Xinjiang , China and adjacent areas of Mongolia .
Exelastis rhynchosiae is a species of moth in the genus Exelastis , known from Arkansas and Florida .
Poa chaixii ( known as Broad - leaved Meadow - grass or broadleaf bluegrass ) is a species of perennial grass native to Europe and temperate Asia .
Elaeocarpus cordifolius is a species of tree in the plant family Elaeocarpaceae .
Pandemis pyrusana , the apple pandemis or pandemis leafroller moth , is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae .
Conilurus capricornensis commonly known as Capricorn rabbit rat is an extinct species of rabbit rat ( Conilurus ) .
Heterakis is a genus of parasitic nematodes .
Sepia insignis is a species of cuttlefish native to the southwestern Indian Ocean , specifically South Africa , from the Cape of Good Hope to Natal .
Heterotheca stenophylla , called the Stiffleaf goldenaster , is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family .
Flabellina pellucida is a species of sea slug , an aeolid nudibranch , a marine heterobranch mollusc in the family Flabellinidae .
Aerides rosea is a species of epiphytic orchid .
Alocasia is a genus of broad - leaved rhizomatous or tuberous perennials from the family Araceae .
Nerita orbignyana is a species of sea snail with an operculum , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Neritidae , the nerites .
Alopecosa taeniopus is a wolf spider species in the genus Alopecosa found from Bulgaria to China .
Khorassania hartigi is a species of snout moth in the genus Khorassania .
Provelosaurus is an extinct Pareiasaur genus of the Late Permian found on the road between Aceguá and Bagé in the Paleorrota , Rio Grande do Sul , Brazil .
Heteroponera dentinodis is a species of ant in the genus Heteroponera , endemic to Chile and Brazil .
Pseudotropheus tursiops is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known from Chisumulu Island .
Homalictus singhalensis , also known as Lasioglossum ( Homalictus ) singhalensis , is a species of bees in the genus Homalictus , of the family Halictidae .
Selysiothemis nigra , the Black Pennant , is a monotypic species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Amaranthus blitum , commonly called purple amaranth or Guernsey pigweed , is an annual plant species in economically important plant family Amaranthaceae .
Cleome sparsifolia is a species of cleome known by the common names fewleaf cleome and fewleaf spiderflower .
Asplenium dimorphum ( Norfolk Island Spleenwort ) is a species of fern in the Aspleniaceae family , endemic to Norfolk Island .
Magnapinna talismani is a species of bigfin squid known only from a single damaged specimen .
Osmunda vachellii is a species of fern in the genus Osmunda , section Plenasium .
Aldisa albatrossae is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Cadlinidae .
Mertensia longiflora is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common names small bluebells and long bluebells .
Leucopaxillus giganteus , commonly known as the giant leucopax ( formerly as the giant clitocybe ) or the giant funnel , is a saprobic species of fungus in the Tricholomataceae family .
Psectrogaster is a genus of toothless characins from South America , with these currently described species :
The Thai Bamboo , ( Thyrsostachys siamensis ) , is one of two bamboo species belonging to the Thyrsostachys genus .
Turnix novaecaledoniae ( New Caledonian Buttonquail ) is a species of bird in the Turnicidae family .
Xinpusaurus is an extinct genus of thalattosaur from the Late Triassic of Guanling in Guizhou , China .
Bower 's white - toothed rat ( Berylmys bowersi ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Nemachilichthys rueppelli , also known as the Mongoose loach is a species of stone loach from rivers in India .
Pleurotus is a genus of gilled mushrooms which includes one of the most widely eaten mushrooms , P. ostreatus .
Rhinopetitia myersi is a species of characin endemic to Brazil , where it is found in the Rio Araguaia .
Fossilized remains of the single known genus Messelirrisor have been found in the Messel Pit ( Hesse , Germany ) .
Malaxis , commonly called Adder 's mouth , is a genus of terrestrial and semiepiphytic orchids .
Eokrefftia is an extinct genus of prehistoric ray - finned fish that lived during the Paleocene epoch .
It is the only species in the genus Avitelmessus and is known from finds in the southeastern United States .
The Cape clapper lark is a species of open grassland and savannah , also inhabiting karoo , fynbos and fallow agricultural land .
Nebria rhilensis is a species of beetle in the Carabidae family that is endemic to Rila , Bulgaria .
Cymbium glans , commonly known as the elephant 's snout volute , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Jujubinus striatus , common name the grooved top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Craugastor adamastus is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family endemic to Guatemala .
Eriogonum coloradense is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name Colorado buckwheat .
Emblemariopsis occidentalis , the Flagfin blenny , Blackfin blenny or the Redspine blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found around the Bahamas , Brazil , and the Lesser Antilles , in the western Atlantic ocean .
Nowakowskiella is the sole genus of fungi in the family Nowakowskiellaceae .
Skenea californica , common name the California skenea , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Skeneidae .
Lycoperdon radicatum is a species of puffball mushroom in the family Agaricaceae .
Gentiana plurisetosa is a rare species of gentian known by the common names Klamath gentian and bristly gentian .
Pterostylis stenochila is a species of orchid endemic to Tasmania .
Ephemerelloidea is a superfamily of mayflies in the suborder Pannota .
Eryx jayakari , known commonly as the Arabian sand boa or Jayakar 's sand boa , is a species of snake in the Boidae family .
The genus Muilla includes three to four species of flowering plants .
Gaura sinuata is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common names wavyleaf beeblossom and Red River gaura .
Sagdidae is a family of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks with highest diversity in the Greater Antilles .
Eunephrops manningi , the banded lobster , is a species of lobster found in the Florida Straits and off the coast of Anguilla .
The Pacific saury is a highly migratory species .
Palaearctonyx is an extinct genus of omnivorous Miacidae which inhabited North America during the Eocene living from 50.3 - -46.2 Ma and existed for approximately 4.1 million years .
Coelotes poleneci is a funnel - web spider species found in Austria and Slovenia .
Laubuka caeruleostigmata also known as the Leaping barb , is a species of cyprinid fish found in the Mekong and the Chao Phraya .
Ranunculus hebecarpus is a species of buttercup known by the common name delicate buttercup .
Pomacentridae is a family of perciform fish , comprising the damselfishes and clownfishes .
Wattieza was a genus of prehistoric trees that existed in the mid - Devonian that belong to the cladoxylopsids , close relatives of the modern ferns and horsetails .
Phyllostegia knudsenii is a rare species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name Waimea phyllostegia and Knudsen 's phyllostegia .
Plantago lanceolata is a species of genus Plantago known by the common names English plantain , narrowleaf plantain , ribwort plantain , ribleaf , buckhorn plantain , buckhorn , and lamb 's tongue .
Phallichthys is a genus of poeciliids native to Central America .
Amoria damonii , common name Damon 's Volute , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Ryssota ovum , the Polished Muffin , is a species of large air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicarionidae .
Trachidermus fasciatus is a species of fish in the superfamily Cottoidea , the sculpins , and the only member of the monotypic genus Trachidermus .
Omphiscola glabra is a species of small to medium - size , air - breathing , freshwater snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Lymnaeidae .
Mennegoxylon , commonly referred to as `` snakewood '' , is a genus of now extinct trees exhibiting a cell structure resembling snake skin when viewed in cross section .
Koumansetta rainfordi , the Old glory , is a species of goby native to tropical reefs of the western Pacific Ocean where it occurs at depths of from 2 to 30 metres ( 6.6 to 98.4 ft ) .
Claviceps zizaniae is a plant pathogen that causes ergot in the wild rice species Zizania aquatica and Z. palustris .
Anathallis obovata , the South American bonnet orchid , is a species of orchid .
Lepidiolamprologus nkambae is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it occurs in rocky areas at the southern end of the lake .
Bursaphelenchus is a genus of nematodes ( roundworms ) in the order Aphelenchida .
Geranium wallichianum is a species of hardy flowering herbaceous perennial plant in the genus Geranium , Geraniaceae family .
Cyprinodon nevadensis is a species of pupfish in the genus Cyprinodon .
Carditamera gracilis , or the West Indian cardita , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Carditidae .
Secostruma is a genus of subterranean ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae containing the single species Secostruma lethifera .
Hamelia papillosa is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family , Rubiaceae , that is endemic to Jamaica .
Notobrachyops is a genus of brachyopid temnospondyl amphibian .
Lecanodiaspis acaciae is a species of scale insect of the family Lecanodiaspididae .
Stipa barbata is a species of perennial grass native to southern Europe , North Africa , and the Levant in the Mediterranean Basin , and temperate Asia .
The Pleurothallidinae are a neotropical subtribe of plants of the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) including 29 genera in more than 4000 species .
Turridrupa bijubata , common name the crested turrid , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Clavatulidae .
Cotinis is a genus of scarab beetle found throughout North and South America ; at least two species ( Cotinis mutabilis and Cotinis nitida ) are common pests .
Guizotia is a genus of African herbs in the sunflower family .
Aglae is a genus of euglossine bees , with the only described species Aglae caerulea .
Acacia linifolia , known colloquially as white wattle , is a species of Acacia native to eastern Australia .
Pseudaspius leptocephalus , the Redfin , is a species of cyprinid fish found in eastern Asia where it occurs in the countries of Russia , Mongolia and China .
Oxyurichthys keiensis also known as the Kei goby is a species of goby native to marine and brackish waters along the coasts of Mozambique , South Africa , Madagascar and the Seychelles .
Snipe eels are a family , Nemichthyidae , of eels that consists of nine species in three genera .
Ferocactus latispinus is a species of barrel cactus native to Mexico .
Pasteurella testudinis is a Gram - negative , nonmotile , rod - shaped species of bacteria belonging to the Pasteurellaceae family .
Pococera is a genus of snout moths in the subfamily Epipaschiinae .
The Adelgidae is a small family of the Hemiptera closely related to the aphids , and often traditionally included in the Aphidoidea with the Phylloxeridae .
Cimolichthys is an extinct genus of 1.5- to 2.0-meter - long nektonic predatory aulopiformid fish .
Palpada lindneri is a species of flower fly first found in Bolivia .
Mipus gyratus is a species of medium - sized to large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
The Diopsoidea are a small but diverse cosmopolitan superfamily of acalyptrate muscoids , especially prevalent in the tropics .
Bandicota is a genus of rodents from Asia .
A monotypic genus , it contains the single species Caloscypha fulgens , commonly known as the spring orange peel fungus , the golden cup , or the dazzling cup .
Anillidris is a genus of ants which only contains the species Anillidris bruchi .
Silphedosuchus is an extinct genus of therocephalian therapsid from the Early Triassic of Russia .
Tidarren is a genus of spiders .
Vibrio is a genus of Gram - negative bacteria , possessing a curved - rod shape ( comma shape ) , several species of which can cause foodborne infection , usually associated with eating undercooked seafood .
Fragum erugatum is a species of small cockle , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Cardiidae .
Galium trifidum is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family , known by the common name threepetal bedstraw .
Delphinium hutchinsoniae is a rare species of larkspur known by the common names Monterey larkspur and Hutchinson 's larkspur .
Jacaratia mexicana is a species of the tropical papaya tree , in the Jacaratia genus - Caricaceae family .
Peucephyllum is a monotypic genus of flowering plants containing the single species Peucephyllum schottii .
Entelodon ( meaning `` complete teeth '' , from Ancient Greek ἐντελής entelēs `` complete '' and ὀδών odōn `` tooth '' , referring to its `` complete '' eutherian dentition ) , is an extinct genus of entelodont artiodactyl endemic to Eurasia .
Terminalia chebula , commonly known as yellow- or chebulic myrobalan , is a species of Terminalia , native to South Asia from India and Nepal east to southwest China ( Yunnan ) , and south to Sri Lanka , Malaysia , and Vietnam .
Allium gooddingii is a species of wild onion known by the common name Goodding 's onion .
Eleutherodactylus grandis ( common name : great peeping frog ; in Spanish rana - fisgona labios blancos ) is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family .
Chalcides pentadactylus , or Five - Fingered Skink , is a species of skink found in the Western Ghats of India .
Bembras is a genus of deep - water flatheads native to the Indian and western Pacific oceans .
Galatella is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , native to Europe , Asia , and northern Africa .
Erythrophleum africanum , the African blackwood , is a legume species in the genus Erythrophleum found in Savannahs of tropical Africa .
Bagrichthys macropterus , the false black lancer , is a species of bagrid catfish found in Cambodia , China , Indonesia , Laos , Malaysia , Thailand and Vietnam .
Palaeoryctes is an extinct genus of mammal from Middle to Late Palaeocene of North America .
Cymbidium tracyanum ( Tracy 's Cymbidium ) is a species of orchid .
Paludititan is a genus of titanosaurian dinosaur which existed in what is now Haţeg Basin , Romania during the late Cretaceous period .
Pleione praecox is a species of orchid found from the west - central Himalaya to China ( southern Yunnan ) .
Gastrotheca albolineata ( common name : white - lined treefrog ) is a frog species in family Hemiphractidae .
Diplocercidae is an extinct family of prehistoric coelacanth fishes which lived during the Devonian and Carboniferous period .
Erysiphe heraclei is a plant pathogen that causes powdery mildew on several species including dill , carrot and parsley .
Atretochoana eiselti is a species of caecilian originally known only from two preserved specimens discovered by Sir Graham Hales in the Brazilian rainforest , while on an expedition with Sir Brian Doll in the late 1800s , but rediscovered in 2011 by engineers working on a hydroelectric dam project in Brazil .
Cistus ocreatus is a shrubby species of flowering plant in the family Cistaceae , with purple - pink flowers .
Lasioglossum serenum , also known as the Lasioglossum ( Nesohalictus ) serenum , is a species of bees in the genus Lasioglossum , of the family Halictidae .
Chelmon marginalis , commonly known as margined coralfish , is a species of tropical fish in the family Chaetodontidae .
Ipomoea simplex is a central and eastern Southern African grassland species of Convolvulaceae or Sweet Potato family , notable for its large tuber or root , often eaten raw by Xhosa and Sotho herd boys .
Uromastyx is a genus of African and Asian agamid lizards , the member species of which are commonly called spiny - tailed lizards , uromastyces , mastigures , or dabb lizards .
Nelson 's collared lemming ( Dicrostonyx nelsoni ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Typhleotris madagascariensis is a species of troglobitic sleeper goby endemic to Madagascar , where it is only known from underground waters in the southwestern portion of the island .
The Madagascan pygmy kingfisher ( Corythornis madagascariensis ) is a species of bird in the family Alcedinidae .
Acropora caroliniana is a species of acroporid coral that was first described by Nemenzo in 1976 .
The genus contains four described species , Archimyrmex rostratus , Archimyrmex piatnitzkyi , Archimyrmex smekali and Archimyrmex wedmannae .
Tropidia is a genus of terrestrial , partly myco - heterotrophic orchids distributed across the warmer parts of both the Eastern and Western Hemispheres .
Oeonia is a genus of rare orchids ( family ( Orchidaceae ) comprising 5 currently accepted species native to Madagascar and the Mascarenes .
Echis coloratus is a venomous viper species endemic to the Middle East and Egypt .
Neon valentulus is a species of jumping spider found from Europe to Central Asia .
Krigia montana , known as Mountain dwarfdandelion , is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Primnoidae is a family of soft corals .
Ulva brevistipita is a species of blackish - green coloured seaweed in Ulvaceae family that can be found in Australia and New Zealand .
Schizopygopsis pylzovi is a species of river - dwelling fish endemic to China .
Clathrina spongiosa is a species of the genus Clathrina .
Mesaspis moreletii , commonly known as Morelet 's alligator lizard , is a species of lizard in the family Anguidae .

Metanarthecium is a genus of monocotyledonous flowering plants native to eastern Asia .

Phacelia congdonii is a species of phacelia known by the common name Congdon 's phacelia .

Entosphenus is a genus of lampreys .

Eotitanosuchus ( `` dawn giant crocodile '' ) is an extinct genus of biarmosuchian therapsid whose fossils were found in the town of Ochyor in Perm Krai , Russia . It lived about 267 mya . The only species is Eotitanosuchus olsoni .
Ceratophaga vicinella is a species of moth belonging to the family Tineidae .
It was described by Schaus in 1911 , and contains the single species , Anaulosia impolita , which is found in Costa Rica .

Lessingia leptoclada is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Sierra lessingia .

Notoxus is a genus of beetles that resemble ants .

Aralobatrachus is an extinct genus of prehistoric amphibian of the Bissekty Formation .
Franklinothrips is a genus of thrips with pantropical distribution .
Rhodogeron is a genus of flowering plants in the inula tribe within the daisy family .
Morganucodonta ( `` Glamorgan teeth '' ) is an extinct order of primitive mammaliaformes similar to crown - group mammals .
The Bala De Cañón , Coco De Mono , Paraíso , Zapote De Mico , or Zapote De Mono ( Couroupita nicaraguarensis , the epithet often spelled as nicaraguensis ) is a species of woody plant in the Lecythidaceae family .
Hopea nutans is a large rainforest tree species in the Dipterocarpaceae family .
A camel is an even - toed ungulate within the genus Camelus , bearing distinctive fatty deposits known as `` humps '' on its back .
The Bocage 's akalat ( Sheppardia bocagei ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Penicillium roseopurpureum is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which produces Carviolin .
Chiloglanis sp . nov . ' Northern Ewaso Nyiro ' is a species of fish in the Mochokidae family .
Pentasachme is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1834 .
Australian finger lime ( Meiogyne cylindrocarpa ) , also known as Fingersop , is a species of flowering shrub in the Annonaceae family .
Mecocerus wallacei is a species of beetle belonging to the family Anthribidae .
Spermacoce alata , the winged false buttonweed , is a species of plants in the Rubiaceae .
Sparrmannia africana ( African hemp , African linden ) is a species of flowering plant in the Tiliaceae family , native to open woodland in Africa , South Africa and Madagascar .
Neviusia cliftonii is a rare species of shrub in the rose family which is known by the common name Shasta snow - wreath .
Rosa henryi is a rose species native to China .
Placostylus hongii is a species of very large , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Bothriembryontidae .

Persicaria amphibia ( syn . Polygonum amphibium ) is a species of flowering plant in the knotweed family known by several common names , including longroot smartweed , water knotweed , water smartweed , and amphibious bistort .
