Mesitornis is a genus of birds in the family Mesitornithidae .
Bupleurum falcatum , also known as sickle - leaved hare's - ear , Chinese thoroughwax , sickle hare 's ear and sickle - leaf hare 's ear , is a species of flowering plant in the Apiaceae family .
Didynamipus sjostedti , the four - digit toad , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Artemisia rothrockii is a North American species of sagebrush known by the common names timberline sagebrush and Rothrock 's sagebrush .
Monotocheirodon pearsoni is a species of characin endemic to Bolivia where it occurs in the Rio Beni basin .
Volegalea cochlidium , common name the spiral melongena , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Melongenidae , the crown conches and their allies .

Agave anomala is a species of Agave in the family Asparagaceae .
Bifidobacterium bifidum is a bacterial species of the Bifidobacterium genus .
Gnaphosa taurica is a ground spider species found from Bulgaria to China .
Rhadine balesi is a species of ground beetle in the Platyninae subfamily that can be found in North America .
Carex filifolia is a species of sedge known by the common name threadleaf sedge .
Eupachygaster tarsalis , the sarce black , is a European species of soldier fly .
It is also known as dwarf water lily because it is the dwarf species of Nuphar lutea ; while Nuphar lutea has a star - shaped form of the stigma disc and glabrous leaf undersides , Nuphar pumila has a round stigma disc and the undersides of its leaves are fine - haired .
Colossendeidae is a family of sea spider ( class Pycnogonida ) .
Mitella pentandra , or Pectiantia pentandra , is a species of flowering plant in the Saxifrage Family ( Saxifragaceae ) , known by the common names fivestamen miterwort or five - point bishop 's cap .
Acanthognathus is a genus of ants that are found in tropical Central and South America .
Epilobium halleanum is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name glandular willowherb .
The family Alligatoridae of crocodylians includes alligators and caimans .
Benthoctopus levis is a species of octopus in the Octopodidae family .
Gyrinulopsis nanus is an extinct species of fossil beetle in the family Gyrinidae , the only species in the genus Gyrinulopsis .
Daphne odora ( winter daphne ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Thymelaeaceae , native to China , Japan and Korea .
Lopholiparis flerxi , the hardhead snailfish , is a species of snailfish from the northern Pacific Ocean where a single specimen ( the holotype ) was collected in June 2000 from near the Aleutian Islands at a depth of 285 metres ( 935 ft ) .
Lachesilla meinanderi is a species of Psocoptera from Lachesillidae family that is endemic to the Canary Islands .
Arctostaphylos patula is a species of manzanita known by the common name greenleaf manzanita .
Lychnis flos - jovis , the flower - of - Jove , is a species of flowering plant in the carnation and pink family Caryophyllaceaea , native to the central Alps and found at elevations of 1,000 - -2,400 m ( 3,281 - -7,874 ft ) .
Pseudopentameris is a genus of South African plants in the grass family , found only in Western Cape Province .
Anatropanthus is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1908 .
Ranunculus glacialis is an Arctic -- alpine species , found in the high mountains of southern Europe ( Alps , Pyrenees , Carpathians , Sierra Nevada ) as well as on the Scandinavian peninsula , Iceland , the Faroe Islands , Jan Mayen , Svalbard and eastern Greenland .
Helenoconcha minutissima was a species of gastropod in the Charopidae family .
Bananogmius is an extinct genus of bony fish that lived in what is today Kansas during the Late Cretaceous .
Ablepharus darvazi is a species of skink that is known only from Darvaz mountains of Tajikistan .
Erigeron arenarioides is a species of flowering plant in the ( daisy family ) known by the common names sand fleabane and Wasatch fleabane .
Radula demissa is a species of liverwort .
Penicillium crustosum is a species of Penicillium , within the phylum Ascomycota .
Musa zaifui is a species of plant in the banana family native to temperate China ( Yunnan province ) .
Camarhynchus is a genus of bird in the family Thraupidae ; all species of Camarhynchus are endemic to the Galápagos Islands , and together with related genera they are collectively known as Darwin 's finches .
Rhinotyphlops unitaeniatus , commonly known as the yellow - striped blind snake or the Kenya beaked snake , is a species of snake in the Typhlopidae family .
Urochloa brizantha ( syn . Brachiaria brizantha ) is a species of grass known by the common name palisade grass .
Cumia adjuncta is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Colubrariidae , the spindle snails , the tulip snails and their allies .
Suboestophora altamirai is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Trissexodontidae , within the Helicoidea .
Liopeltis stoliczkae is a species of snake found in South Asia and parts of Southeast Asia .
Castilleja attenuata is a species of Indian paintbrush , known by the common names valley tassels and attenuate Indian paintbrush .
Oxybasis glauca ( Syn . Chenopodium glaucum ) , common name oak - leaved goosefoot , is a species of goosefoot plant native to Europe .
Drosera macrantha , the bridal rainbow , is a scrambling or climbing perennial tuberous species in the carnivorous plant genus Drosera that is endemic to Western Australia .
Nesopupa madgei is a species of very small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Vertiginidae the whorl snails .
Neptunea antiqua , common name the red whelk , is a species of Northeast Atlantic sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
As an invasive species , Daphnia lumholtzi disrupts aquatic habitats by spreading throughout the warmer waters of lakes and reservoirs .
Echinocereus poselgeri , also known as the dahlia cactus , is a species of Echinocereus .
Rudbeckia laciniata is a species of flowering plant in the sunflower / daisy family Asteraceae , native to eastern North America , most often found in flood plains and moist soils .
Aldina is a genus of plant from Venezuelan Amazonia , of the family Fabaceae .
Mimoricopis rufescens is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimoricopis .
Arthuria tenuipilosa is a species of calcareous sponge in the genus Arthuria from Sri Lanka .
Trichonitocris tibialis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Trichonitocris .
Amorphoscelis orientalis is a species of praying mantis native to Kenya , Somalia , and Tanzania .
Gobiomorphus is a genus of sleeper gobies native to New Zealand and Australia .
Scophthalmus maeoticus ( Black Sea turbot or kalkan ) is a fish species in the family Scophthalmidae .
Symphyotrichum georgianum ( formerly Aster georgianus ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the Asteraceae , the aster family .
Pulanesaura is an extinct genus of basal sauropod known from the Early Jurassic ( late Hettangian to Sinemurian ) Upper Elliot Formation of the Free State , South Africa .
Only one species is assigned to the genus , Kiaeria limuloides .
Amblyglyphidodon aureus also known as the Golden damselfish is a species of marine fish in the family Pomacentridae , the damselfishes and clownfishes .
Trematochampsidae is an extinct family of mesoeucrocodylian crocodylomorphs .
Tahuantinsuyoa is a small genus of cichlids endemic to Peru where they are found in the Amazon Basin .
Argostemma ophirense is a species of herbaceous flowering plant in the Rubiaceae family .
Aiphanes chiribogensis is a species of palm which is endemic to western Ecuador .
Eriogonum luteolum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name goldencarpet buckwheat .
Hypsiboas riojanus is a frog species in the family Hylidae endemic to Argentina .
Lupinus havardii is a species of lupine known by the common names Big Bend bluebonnet and Chisos bluebonnet .
Asiadelphia ( `` Asian opossum '' ) is an order of Cretaceous Metatherians .
Many scientific binomial names have been given to the species Thinopyrum intermedium .
Oryctes is a genus of flowering plants in the nightshade family containing the single species Oryctes nevadensis , which is known by the common name Nevada oryctes .
Cycas bougainvilleana is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas , native to the islands northeast of Papua New Guinea , on New Britain , the Bismarck Archipelago and the Solomon Islands , where it occurs on or near the coast in calcareous coral sand dunes and in adjacent forests .
Myotis davidii , the David 's myotis , is a species of vesper bat .
Chorebus lateralis is an insect species in the genus Chorebus .
Pyrosoma atlanticum is a pelagic species of marine colonial tunicate in the class Thaliacea found in temperate waters worldwide .
Xixuthrus is a small genus of long - horned beetles , found primarily on Pacific islands , including Indonesia , New Guinea , the Solomon Islands , and Fiji , and contains some of the largest living insect species , the giant Fijian long - horned beetle and the Taveuni beetle .
Ranunculus trichophyllus , the threadleaf crowfoot or thread - leaved water - crowfoot , is a plant species in the genus Ranunculus , native to Europe , Asia and North America .
The Argentine red tegu , ( Tupinambis rufescens ) , often referred to as simply red tegu , is one of the largest species of the Tupinambis lizards .
Flaveria mcdougallii is a very rare North American plant species of yellowtops within the sunflower family .
Ganoderma zonatum is a plant pathogen that infects the palm species causing butt rot .
Scirtidae is a family of beetles ( Coleoptera ) .
Pterocarpus macrocarpus , the Burma padauk , is a species of Pterocarpus native to southeastern Asia in northeastern India , Burma , Laos , Thailand , and Vietnam .
Peziza domiciliana , commonly known as the domicile cup fungus , is a species of fungus in the genus Peziza , family Pezizaceae .

Anametalia regularis is a species of sea urchin of the family Brissidae .
Maingaya is a monotypic genus of plant containing the sole species Maingaya malayana .
Alopecosa trabalis is a wolf spider species in the genus Alopecosa found in Europe and Central Asia .
Vestia gulo is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Clausiliidae , the door snails , all of which have a clausilium .
Belontia is a genus of gouramis , the only genus within the subfamily Belontiinae , native to southern Asia .
Polytaenia nuttallii is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name Nuttall 's prairie parsley , or simply prairie parsley .
Agave utahensis is a species of agave known by the common name Utah agave .

Xestospiza fastigialis is an extinct species of bird with a ridge - shape bill that was described on the basis of fossils .
It was described by Heinrich in 1956 , and contains the species Patriciola semicana .
Thinopyrum ponticum ( syn . Agropyron elongatum , Elymus elongatus , Elymus obtusiflorus ) is a species of grass known by the common names tall wheatgrass , rush wheatgrass , and Eurasian quackgrass .

Acanthodoris uchidai is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusc in the family Onchidorididae .
The Mascarene paradise flycatcher ( Terpsiphone bourbonnensis ) is a species of bird in the Monarchidae family .
Serpianosaurus is an extinct genus of pachypleurosaurs known from the Middle Triassic ( late Anisian and early Ladinian stages ) deposits of Switzerland and Germany .
Coleotichus blackburniae is a species of insect in the family Scutelleridae , the jewel bugs .
Synodontis khartoumensis is a species of upside - down catfish native to the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Sudan and Uganda where it occurs in Lake Albert and the Nile basin .
Hara hara is a species of South Asian river catfish that occurs in Bangladesh , China , India , Myanmar and Nepal .
The Kinda baboon ( Papio cynocephalus subsp . kindae ) is a subspecies of baboon present in the Miombo woodlands of Angola , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Zambia , and possibly western Tanzania .
Bazaria djiroftella is a species of snout moth in the genus Bazaria .
Mampava rhodoneura , the buffel grass seed caterpillar , is a species of snout moth in the genus Mampava .
Dactylorhiza foliosa , common name Madeiran orchid , is a species of flowering plant in the family Orchidaceae , endemic to the Portuguese Island of Madeira in the eastern North Atlantic .
Its sole known species , Faecalibacterium prausnitzii , is an important commensal bacterium of the human gut flora .
Euryoryzomys macconnelli , also known as MacConnell 's rice rat or MacConnell 's oryzomys , is a rodent species from South America .
Centaurea pullata is a species of Centaurea found in Europe and North Africa .
Limnenetes is an extinct genus of oreodont , endemic to North America during the Late Eocene - Early Oligocene subepochs ( 38 - -33.9 mya ) existing for approximately 4.1 million years .
Caladenia robinsonii , commonly known as the Frankston Spider Orchid is a rare species of orchid which is endemic to Victoria , Australia .
Allium platycaule is a species of wild onion known by the common name broadstemmed onion or flat - stem onion .
Haplochromis arcanus was a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Victoria .
Hemithecella is a problematic genus of Ordovician mollusc proposed by Stinchcomb and Darrough in 1995 .
Kerberosaurus ( meaning `` Kerberos lizard '' ) was a genus of saurolophine duckbill dinosaur from the late Maastrichtian - age Upper Cretaceous Tsagayan Formation of Blagoveshchensk , Amur Region , Russia ( dated to 66 million years ago ) .

Zeuxine is a large genus of about 80 orchids belonging to the subfamily Orchidoideae .

Aphyocharax is a genus of characins from South America , specifically the Amazon , Orinoco , Essequibo , Paraguay and Paraná basins .

Mimulus shevockii is a rare species of monkeyflower known by the common name Kelso Creek monkeyflower .
Perenniporia is a cosmopolitan genus of bracket - forming or encrusting polypores containing over 60 currently recognized species .
Enhydrina , commonly known as the beaked sea snake , hook - nosed sea snake , common sea snake , is a genus of highly venomous sea snakes .
Schindleria brevipinguis is a species of marine fish in family Schindleriidae of Perciformes .
Laevimenes is a small neotropical genus of potter wasps which contains two species which live mainly in the Chaco and Cerrado biogeographical provinces .
Metioche vittaticollis , the silent leaf - runner cricket or silent leaf runner , is a species of cricket of the genus of Metioche .
It was described by Struve in 1958 , and the type species is Delocare boopis , which was originally described under the genus Cryphaeys by Richter in 1909 .

Streptomyces aculeolatus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from the Tottori prefecture in Japan .

Amblyeleotris diagonalis , the Diagonal shrimpgoby , is a species of goby native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean where it can be found on reefs at depths of from 6 to 40 metres ( 20 to 131 ft ) .

Peponapis pruinosa is a species of bee in the tribe Eucerini , the long - horned bees .
Panus conchatus , commonly known as the lilac oysterling , is an inedible species of mushroom that occurs throughout the Northern Hemisphere .
Bagrichthys hypselopterus is a species of bagrid catfish found in Thailand , Indonesia and Malaysia .
Rubus exsularis , the fenceline dewberry , is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Phyllomys is a genus of arboreal spiny rat , geographically restricted to the forests of eastern Brazil .
Eriogonum intrafractum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common names jointed buckwheat and napkinring .
Ginseng ( ) is any one of the 11 species of slow - growing perennial plants with fleshy roots , belonging to the genus Panax of the family Araliaceae .
Moraea viscaria is the type species of the genus of Moraea in the Iridaceae that is named after the sticky secretion on the stem and branches .
Chionaspidina is a subtribe of armored scale insects established by Borchenius .
Odostomia tasmanica , common name the Tasmania pyramid - shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Phycolepidozia exigua is the only species of liverwort in the genus Phycolepidozia and family Phycolepidoziaceae .
Ellobium chinense is a species of small , air - breathing , snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Ellobiidae .
Inyoka is a monotypic genus of southern African colubrids .
Lucilla scintilla is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Helicodiscidae .
Tandanus tropicanus or the Wet Tropics Tandan is a species of eeltail catfish native to Australia .
Niphopterolophia geminata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Niphopterolophia .
Macroscaphites is an extinct cephalopod genus included in the Ammonoidea that lived during the Barremian and Aptian stages of the Early Cretaceous ( 118 - 110 million years ago ) .
Arctostaphylos hookeri is a species of manzanita known by the common name Hooker 's manzanita .
Tillandsia utriculata , commonly known as the spreading airplant , is a species of bromeliad that is native to Florida and Georgia in the United States , the Caribbean , southern and eastern Mexico ( Tamaulipas , Veracruz , Oaxaca , the Yucatán Peninsula ) , Central America , and Venezuela .
Cuscuta pacifica is a species of dodder .
Coloeus is a subgenus of the bird genus Corvus , the crows and allies .
Rachoviscus is a small genus of characins endemic to Brazil , with two currently recognized species :
Cedrorestes is a genus of iguanodontian dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous of Utah .
Echinacea laevigata , the smooth purple coneflower , is an Endangered Species Act federally listed endangered species of plant found in the piedmont of the eastern United States .
Ophthalmopone is a ponerine genus of ants found in Sub - Saharan Africa .
Dipsas is a genus of nonvenomous New World colubrid snakes in the subfamily Xenodontinae .
Osmunda is a genus of primarily temperate - zone ferns of family Osmundaceae .
Spionidae is a family of marine worms within the Polychaeta .
Luciobarbus mursa is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Luciobarbus from freshwater habitats in Central Asia and Iran .
Tricheczemotes dystasioides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Tricheczemotes .
Cyrtopodium cristatum is a species of orchid native to South America ( Brazil , Venezuela , Colombia and the Guianas ) .
Schaereria brunnea is a species of fungi within the Agyriaceae family , first found in inland rainforests of British Columbia .
Suillellus pictiformis is a species of bolete fungus found in North America .
Gynocardia odorata is a species of evergreen tree belonging to the Achariaceae family .
Borkovia is a genus of Cercozoa .
Chamaechaenactis , common name fullstem , is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Anthela varia , the variable anthelid , is a species of moth of the Anthelidae family .
Thorybopus is a genus of sea slugs , specifically dorid nudibranchs .
Conus bullatus , common name the bubble cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Elgaria is a genus of New World lizards in the family Anguidae .
Eria ovata is a species of orchid found from the Ryukyu Islands and Taiwan to the Philippines .
Penicillium palitans is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from cheese and ancient permafrost deposits .
Pemptolasius humeralis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pemptolasius .
Searsia pyroides , previously known as Rhus pyroides , ( common currant - rhus English , gewone taaibos Afrikaans , nhlokoshiyane isiZulu ) is a species of Searsia , native to southern Africa .
Limbochromis robertsi is a species of cichlid endemic to Ghana where it is found in the upper reaches of the Pra River Basin .
Rhyncholepis is an extinct genus of anaspida from the Late Silurian .
The Madagascan rousette or Madagascar rousette ( Rousettus madagascariensis ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae endemic to Madagascar .
Phrynocephalus mystaceus is a species of agamid lizard found in Iran , North Afghanistan , Eastern Caucasus , Kazakhstan , Uzbekistan and possibly in south of Astrakhan Oblast .
Rhetus arcius is a species of Neotropical butterfly , first described in Carl Linnaeus ' 1763 Centuria Insectorum .
Microsauria ( `` small lizards '' ) is an extinct order of lepospondyl amphibians from the late Carboniferous and early Permian periods .
Mordellistena horvathi is a species of beetle in the Mordellidae family which is in the Tenebrionoidea superfamily .
Coenochroa prolixa is a species of snout moth in the genus Coenochroa .
Alluaudia montagnacii is a rare species of flowering plants belonging to the family Didiereaceae .
Amblyotrypauchen arctocephalus , the armor eelgoby , is a species of goby found from the Indian Ocean waters around India to the western Pacific Ocean where it occurs at depths of from 37 to 92 metres ( 121 to 302 ft ) .
Ithycyphus miniatus is a species of venomous lamprophiid snake native to Madagascar .
Geomalacus malagensis is a species of air - breathing land slug , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Arionidae , the round back slugs .
Sebastes miniatus is a species of rockfish known by the common names vermilion rockfish , vermilion seaperch , red snapper , and red rock cod . It is native to the waters of the Pacific Ocean off western North America from Baja California to Vancouver Island .
Sphaeridium is a genus of beetles in the family Hydrophilidae , the water scavenger beetles .
Pemphigus betae , also known as the sugarbeet root aphid , is a species of gall - forming aphid that forms galls specifically on the commonly found Narrowleaf Cottonwood ( aka the Willow - leaved Poplar tree ) , Populus angustifolia .
Nebria andalusia is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily .
Acanthostichus brevicornis is a species of ant belonging to the Acanthostichus genus .
Pleuroncodes monodon , sometimes called the red squat lobster , is a species of squat lobster from the south - eastern Pacific Ocean , where it is the subject of commercial fishery alongside the species Cervimunida johni .
Bergamodactylus is a genus of basal pterosaur living during the Late Triassic ( early Norian ) in the area of present - day Bergamo province in Italy .
Bombus confusus is a species of bumblebee found in Austria , Belgium , the Czech Republic , France , Germany , Hungary , Lithuania , Poland , Romania , Slovakia , Slovenia , Spain , and Switzerland .
Clanculus miniatus , common name the keeled top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Cerithiopsis apicina is a species of very small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Cerithiopsidae .
Cordania is an extinct genus of trilobite that lived during the lower and Middle Devonian .
Ancyloxypha is a genus of skipper butterflies in the subfamily Hesperiinae .
Paratetralophodon is an extinct genus of gomphothere .
Pseudothelphusidae is a family of freshwater crabs found chiefly in mountain streams in the Neotropics .
Heterocaprella krishnaensis is a species of crustacean from the Caprellidae family .
Pontinus is a genus of scorpionfishes .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Harknessiella purpurea .
The orthopteran family Rhaphidophoridae includes the cave weta , cave crickets , camelback crickets , camel crickets , spider crickets ( sometimes shortened to `` criders '' , or `` land shrimp '' or sprickets `` ) and sand treaders , of the suborder Ensifera .
Azara 's tuco - tuco ( Ctenomys azarae ) is a species of rodent in the family Ctenomyidae .
Kurtus gulliveri , the nurseryfish , is a species of nurseryfish native to fresh and brackish waters in southern New Guinea and northern Australia .
Typhlocerus prodigiosus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Typhlocerus .
Ecsenius tricolor , known commonly as the Derawan combtooth - blenny in Indonesia , is a species of combtooth blenny in the genus Ecsenius .
Euryclytosemia nomurai is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Euryclytosemia .
Bucanellidae is an extinct family of Paleozoic molluscs of uncertain position , belonging either to Gastropoda ( snails ) or Monoplacophora .
Pseudochattonella is a genus of marine , heterokont flagellates belonging to the class of Dictyochophyceae .
Xenorophidae is an extinct family of primitive odontocetes currently known from the Oligocene of the southeastern US .
Oberea assamensis is a species of flat - faced longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Oberea , discovered by Breuning in 1982 .
Exaerete smaragdina is a species of euglossine bees .
Henri 's snowfinch ( Montifringilla henrici ) is a species of bird in the sparrow family .
Cassidulus delectus is a species of sea urchins of the Family Cassidulidae .
Ombrana sikimensis is a species of frog that is the only member of genus Ombrana ; the validity of this genus is uncertain .
Bayerotrochus teramachii , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pleurotomariidae .
Trichomycterus poikilos is a species of pencil catfish endemic to Brazil , where it occurs in the Jacuí , Pardo and Taquari - das Antas river basins , tributaries of the Laguna dos Patos system , in the state of Rio Grande do Sul .
Orthochilus ecristatus , the giant orchid , is a terrestrial species of orchid native to Cuba and to the southeastern United States ( from Louisiana to North Carolina ) .
Badumna is a genus of spiders from Australasia .
Hirudo verbana is a species of leech .
Kohleria amabilis , the tree gloxinia , is a species of the flowering plant belonging to the family Gesneriaceae .
Umbonia spinosa is a species of Membracidae ( also known as Treehoppers ) native to South America .
Roeslerstammiidae is a family of insects in the order Lepidoptera .
Phalangiotarbi ( Haase , 1890 ) is an extinct arachnid order first recorded from the Early Devonian of Germany and most widespread in the Upper Carboniferous coal measures of Europe and North America .
Monoctenocera brachiella is a species of snout moth , and the type species in the genus Monoctenocera .
Thermus is a genus of thermophilic bacteria .
Pelosia muscerda , the dotted footman , is a species of moth of the family Arctiidae .
Actinobacillus is a genus of Gram - negative , immotile and nonspore - forming , oval to rod - shaped bacteria occurring as parasites or pathogens in mammals , birds , and reptiles .
Sphodros atlanticus is a species of spider from the family Atypidae .
Oxalis articulata , known as pink - sorrel , or windowbox wood - sorrel , is a plant species in the genus Oxalis native to South America .
Vanda flabellata is a species of epiphytic orchid native to Yunnan , Myanmar , Laos and Thailand .
Colopea xerophila is a species of spider in the Colopea genus .
Both Polychelidae and Eryonoidea had traditionally been included in the infraorder Palinura , alongside the spiny lobsters and slipper lobsters ( now in the infraorder Achelata ) .
Echinacea angustifolia ( Narrow - leaved purple coneflower or blacksamson echinacea ) is a North American plant species in sunflower family .
Mastacembelus alboguttatus ( Boulenger 's spiny eel ) is a species of ray - finned fish endemic to India , Myanmar and Thailand , known from Sittaung River , Salween River and Manipur River and possibly Irrawaddy River .
Atriplex coronata is a species of saltbush known by the common name crownscale .
Carex dallii is an uncommon species of sedge native to the South Island ( North West Nelson , Westland and Otago ) of New Zealand .
Scaphella evelina , commonly known as the Evelyn 's volute is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Plagiochila wolframii is a species of plant in the Plagiochilaceae family .
Neopseustis fanjingshana is a species of moth belonging to the family Neopseustidae .
Peipiaosteus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish , closely related to living sturgeon and paddlefish .
Bunodophoron is a genus of lichens in the order Lecanorales .
Amalda novaezelandiae is a species of small sea snail , a gastropod mollusc of the family Olividae , the olives .
Kurixalus banaensis ( Bana bubble - nest frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
The Indian hare ( Lepus nigricollis ) , also known as the black - naped hare , is a common species of hare found in the Indian Subcontinent and in Java .
Larinus pollinis is a species of cylindrical weevils belonging to the family Curculionidae , subfamily Lixinae .
Lasthenia platycarpha is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name alkali goldfields .
Symphyotrichum lanceolatum ( syn . Aster lanceolatus ) is a species of flowering plant in the aster family , Asteraceae .
Salangichthys microdon , the Japanese icefish , is a species of icefish found in Japan , Korea and Siberia .
The Ditomyiidae are a family of flies ( Diptera ) comprising only two genera :
Chaetostoma microps is a species of suckermouth armored catfish native to Ecuador .
Clavoserixia bifasciata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Clavoserixia .
Hygrocybe virescens , commonly known as the lime - green waxy cap , is a species of agaric mushroom in the Hygrophoraceae family .
Feltiella acarisuga is a predatory gall midge which will feed on various species of spider mites .
Homalium ceylanicum is a species of tree which grows up to 30 metres tall .
Uromycladium falcatarium ( falcataria gall rust fungus ) is a species of rust fungus in the genus Uromycladium .
The Nodding Epidendrum ( Epidendrum nutans ) is a species of orchid in the genus Epidendrum .
Anthrasimias gujaratensis was a species of primate first found in Gujarat , India in 2008 .
Nebria danmanni is a species of ground beetle from Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to the US state of Washington .
Ranunculus jovis is a species of buttercup known by the common name Utah buttercup .
Tauschia howellii is a rare species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common names Howell 's umbrellawort and Howell 's tauschia .
Haliichthys taeniophorus , the Ribboned pipefish , is a species of pipefish found along the coast of Western Australia in habitats ranging from shallow and weedy to deeper and sandy bottoms down to depths of 16 metres ( 52 ft ) .
Galium saxatile or heath bedstraw is a plant species of the genus Galium .
Nedcolbertia is a genus of theropod dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous Period of North America .
Leptodactylus labyrinthicus is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family , commonly known in English as the labyrinth frog , pepper frog , or pepper foam frog .
Cryopterygius ( meaning ' frozen fin ' in Greek ) is an extinct genus of ophthalmosaurid ichthyosaurian known from the uppermost Jurassic of Central Spitsbergen , Norway .
Pimelia angulata is a species of darkling beetles in the subfamily Pimeliinae .
Chondrichthyes ( /kɒnˈdrɪkθᵻ.iːz/ ; from Greek χονδρ- chondr- ' cartilage ' , ἰχθύς ichthys ' fish ' ) is a class that contains the cartilaginous fishes : they are jawed vertebrates with paired fins , paired nares , scales , a heart with its chambers in series , and skeletons made of cartilage rather than bone .
Rubicundus is a genus of hagfishes .
Canna coccinea is a species of the Canna genus , belonging to the family Cannaceae , a native of northern Argentina .
Parapomempsoides camerunica is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parapomempsoides .
Ornatifilum ( Latin ornatus + filum , Ornamented filament ) is an artificial form genus , which is used to categorise any small , branched filaments with external ornamentation .
Ammotretis is a genus of righteye flounders native to the coastal waters off southern Australia .
Erigeron maguirei is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Maguire daisy and Maguire 's fleabane .
Mitella trifida is a species of flowering plant in the saxifrage family known by the common names threeparted miterwort and Pacific miterwort .
Rhacophorus omeimontis is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family endemic to China .
Toxochelys ( TOKS uh KEE leez ) is an extinct genus of marine turtle from the Cretaceous period .
Psilothrix viridicoerulea is a species of soft - winged flower beetles belonging to the family Melyridae , subfamily Dasytinae .
Carex chichijimensis is a species of perennial sedge of the genus Carex endemic to Chichijima Island in Japan .
Paraprenanthes is a genus of East Asian plants in the dandelion tribe within the daisy family , most of the species found only in China .
Acantholycosa lignaria is a species of wolf spider .
Microleter is an extinct genus of parareptile which existed in Oklahoma during the Early Permian period .
Colubrina oppositifolia , known as Kauila in Hawaiian , is a species of flowering tree in the buckthorn family , Rhamnaceae , that is endemic to Hawaii .
Correa reflexa var . angustifolia , commonly known as Grampians Correa , is a variety of Correa reflexa endemic to Victoria in Australia .
Spiny lobsters , also known as langouste or rock lobsters , are a family ( Palinuridae ) of about 60 species of achelate crustaceans , in the Decapoda Reptantia .
Phlox speciosa is a species of phlox known by the common name showy phlox .
Colpodium is a genus of plants in the grass family , native primarily to Asia but with a few species on certain mountains in Africa .
Paraleptamphopidae is a family of amphipod crustaceans , containing three genera .
Arnoliseus is a genus of jumping spiders that is only found in Brazil .
Limonium emarginatum is a species of sea lavender known by the common names Gibraltar sea lavender .
Cylindera agnata is an extant species of tiger beetle in the genus Cylindera .
Parodia mammulosa is a species of succulent plant in the Cactaceae family .
Collinsia multicolor is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family , known by the common names San Francisco blue - eyed Mary and San Francisco collinsia .
Musgravea heterophylla , commonly known as the crater oak or grey silky oak , is a species of rainforest tree of the family Proteaceae from north - eastern Queensland .
Brachinus pectoralis is a species of ground beetle in the Brachininae subfamily that can be found in Albania , Bulgaria , Corsica , Canary Islands , France , Greece , Hungary , Italy , Slovakia , Ukraine , southern part of Russia , European part of Turkey , and Spain .
Erigeron vernus is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Early white - top fleabane .
Quercus myrsinifolia is an Asian species evergreen oak tree to 20 metres ( 66 ft ) tall in the ring - cupped oaks subgenus .
Banksia sphaerocarpa var . pumilio is a variety of Banksia sphaerocarpa .
Crymocetus is an extinct genus of plesiosaur from the Cretaceous Chalk Group of Sussex , England .
Obergfellia is an extinct genus of stem perissodactyl from the middle Eocene , discovered in 1980 .
Morimopsidius triangularis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Morimopsidius .
Chalcides montanus is a species of skink found in the Atlas Mountains in Morocco .
Ectopsocus ( McLachlan , 1899 ) is a genus of insects , often known commonly as book lice or bark lice .
The Tingidae are a family of very small ( 2 - -10 mm ( 0.08 - -0.39 in ) ) insects in the order Hemiptera that are commonly referred to as lace bugs .
Phliantidae is a family of isopod - like amphipod crustaceans chiefly from the southern hemisphere .
Alocasia macrorrhizos is a species of flowering plant in the arum family , Araceae , that it is native to rainforests from Malaysia to Queensland and has long been cultivated on many Pacific islands and elsewhere in the tropics .
Bothrops fonsecai , or Fonseca 's lancehead , is a species of venomous snake in the Viperidae family .
Drepanosaurus ( Dre - pan - o - sore - us ) is a genus of arboreal ( tree - dwelling ) reptile that lived during the Triassic Period .
Poa kelloggii is a species of grass known by the common name Kellogg 's bluegrass .
The Zygaenidae moths are a family of Lepidoptera .
Corallus cropanii , or Cropan 's tree boa , is a nonvenomous boa species found in the state of São Paulo , Brazil .
Nehalennia speciosa ( pygmy damselfly , sedgeling or sedgling ) is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
Anisopodus hamaticollis is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family that was described by Bates in 1872 .
Anemia mexicana , the Mexican flowering fern , is a fern species in the genus Anemia , sometimes called flowering ferns .
Aplexa hypnorum , or by the common name , the moss bladder snail , is a species of small air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Physidae , a family which are sometimes known as the bladder snails .
Boykinia rotundifolia is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the saxifrage family known by the common name roundleafed brookfoam .
Gilia minor is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name little gilia .
Pteris semipinnata is a fern species in the Pteridoideae subfamily of the Pteridaceae .
Copelandia is a now deprecated genus of mushrooms consisting of at least 12 species .
Pakicetidae ( `` Pakistani whales '' ) is an extinct family of early whales that lived during the Early Eocene on the shores of Pakistan .
Stipa capillata is a perennial bunchgrass species in the family Poaceae , native to Europe and Asia .
Tryblidium is a paleozoic genus of Ordovician and Silurian monoplacophorans .
Kerodiadelia capicola is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Kerodiadelia .
It contains the single species Hypagoptera rufeola , which is found in South Africa .
Taphrina caerulescens is a species of fungus in the Taphrinaceae family .
Dugastella marocana is a species of shrimp from the Atyidae family .
Lophomyrtus bullata , also known as ramarama or bubbleleaf , is a species of evergreen myrtle shrub in the genus Lophomyrtus , family Myrtaceae .
Euprymna stenodactyla is a species of bobtail squid .
Microsynodontis hirsuta is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Gabon where it occurs in the Ntem River .
Bowlesia incana is a species of flowering plant in the parsley family known by the common name hoary bowlesia .
Cranopsis expansa , common name the broad puncturella , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .
Harfordia , also called Rabbit 's Purse , is a genus of plants in the family Polygonaceae , with a single species Harfordia macroptera .
Campanula alpina is a species of perennial bellflower found in the Eastern Alps , Carpathian Mountains and the Balkans .
Phacelia argillacea is a rare species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common names clay phacelia and Atwood 's phacelia .
Dierama pendulum , commonly known as fairy bell , hair bell and wedding bell , is a species of Iridaceae endemic to the Eastern Cape and first collected in 1772 by the Swedish naturalist Carl Peter Thunberg near Essenbos on the Kromme River or Kromrivier which flows down the Langkloof .
Leontice is a group of perennial , tuberous herbs in the Berberidaceae described as a genus by Linnaeus in 1753 .
Rhododendron catawbiense , with common names Catawba rosebay , Catawba rhododendron , mountain rosebay , purple ivy , purple laurel , purple rhododendron , red laurel , rosebay , rosebay laurel , is a species of Rhododendron native to the eastern United States , growing mainly in the southern Appalachian Mountains from Virginia south to northern Alabama .
Ceroxys hortulana is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Ceroxys of the family Ulidiidae found in the Czech Republic , Austria , Bosnia Herzegovina , Corsica , Croatia , France , Germany , Italy , Lithuania , Moldova , Poland , Portugal , Romania , Hungary , Slovakia , Ukraine , and Russia .
Arctostaphylos hooveri , the Santa Lucia Manzanita , is a plant species endemic to the Santa Lucia Mountains in Monterey County , California .
Mesopropithecus is an extinct genus of small to medium - sized lemur , or strepsirrhine primate , from Madagascar that includes three species , M. dolichobrachion , M. globiceps , and M. pithecoides .
The order Cyatheales , which includes the tree ferns , is a taxonomic division of the fern class , Polypodiopsida .
Auchenipterichthys thoracatus is a species of driftwood catfish endemic to Peru where it is found in the Amazon River basin .
Leftvents are small , deep - sea lophiiform fish comprising the family Linophrynidae distributed throughout tropical to subtropical waters of all oceans .
Galega orientalis is a species of flowering plant in the Fabaceae , the legume family .
Pliobates cataloniae is a species of stem - ape that was found to be the sister taxon to gibbons and great apes and humans .
Hydrophis spiralis , commonly known as the yellow sea snake , is a species of venomous sea snake in the family Elapidae .
Bromus ciliatus is a species of brome grass known by the common name fringed brome .
Myrmica schencki is a species of ant in the genus Myrmica .
Saurosuchus ( meaning `` lizard crocodile '' in Greek ) is an extinct genus of paracrocodylomorph .
Brookesia therezieni , also known as the Perinet leaf chameleon , is a species of chameleon endemic to eastern Madagascar .
Xyliphius lombarderoi is a species of banjo catfish endemic to Argentina where it occurs in the Paraná River basin .
Pilostyles thurberi is a species of flowering plant known by the common names Thurber 's stemsucker and Thurber 's pilostyles .
Schultesiophytum is a genus of plants first described as a genus in 1958 .
Babiana stricta ( baboon flower , blue freesia ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Iridaceae , native to Cape Province , South Africa and naturalized in Australia .
Guarea thompsonii ( also called Black Guarea or Dark Bossé ) is a species of plant in the Meliaceae family .
It was first named by Allison C. Daley , Graham E. Budd in 2010 and the type species is Caryosyntrips serratus .
Calliandra bella is a species of flowering plants of the genus Calliandra in Fabaceae family .
Tetrapus is a genus of fig wasp native to the Americas .
Dahlia anemones are closely related to mottled anemones ( Urticina crassicornis ; Müller , 1776 ) , and both species are usually referred to as northern red anemones .
Tintinnabularia is a genus of flowering plants in the dogbane family , Apocynaceae , first described for modern science as a genus in 1936 .

Homalopoma grippii , common name Gripp 's dwarf turban , is a species of small sea snail with calcareous opercula , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Colloniidae .
Euzophera osseatella , the eggplant borer , is a species of snout moth in the genus Euzophera .
Cadomoceras is an extinct cephalopod genus from the order ammonitida that lived during the Bajocian Stage of the Middle Jurassic , approximately 178 to 175 million years ago .
Parachondrostoma is a genus of cyprinid fish found mostly in Spain with one species entering France .
Serolis is a genus of isopod crustacean , containing the following species :
Requienella is a genus of lichenized fungi in the family Requienellaceae .
Crataegus aprica is a species of hawthorn native to the southeastern United States .
Psychropotes longicauda is a species of sea cucumber in the family Psychropotidae .
Capsicum mirabile is a wild species of the genus Capsicum , which is found in the rainforests of Brazil .
The family Melastomataceae ( alternatively Melastomaceae ) is a taxon of dicotyledonous flowering plants found mostly in the tropics ( two thirds of the genera are from the New World tropics ) comprising some 200 genera and 4500 species .
Mastigoproctus colombianus is a whip scorpion species found in Colombia , South America , near west deserts areas .
Loweina is a small genus of lanternfishes .
Triuris hyalina is a species in genus Triuris .
Cyrenida is an extinct genus of clams in the family Cyrenidae .
Polanisia dodecandra is a species of flowering plant in the Cleome family , Cleomaceae , known by the common name redwhisker clammyweed , or western clammyweed , although there are other Polanisia species called clammyweed .
Acanthoscurria antillensis is a species of large spider , a tarantula in the family Theraphosidae .
Philautus similipalensis ( common name : Similipal bush frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Pilina solarium is an extinct species of a paleozoic Silurian monoplacophoran .
Restrepia chocoensis is a species in the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) , named for the Department of Chocó , Colombia , where it was discovered .
Tradescantia zebrina , formerly known as Zebrina pendula , is a species of spiderwort more commonly known as an inchplant or wandering jew .
It contains only one species , Taiwancylis cladodium , which is found in Taiwan .
Huntleya fasciata is a species of orchid that occurs from Colombia and northwestern Ecuador to Honduras and Belize .
Bradyrhizobium is a genus of Gram - negative soil bacteria , many of which fix nitrogen .
Anthribidae is a family of beetles also known as fungus weevils .
Pademelons are small marsupials of the genus Thylogale .
Trichophorum alpinum is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family known by the common name alpine bulrush .
Tillandsia paucifolia , the potbelly airplant , is a species in the genus Tillandsia .
Chloroselas is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . The members ( species ) of this genus are found in the Afrotropic ecozone .
Procambarus nueces , sometimes called the Nueces crayfish , is a species of crayfish in the family Cambaridae .
Clathrinidae is a family of calcareous sponges in the order Clathrinida .
Calanoida is an order of copepods , a kind of zooplankton .
Phoenix acaulis ( acaulis , Latin , trunkless ) or Dwarf Date Palm / Stemless Date Palm is a species of flowering plant in the palm family , native to northern India , Bhutan and Nepal .
Raymondiceras is genus of ammonoid cephalopod belonging to the Cheiloceratidae family .
Parajoesse nagaensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parajoesse .
Eleutherodactylus teretistes ( Spanish : Rana - ladrona Silbadora ) is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family .
Hernandia drakeana was a species of plant in the Hernandiaceae family .
Veronica officinalis ( heath speedwell , common gypsyweed , common speedwell , or Paul 's betony ) is a species of Veronica , native to Europe and western Asia .
Micropterix aureocapilla is a species of moth belonging to the family Micropterigidae that was described by Heath in 1986 , and is known only of the type locality El Hadjar in Algeria .
Rhododendron selense ( 多变杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to southwestern Sichuan , eastern Xizang , and western Yunnan in China , where it grows at altitudes of 2700 - -4000 meters .
Amaranthus acanthochiton ( Greenstripe ) , is an annual plant species of the genus Amaranthus in the Amaranthaceae family .
Guchengosuchus is an extinct genus of erythrosuchid archosauriform from the Early Triassic of China .
Lomanotidae is a family of sea slugs , marine gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Tritonioidea .
Sinistrella sinistralis is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk unassigned in the superfamily Conoidea .
Alagomyidae is a family of rodents known from the late Paleocene and early Eocene of Asia and North America ( McKenna and Bell , 1997 ) .
Glyptops ( Greek for `` grooved face '' ) is an extinct genus of cryptodire turtle dating from the Late Jurassic and Early Cretaceous periods 155 to 99 m.y.a .
Adenium obesum is a species of flowering plant in the dogbane family , Apocynaceae , that is native to the Sahel regions , south of the Sahara ( from Mauritania and Senegal to Sudan ) , and tropical and subtropical eastern and southern Africa and Arabia .
Tricolia speciosa , common name the Mediterranean pheasant , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Phasianellidae .
Commersonia dasyphylla , commonly known as kerrawang , is a species of shrub of the Malvaceae family native to eastern Australia .
Pseudobagarius meridionalis is a species of catfish belonging to the family Akysidae ( the stream catfishes ) .
Halocaridina is a genus of atyid shrimp .
Virginia valeriae , commonly known as the smooth earth snake , is a species of nonvenomous natricine colubrid snake native to the eastern half of the United States .
Insalebria concineratella is a species of snout moth in the genus Insalebria .
Weissella cibaria is a species of Gram - positive bacteria , placed within the family of Leuconostocaceae .
Epidirona is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Turridae , the turrids .
Eatonina laurensi is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cingulopsidae .
Alphomorphus vandykei is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Alphomorphus .
Chandlerella quiscali , also known as the Grackle nematode , is a species of filarial nematode that parasitizes the brain of several common North American birds , namely the grackle , blue jay , brown cowbird , and starling .
Leioproctus carinatifrons is a species of Australian bee .
Silesitidae is an ammonite family .
Pitar fulminatus , or the lightning venus clam , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Veneridae .
The Mountain Frog ( Philoria richmondensis ) is a species of frog in the Myobatrachidae family .
Aristida rhizomophora is a species of grass known by the common name Florida threeawn .
Epicoccum nigrum is a species of fungus , from the phylum Ascomycota .
Perkinsus is a genus of protists in the phylum Perkinsozoa .
Cyclamen alpinum (= Cyclamen trochopteranthum ) is a perennial growing from a tuber , native to pine , juniper , sweetgum , or cedar woodland at 350 - -1,500 m ( 1,150 - -4,920 ft ) above sea level in an area of southwestern Turkey , northwest of Antalya , isolated from other species of the Cyclamen coum group .
Nucella canaliculata , common name : the Channelled Dog Winkle , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Candida dubliniensis is cosmopolitan ( found around the world ) , and has been described as a separate species in 1995 .
Batrachomimus is an extinct genus of neosuchian crocodyliform known from the Late Jurassic of northeastern Brazil .
The Nilgiri marten ( Martes gwatkinsii ) is the only species of marten found in southern India .
Bullia natalensis , the pleated plough shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae , the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks .
Craterocephalus is a genus of small and slender brackish or freshwater silversides from Australia and New Guinea .
Cryptococcus ( Greek for `` hidden sphere '' ) is a genus of fungus .
Huperzia mannii is a species of lycopod plant known by the common names Mann 's clubmoss and wawae`iole .
Eumerus funeralis or Lesser bulb fly ( Eumerus strigatus shares this name ) is a species of Hoverfly , from the family Syrphidae , in the order Diptera .
Cyrtomium falcatum is a species of fern known by the common names house holly - fern and Japanese holly fern .
Arctostaphylos pumila , with the common name Sandmat manzanita , is a species of manzanita .
Elasmostethus tristriatus ( also called Juniper Shieldbug ) is a species of bugs in Shield bug family .
Pseudopontia paradoxa is a species of butterfly found only in wet forests of tropical Africa .
Fundella ignobilis is a species of snout moth in the genus Fundella .
Pycna is a genus of cicadas from Africa and Asia .
Neatypus obliquus , the western footballer or footballer sweep , is a species of sea chub endemic to southern reefs of Australia , where it can be found down to 30 m ( 98 ft ) .
Clarazia is an extinct genus of thalattosaur from the Middle Triassic of Monte San Giorgio in Switzerland .
Aphthona herbigrada is a species of leaf beetles from the subfamily Galerucinae .
Sardinella hualiensis ( Taiwan sardinella ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Sardinella .
Theelia is an extinct genus of sea cucumber which existed from 312 to 40.4 million years ago ( Middle Pennsylvanian to the Lutetian age ) .
Conus quercinus , common names the oak cone or the yellow cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Pistacia mexicana , the American pistachio , is a species of plant in the Anacardiaceae family found in Guatemala , Mexico , and Texas .
Parlatoreopsidina is a subtribe of armored scale insects .
Celmisia spectabilis is one of the more widespread species in the mountainous areas of New Zealand , where it is commonly known as the cotton daisy .
It contains the single known species Amianthium muscitoxicum , known in English as fly poison from a literal translation of the Latin epithet muscitoxicum , and is noted for its pretty flowers and its toxic alkaloid content .
Hydrogenophaga flava is a species of Gram - negative , rod - shaped comamonad bacteria .
Opuntia microdasys ( angel's - wings , bunny ears cactus , bunny cactus or polka - dot cactus ) is a species of cactus native and endemic to central and northern Mexico .
Mittonia carcassoni is a species of snout moth , and the type species in the genus Mittonia .
Cabreuva lucianoi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cabreuva .
Ogilbia galapagosensis , or the Galapagos cuskeel , is a species of fish in the Bythitidae family .
Gundlachia radiata is a species of minute freshwater snail or limpet , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Planorbidae .
Vertigo milium , common name the blade vertigo , is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Vertiginidae , the whorl snails .
The Limidae or file shells are members of the only family of bivalve molluscs in the suborder Limoida .
Carapa guianensis is a species of the family Meliaceae ( Mahogany family ) .
Atopochilus vogti is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Tanzania where it occurs in the Wami River .
Philodromus depriesteri is a spider species found in Austria and Germany .
Selaginella willdenowii is a species of spikemoss known by the common names Willdenow 's spikemoss and peacock fern , due to its iridescent blue leaves .
Salix gooddingii is a species of willow known by the common name Goodding 's willow , or Goodding 's black willow .
Asplenium scolopendrium is a common species in Europe , but in North America occurs as rare , widely scattered populations that have been given varietal status , A. scolopendrium var . americanum .
Herniaria hirsuta is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name hairy rupturewort .
Feia is a genus of gobies native to shallow coastal waters of the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
The sole species , Cyclolepis genistoides , is native to South America , where it occurs in Argentina , Chile , Paraguay , and possibly Bolivia .
Ichibengops is an extinct genus of therocephalian therapsid known from the type species Ichibengops munyamadziensis , which lived in what is now Zambia during the Late Permian .
Calochortus palmeri is a species of flowering plant in the lily family known by the common names Palmer 's mariposa lily and strangling mariposa .
Ibacus ciliatus is a species of slipper lobster from the north - west Pacific Ocean .
Trifolium bifidum is a species of clover known by the common names notchleaf clover and pinole clover .
Streptomyces amritsarensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from Punjab in India .
Haliplus ruficollis is a species of water beetle from the Haliplidae family that can be found everywhere in Europe , the Near East and the East Palaearctic , but is absent in Albania and all European islands except for Corsica .
Cicindela marginipennis is a species of tiger beetle native to the eastern North America .
Amorpha ouachitensis is an uncommon North American species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common names Ouachita leadplant , Ouachita Mountain leadplant , Ouachita false indigo , and Ouachita indigobush .
Lampedusa imitratix is a species of small , very elongate , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Clausiliidae , the door snails , all of which have a clausilium .
Tirania purpurea , the sole species in genus Tirania , is a species of climbing plant native to Asia .
Allium lacunosum is a species of wild onion known by the common name pitted onion .
Vanilla humblotii is a species of orchid endemic to Madagascar and the island of Grande Comore in the Comoros Islands .
Astralium haematragum , common name the Pacific star shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Synapsis ilicifolia is a species of plant in the Schlegeliaceae family .
Carallia diplopetala is a species of plant in the Rhizophoraceae family that can be found in China and Vietnam .
Staphylococcus capitis is a coagulase negative species ( CoNS ) of Staphylococcus .
Cribragapanthia scutellata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cribragapanthia .
Oberea coxalis is a species of longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Oberea , discovered by Gressitt in 1940 .
Steindachneridion is a genus of South American pimelodid catfish ( order Siluriformes ) .
Muscari neglectum is a perennial bulbous plant , one of a number of species and genera known as grape hyacinth and in particular common grape hyacinth or starch grape hyacinth .
The tapertail , Radiicephalus elongatus , is a species of marine fish found in the central and eastern Atlantic and eastern Pacific .
Littledalea is a genus of Asian plants in the grass family , native to mountains in China and neighboring countries .
Dardanus gemmatus , the jeweled anemone hermit crab , is a species of hermit crab native to tropical reefs surrounding the Indo - Pacific , typically at depths of 2 - -100 metres ( 10 - -330 ft ) .
Aegialiinae is a small subfamily of much larger Scarabaeidae family , which contains all species of scarab beetles .
Amphisbaena arenaria is a species of worm lizard found in Brazil .
Apis mellifera sahariensis is a North African bee subspecies , of the species Apis mellifera .
Songanella is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the early Tithonian stage of the Late Jurassic epoch .
Penicillium multicolor is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which produces alpha - L - fucosidase , tilactase , sclerotiorin , 8-O - Methylsclerotiorinamine , multicolosic acid and isochromophilones .
Hypericum anagalloides is a species of St. John 's wort known by the common names creeping St. John's - wort , tinker 's penny and bog St. John's - wort .
The Thyreocorinae ( formerly Thyreocoridae at the family level ) are a subfamily of shield bugs , known by common names that include negro bugs or ebony bugs .
Meiacanthus anema , the Threadless blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in Asia and Oceania .
Simnia spelta is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Ovulidae , the ovulids , which are cowrie allies sometimes called `` false cowries '' .
The Yungas screech owl ( Megascops hoyi ) , also known as Hoy 's screech owl , is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
Solidago faucibus , the gorge goldenrod , is North American species of flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Parentucellia latifolia is a species of flowering plant in the broomrape family known by several common names , including red bartsia , red tarweed , and broadleaf glandweed .
Notostylops ( `` South Pillar Face '' ) is a genus of extinct South American ungulate from the Eocene .
Pouteria hotteana , the redmammee , is a species of plant in the Sapotaceae family .
The Crabronidae are a large paraphyletic group ( nominally a family ) of wasps , including nearly all of the species formerly comprising the now - defunct superfamily Sphecoidea .
Ircinia spiculosa is a marine sponge species in the genus Ircinia .
Metzgeriites is a genus of fossil liverwort .
Solidago californica is a species of goldenrod known by the common name California goldenrod .
Eugeissona is a clustering genus of flowering plant in the palm family native to Borneo , Thailand and Malaysia .
Hagenia abyssinica is a species of flowering plant native to the high - elevation Afromontane regions of central and eastern Africa .
Actaea asiatica is species of baneberry that ranges throughout Asia . The flowers are ranges from gray to white .
Athyrium niponicum is a species of fern in the genus Athyrium , native to eastern Asia in Japan , northern China , Korea and Taiwan .
Huperzia megastachya is a species of firmoss ( genus Huperzia ) found exclusively in Madagascar .
Nebria holzunensis is a species of ground beetle from Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Altai region of Russia .
Kachinus is an extinct genus of ant - like stone beetle in the family Staphylinidae containing the single species Kachinus antennatus .
The Seychelles frogs ( Sooglossidae ) are a family of frogs found on the Seychelles Islands and India .
Tapejaridae ( meaning `` the old beings '' ) are a family of pterodactyloid pterosaurs from the Cretaceous period .
Astragalus clevelandii is an uncommon species of milkvetch known by the common name Cleveland 's milkvetch .
Cymopterus aboriginum is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name Indian springparsley .
It contains the single species Lobilema conspersa , which is found in Tanzania .
Mibora , sandgrass , is a genus of European and North African plants in the grass family .
Mycena galericulata is a mushroom species commonly known as the common bonnet , the toque mycena , or the rosy - gill fairy helmet .
Nebaliopsis typica is a species of leptostracan crustacean , the only species in the genus Nebaliopsis .
Borassus akeassii is a species of Palmyra palm from west and central Africa from Senegal to Congo - Kinshasa .
Ewunia gemella is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family that is endemic to Puerto Rico .
Atractus trilineatus , commonly known as the three - lined ground snake , is a species of small burrowing colubrid snake , which is endemic to South America .
Arctostaphylos mendocinoensis is a species of manzanita known by the common name Pygmy manzanita .
Xylocaris oculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Xylocaris .
Opsilia badenkoi is a species of beetle from a Cerambycidae family , which are native to Kazakhstan .
Parachaetodon ocellatus , the Sixspine butterflyfish , is a species of butterflyfish native to tropical reefs of the eastern Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Amaranthus palmeri is a species of edible flowering plant in the amaranth genus .
Delias paoaiensis is a species of pierine butterfly endemic to Cordillera Central Mountains of Luzon , in the Philippines .
Pellaea mucronata is a species of fern known by the common name bird 's foot cliffbrake .
Cermatulus nasalis is a species of predatory shield bug in the family Pentatomidae .
The Hymenolepididae are family of cyclophyllid tapeworms .
Phragmidium rosae - pimpinellifoliae is a species of fungus in the Phragmidiaceae family .
Aspidura ceylonensis , commonly Black - spined snake and as කුරුන් කරවලා ( kurun karawala ) or රත් කරවලා ( rath karawala ) in Sinhala , is a colubird species endemic to Sri Lanka .
Eulima bilineata ( Dutch : gestreepte glanshoren ) is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Eulimidae .
Pterotracheidae is a family of medium - sized to large floating sea snails , pelagic gastropod molluscs .
Erigeron versicolor is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names bald - fruit fleabane and changing fleabane .
Huaiheceras is an ellesmerocerd genus from China , and type for the Heuhiceratidae that lived during the Late Cambrian .
Clostridium tertium is a Gram - positive , spore forming , anaerobic bacillus found in the soil and the gut of many animal species , including humans .
Elasmopoda is a genus in the `` true bug '' family Coreidae , order Hemiptera .
Piperia michaelii is an uncommon species of orchid known by the common names Michael 's rein orchid and Michael 's piperia .
Meliola zangii is a species of fungus in the family Meliolaceae that is found in China .
Penicillium buchwaldii is a fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which produces asperphenamate , citreoisocoumarin , communesin A , communesin B , asperentin and 5'-hydroxy - asperentin
Heliades lindae is a species of moth of the Pyralidae family that is endemic to Arizona .
The Amphidontidae are a family of extinct mammals from the Early Cretaceous , belonging to the triconodonts .
Eriogonum giganteum , with the common name St. Catherine 's lace , is a species of wild buckwheat in Southern California .
Ophiderpeton is an extinct genus of lepospondyl amphibian from the early Carboniferous to the early Permian .
Papilio alexiares , the Mexican Tiger Swallowtail , is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Mexico and southern Texas .
Litthabitella elliptica is a species of very small freshwater snails with a gill and an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrobiidae .
It consists of only one species , Costicoma exangulata , which is found in northern India .
Elipsocus fasciatus is a species of Psocoptera from Elipsocidae family that is endemic to Canary Islands .
Pectenodoris trilineata is a colourful species of sea slug , specifically a dorid nudibranch .
Isotemnidae is an extinct family of notoungulate mammals known from the Paleocene through Oligocene of South America .
Didymoceras nebrascense was an extinct species of heteromorph ammonite from the upper Campanian age ( around 83 to 70 million years ago ) .
Clanculus multipunctatuscommon name the beautiful clanculus , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Thelypteris puberula is a species of fern known by the common name showy maiden fern .
Salix shiraii is a species of willow native to mountains of central Honshū ( Japan ) .
Adenoglossa is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family described as a genus in 1976 .
Zemistephanus is an extinct ammonite genus from the middle Jurassic of western North America and Western Australia , named by McLearn 1927 .
Macrobrachium hancocki is a species of freshwater shrimp found from Costa Rica southwards to Colombia and on the Cocos Islands and the Galápago Islands .
Hydrobasileus brevistylus is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae , commonly known as the Water prince .
Apatopygus recens is a species of sea urchin of the family Apatopygidae .
Vesperus fuentei is a species of beetle in the Vesperidae family that is endemic to Spain .
Pomatiopsis lapidaria is an amphibious species of snail with gills and an operculum , a gastropod mollusk in the family Pomatiopsidae .
Sardinella lemuru ( Bali sardinella ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Sardinella found in the Eastern Indian Ocean and in the Western Pacific Ocean , in the area that stretches from southern Japan through the Malay Archipelago to the western Australia .
Ajaniopsis is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family described as a genus in 1978 .
Oxyalcia mira is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Oxyalcia .
Carrizal virus ( CARV ) is a single - stranded , enveloped , negative - sense RNA hantavirus species of the Bunyaviridae family .
Zygoballus concolor is a species of jumping spider which occurs in Cuba .
Diasemopsis is a genus of stalk - eyed flies in the family Diopsidae .
Fritillaria montana is a European species of flowering plant in the lily family , native to southern and eastern Europe :
Torquigener pleurogramma , commonly known as the weeping toadfish , is a species of fish in the family Tetraodontidae .
Banksia rosserae is a recently described species of Banksia .
Piresiella is a genus of Cuban bamboo in the grass family .
Eucephalus elegans is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name elegant aster .
Penicillium arenicola is an anamorph fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from pine forest soil in Russia .
Erythrobacter litoralis is a species of bacterium .
Helobata is a genus of hydrophilid beetles with 11 species in North and South America .
Latrodectus variolus , the northern black widow spider or northern widow , is a medically important spider species of the genus Latrodectus in the family Theridiidae .
Mylothra mithra is a species of moth in the family Autostichidae .
Notohippidae is an extinct family of notoungulate mammals from South America .
Macrosiphum is a genus of aphid .
Swallenia is a rare genus of plants in the grass family , found only in Death Valley National Park , California .
Retama is a genus of flowering bushes in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Eryx tataricus , known commonly as the Tartar sand boa , is a species of snake in the Boidae family .
Warburgia elongata is a species of plant in the Canellaceae family .
Hydrobia lineata is a small species of freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Phenacoscorpius is a genus of scorpionfishes native to the Atlantic and Pacific oceans .
Ischaemum is a genus of plants in the grass family , widespread in tropical and semitropical regions in many countries .
Angelica kingii is a species of angelica known as King 's angelica .
Melissotarsus is a rare African genus of ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Restrepiella is a genus of orchid native to Mexico , Colombia , Florida and Central America .
Maria Müller ( 29 January 1898 -- 15 March 1958 ) was a Czech - Austrian operatic soprano .
Cecil Arden ( December 15 , 1894 -- September 4 , 1989 ) was an American mezzo - soprano and contralto opera singer active over the early decades of the twentieth century .
Robert Weede ( February 22 , 1903 -- July 9 , 1972 ) was an American operatic baritone .
Stéphanie d'Oustrac ( born 1974 in Rennes ) is a French mezzo - soprano .
Erika Miklósa ( born June 9 , 1971 in Kiskunhalas ) , is a Hungarian coloratura soprano .
Dinh Gilly ( July 19 , 1877 -- May 19 , 1940 ) was a French - Algerian operatic baritone and teacher .
Wim Mertens ( born 14 May 1953 ) is a Flemish Belgian composer , countertenor vocalist , pianist , guitarist , and musicologist .
Karl Erb ( 13 July 1877 -- 13 July 1958 ) was a German tenor vocalist who made his career first in opera and then in oratorio and lieder recital .
Neva Pilgrim ( born in Minnesota , United States ) is an American soprano known for her work in the performance of contemporary classical music .
Maurice Renaud ( 24 July 1861 -- 16 October 1933 ) was a cultured French operatic baritone .
